obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5116)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5116&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Central Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act, 2017.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint:`
  line
  line `Provided that different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference in any such provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force of that provision.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 26 of 2017, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-7-2017).`
  line
  line `2. 22nd, June, 2017 for sections 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 10, 22, 23, 24, 25, 26, 27, 28, 29, 30, 139, 146 and 164, vide notification No. G.S.R. 605 (E) dated the 19 June, 2017, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `1st July, 2017 for sections 6 to 9, 11 to 21, 31 to 41, 42 except the proviso to sub-section (9) of section 42, 43 except the proviso to sub-section (9) of section 43, 44 to 50, 53 to 138, 140 to 145, 147 to 163, 165 to 174 vide notification No. G.S.R. 658 (E) dated the 28th June, 2017, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5117)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5117&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(1) "actionable claim" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 3 of the Transfer`
  line `of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882);`
  line
  line `(2) "address of delivery" means the address of the recipient of goods or services or both indicated`
  line `on the tax invoice issued by a registered person for delivery of such goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(3) "address on record" means the address of the recipient as available in the records of the`
  line supplier;
  line
  line `(4) "adjudicating authority" means any authority, appointed or authorised to pass any order or decision`
  line `under this Act, but does not include the ^1[Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs], the Revisional`
  line `Authority, the Authority for Advance Ruling, the Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling, ^2[the National`
  line `Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling,]`
  line `^3[the Appellate Authority, the Appellate Tribunal and the`
  line `Authority referred to in sub-section (2) of section 171];`
  line
  line `(5) "agent" means a person, including a factor, broker, commission agent, arhatia, del credere`
  line `agent, an auctioneer or any other mercantile agent, by whatever name called, who carries on the`
  line `business of supply or receipt of goods or services or both on behalf of another;`
  line
  line `(6) "aggregate turnover" means the aggregate value of all taxable supplies (excluding the value of`
  line `inward supplies on which tax is payable by a person on reverse charge basis), exempt supplies, exports of`
  line `goods or services or both and inter-State supplies of persons having the same Permanent Account Number, to`
  line `be computed on all India basis but excludes central tax, State tax, Union territory tax, integrated tax and cess;`
  line
  line `(7) "agriculturist" means an individual or a Hindu Undivided Family who undertakes cultivation`
  line `of land---`
  line
  line `(a) by own labour, or`
  line
  line `(b) by the labour of family, or`
  line
  line `(c) by servants on wages payable in cash or kind or by hired labour under personal supervision`
  line `or the personal supervision of any member of the family;`
  line
  line `(8) "Appellate Authority" means an authority appointed or authorised to hear appeals as referred`
  line `to in section 107;`
  line
  line `(9) "Appellate Tribunal" means the Goods and Services Tax Appellate Tribunal constituted under`
  line `section 109;`
  line
  line `(10) "appointed day" means the date on which the provisions of this Act shall come into force;`
  line
  line `(11) "assessment" means determination of tax liability under this Act and includes`
  line `self-assessment, re-assessment, provisional assessment, summary assessment and best judgment`
  line assessment;
  line
  line `(12) "associated enterprises" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 92A of the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(13) "audit" means the examination of records, returns and other documents maintained or`
  line `furnished by the registered person under this Act or the rules made thereunder or under any other law`
  line `for the time being in force to verify the correctness of turnover declared, taxes paid, refund claimed and`
  line `input tax credit availed, and to assess his compliance with the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(14) "authorised bank" shall mean a bank or a branch of a bank authorised by the Government to`
  line `collect the tax or any other amount payable under this Act;`
  line
  line `(15) "authorised representative" means the representative as referred to in section 116;`
  line
  line `(16) "Board" means the ^4[Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs] constituted under the`
  line `Central Boards of Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963);`
  line
  line `(17) "business" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) any trade, commerce, manufacture, profession, vocation, adventure, wager or any other`
  line `similar activity, whether or not it is for a pecuniary benefit;`
  line
  line `(b) any activity or transaction in connection with or incidental or ancillary to sub-clause (a) ;`
  line
  line `(c) any activity or transaction in the nature of sub-clause (a) , whether or not there is volume,`
  line `frequency, continuity or regularity of such transaction;`
  line
  line `(d) supply or acquisition of goods including capital goods and services in connection with`
  line `commencement or closure of business;`
  line
  line `(e) provision by a club, association, society, or any such body (for a subscription or any other`
  line `consideration) of the facilities or benefits to its members;`
  line
  line `(f) admission, for a consideration, of persons to any premises;`
  line
  line `(g) services supplied by a person as the holder of an office which has been accepted by him in the`
  line `course or furtherance of his trade, profession or vocation;`
  line
  line `^5[(h) activities of a race club including by way of totalisator or a license to book maker or`
  line `activities of a licensed book maker in such club; and]`
  line
  line `(i) any activity or transaction undertaken by the Central Government, a State Government or`
  line `any local authority in which they are engaged as public authorities;`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(19) "capital goods" means goods, the value of which is capitalised in the books of account of the`
  line `person claiming the input tax credit and which are used or intended to be used in the course or`
  line `furtherance of business;`
  line
  line `(20) "casual taxable person" means a person who occasionally undertakes transactions involving`
  line `supply of goods or services or both in the course or furtherance of business, whether as principal, agent`
  line `or in any other capacity, in a State or a Union territory where he has no fixed place of business;`
  line
  line `(21) "central tax" means the central goods and services tax levied under section 9;`
  line
  line `(22) "cess" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in the Goods and Services Tax`
  line `(Compensation to States) Act;`
  line
  line `(23) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949);`
  line
  line `(24) "Commissioner" means the Commissioner of central tax and includes the Principal`
  line `Commissioner of central tax appointed under section 3 and the Commissioner of integrated tax`
  line `appointed under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(25) "Commissioner in the Board" means the Commissioner referred to in section 168;`
  line
  line `(26) "common portal" means the common goods and services tax electronic portal referred to in`
  line `section 146;`
  line
  line `(27) "common working days" in respect of a State or Union territory shall mean such days in`
  line `succession which are not declared as gazetted holidays by the Central Government or the concerned`
  line `State or Union territory Government;`
  line
  line `(28) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(29) "competent authority" means such authority as may be notified by the Government;`
  line
  line `(30) "composite supply" means a supply made by a taxable person to a recipient consisting of two`
  line `or more taxable supplies of goods or services or both, or any combination thereof, which are naturally`
  line `bundled and supplied in conjunction with each other in the ordinary course of business, one of which`
  line `is a principal supply;`
  line
  line `Illustration.--- Where goods are packed and transported with insurance, the supply of goods,`
  line `packing materials, transport and insurance is a composite supply and supply of goods is a principal`
  line supply;
  line
  line `(31) "consideration" in relation to the supply of goods or services or both includes---`
  line
  line `(a) any payment made or to be made, whether in money or otherwise, in respect of, in`
  line `response to, or for the inducement of, the supply of goods or services or both, whether by the`
  line `recipient or by any other person but shall not include any subsidy given by the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the monetary value of any act or forbearance, in respect of, in response to, or for the`
  line `inducement of, the supply of goods or services or both, whether by the recipient or by any other`
  line `person but shall not include any subsidy given by the Central Government or a State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that a deposit given in respect of the supply of goods or services or both shall not be`
  line `considered as payment made for such supply unless the supplier applies such deposit as consideration`
  line `for the said supply;`
  line
  line `(32) "continuous supply of goods" means a supply of goods which is provided, or agreed to be`
  line `provided, continuously or on recurrent basis, under a contract, whether or not by means of a wire,`
  line `cable, pipeline or other conduit, and for which the supplier invoices the recipient on a regular or`
  line `periodic basis and includes supply of such goods as the Government may, subject to such conditions,`
  line `as it may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(33) "continuous supply of services" means a supply of services which is provided, or agreed to`
  line `be provided, continuously or on recurrent basis, under a contract, for a period exceeding three months`
  line `with periodic payment obligations and includes supply of such services as the Government may,`
  line `subject to such conditions, as it may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(34) "conveyance" includes a vessel, an aircraft and a vehicle;`
  line
  line `(35) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in ^7[clause (b)] of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959);`
  line
  line `(36) "Council" means the Goods and Services Tax Council established under article 279A of the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(37) "credit note" means a document issued by a registered person under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(38) "debit note" means a document issued by a registered person under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 34;`
  line
  line `(39) "deemed exports" means such supplies of goods as may be notified under section 147;`
  line
  line `(40) "designated authority" means such authority as may be notified by the Board;`
  line
  line `(41) "document" includes written or printed record of any sort and electronic record as defined in`
  line `clause (t) of section 2 of the Information Technology Act, 2000 (21 of 2000);`
  line
  line `(42) "drawback" in relation to any goods manufactured in India and exported, means the rebate of`
  line `duty, tax or cess chargeable on any imported inputs or on any domestic inputs or input services used`
  line `in the manufacture of such goods;`
  line
  line `(43) "electronic cash ledger" means the electronic cash ledger referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 49;`
  line
  line `(44) "electronic commerce" means the supply of goods or services or both, including digital`
  line `products over digital or electronic network;`
  line
  line `(45) "electronic commerce operator" means any person who owns, operates or manages digital or`
  line `electronic facility or platform for electronic commerce;`
  line
  line `(46) "electronic credit ledger" means the electronic credit ledger referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 49;`
  line
  line `(47) "exempt supply" means supply of any goods or services or both which attracts nil rate of tax`
  line `or which may be wholly exempt from tax under section 11, or under section 6 of the Integrated Goods`
  line `and Services Tax Act, and includes non-taxable supply;`
  line
  line `(48) "existing law" means any law, notification, order, rule or regulation relating to levy and`
  line `collection of duty or tax on goods or services or both passed or made before the commencement of`
  line `this Act by Parliament or any Authority or person having the power to make such law, notification,`
  line `order, rule or regulation;`
  line
  line `(49) "family" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) the spouse and children of the person, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the parents, grand-parents, brothers and sisters of the person if they are wholly or mainly`
  line `dependent on the said person;`
  line
  line `(50) "fixed establishment" means a place (other than the registered place of business) which is`
  line `characterised by a sufficient degree of permanence and suitable structure in terms of human and`
  line `technical resources to supply services, or to receive and use services for its own needs;`
  line
  line `(51) "Fund" means the Consumer Welfare Fund established under section 57;`
  line
  line `(52) "goods" means every kind of movable property other than money and securities but includes`
  line `actionable claim, growing crops, grass and things attached to or forming part of the land which are`
  line `agreed to be severed before supply or under a contract of supply;`
  line
  line `(53) "Government" means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(54) "Goods and Services Tax (Compensation to States) Act" means the Goods and Services Tax`
  line `(Compensation to States) Act, 2017 (15 of 2017);`
  line
  line `(55) "goods and services tax practitioner" means any person who has been approved under`
  line `section 48 to act as such practitioner;`
  line
  line `(56) "India" means the territory of India as referred to in article 1 of the Constitution, its territorial`
  line `waters, seabed and sub-soil underlying such waters, continental shelf, exclusive economic zone or any`
  line `other maritime zone as referred to in the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive Economic Zone`
  line `and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), and the air space above its territory and territorial`
  line waters;
  line
  line `(57) "Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act" means the Integrated Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act, 2017 (13 of 2017);`
  line
  line `(58) "integrated tax" means the integrated goods and services tax levied under the Integrated`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(59) "input" means any goods other than capital goods used or intended to be used by a supplier`
  line `in the course or furtherance of business;`
  line
  line `(60) "input service" means any service used or intended to be used by a supplier in the course or`
  line `furtherance of business;`
  line
  line `^8[(61) "Input Service Distributor" means an office of the supplier of goods or services or both`
  line `which receives tax invoices towards the receipt of input services, including invoices in respect of`
  line `services liable to tax under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 9 ^9[of this Act or under`
  line `sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 5 of the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (13`
  line `of 2017)], for or on behalf of distinct persons referred to in section 25, and liable to distribute the`
  line `input tax credit in respect of such invoices in the manner provided in section 20;]`
  line
  line `(62) "input tax" in relation to a registered person, means the central tax, State tax, integrated tax`
  line `or Union territory tax charged on any supply of goods or services or both made to him and includes---`
  line
  line `(a) the integrated goods and services tax charged on import of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) the tax payable under the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(c) the tax payable under the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 5 of the`
  line `Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the tax payable under the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 9 of the`
  line `respective State Goods and Services Tax Act; or`
  line
  line `(e) the tax payable under the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 7 of the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act,`
  line
  line `but does not include the tax paid under the composition levy;`
  line
  line `(63) "input tax credit" means the credit of input tax;`
  line
  line `(64) "intra-State supply of goods" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 8 of`
  line `the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(65) "intra-State supply of services" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in section 8 of`
  line `the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(66) "invoice" or "tax invoice" means the tax invoice referred to in section 31;`
  line
  line `(67) "inward supply" in relation to a person, shall mean receipt of goods or services or both`
  line `whether by purchase, acquisition or any other means with or without consideration;`
  line
  line `(68) "job work" means any treatment or process undertaken by a person on goods belonging to`
  line `another registered person and the expression "job worker" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(69) "local authority" means---`
  line
  line `(a) a "Panchayat" as defined in clause (d) of article 243 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(b) a "Municipality" as defined in clause (e) of article 243P of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(c) a Municipal Committee, a Zilla Parishad, a District Board, and any other authority legally`
  line `entitled to, or entrusted by the Central Government or any State Government with the control or`
  line `management of a municipal or local fund;`
  line
  line `(d) a Cantonment Board as defined in section 3 of the Cantonments Act, 2006 (41 of 2006);`
  line
  line `(e) a Regional Council or a District Council constituted under the Sixth Schedule to the`
  line Constitution;
  line
  line `(f) a Development Board constituted under article 371 ^10[and article 371J] of the Constitution;`
  line or
  line
  line `(g) a Regional Council constituted under article 371A of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(70) "location of the recipient of services" means,---`
  line
  line `(a) where a supply is received at a place of business for which the registration has been`
  line `obtained, the location of such place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) where a supply is received at a place other than the place of business for which`
  line `registration has been obtained (a fixed establishment elsewhere), the location of such fixed`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(c) where a supply is received at more than one establishment, whether the place of`
  line `business or fixed establishment, the location of the establishment most directly concerned`
  line `with the receipt of the supply; and`
  line
  line `(d) in absence of such places, the location of the usual place of residence of the recipient;`
  line
  line `(71) "location of the supplier of services" means,---`
  line
  line `(a) where a supply is made from a place of business for which the registration has been`
  line `obtained, the location of such place of business;`
  line
  line `(b) where a supply is made from a place other than the place of business for which`
  line `registration has been obtained (a fixed establishment elsewhere), the location of such fixed`
  line establishment;
  line
  line `(c) where a supply is made from more than one establishment, whether the place of`
  line `business or fixed establishment, the location of the establishment most directly concerned`
  line `with the provisions of the supply; and`
  line
  line `(d) in absence of such places, the location of the usual place of residence of the supplier;`
  line
  line `(72) "manufacture" means processing of raw material or inputs in any manner that results in`
  line `emergence of a new product having a distinct name, character and use and the term "manufacturer"`
  line `shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(73) "market value" shall mean the full amount which a recipient of a supply is required to pay in`
  line `order to obtain the goods or services or both of like kind and quality at or about the same time and at the`
  line `same commercial level where the recipient and the supplier are not related;`
  line
  line `(74) "mixed supply" means two or more individual supplies of goods or services, or any combination`
  line `thereof, made in conjunction with each other by a taxable person for a single price where such supply`
  line `does not constitute a composite supply.`
  line
  line `Illustration.--- A supply of a package consisting of canned foods, sweets, chocolates, cakes, dry`
  line `fruits, aerated drinks and fruit juices when supplied for a single price is a mixed supply. Each of these`
  line `items can be supplied separately and is not dependent on any other. It shall not be a mixed supply if`
  line `these items are supplied separately;`
  line
  line `(75) "money" means the Indian legal tender or any foreign currency, cheque, promissory note, bill of`
  line `exchange, letter of credit, draft, pay order, traveller cheque, money order, postal or electronic remittance or`
  line `any other instrument recognised by the Reserve Bank of India when used as a consideration to settle an`
  line `obligation or exchange with Indian legal tender of another denomination but shall not include any`
  line `currency that is held for its numismatic value;`
  line
  line `(76) "motor vehicle" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (28) of section 2 of`
  line `the Motor Vehicles Act, 1988 (59 of 1988);`
  line
  line `(77) "non-resident taxable person" means any person who occasionally undertakes transactions`
  line `involving supply of goods or services or both, whether as principal or agent or in any other capacity,`
  line `but who has no fixed place of business or residence in India;`
  line
  line `(78) "non-taxable supply" means a supply of goods or services or both which is not leviable to tax`
  line `under this Act or under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(79) "non-taxable territory" means the territory which is outside the taxable territory;`
  line
  line `(80) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expressions`
  line `"notify" and "notified" shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `^11[(80A) "online gaming" means offering of a game on the internet or an electronic network and`
  line `includes online money gaming;`
  line
  line `(80B) "online money gaming" means online gaming in which players pay or deposit money or`
  line `money's worth, including virtual digital assets, in the expectation of winning money or money's`
  line `worth, including virtual digital assets, in any event including game, scheme, competition or any other`
  line `activity or process, whether or not its outcome or performance is based on skill, chance or both and`
  line `whether the same is permissible or otherwise under any other law for the time being in force;]`
  line
  line `(81) "other territory" includes territories other than those comprising in a State and those referred`
  line `to in sub-clauses (a) to (e) of clause (114);`
  line
  line `(82) "output tax" in relation to a taxable person, means the tax chargeable under this Act on`
  line `taxable supply of goods or services or both made by him or by his agent but excludes tax payable by`
  line `him on reverse charge basis;`
  line
  line `(83) "outward supply" in relation to a taxable person, means supply of goods or services or both,`
  line `whether by sale, transfer, barter, exchange, licence, rental, lease or disposal or any other mode, made`
  line `or agreed to be made by such person in the course or furtherance of business;`
  line
  line `(84) "person" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) an individual;`
  line
  line `(b) a Hindu Undivided Family;`
  line
  line `(c) a company;`
  line
  line `(d) a firm;`
  line
  line `(e) a Limited Liability Partnership;`
  line
  line `(f) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, in India or`
  line `outside India;`
  line
  line `(g) any corporation established by or under any Central Act, State Act or Provincial Act or a`
  line `Government company as defined in clause (45) of section 2 of the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(h) any body corporate incorporated by or under the laws of a country outside India;`
  line
  line `(i) a co-operative society registered under any law relating to co-operative societies;`
  line
  line `(j) a local authority;`
  line
  line `(k) Central Government or a State Government;`
  line
  line `(l) society as defined under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(m) trust; and`
  line
  line `(n) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the above;`
  line
  line `(85) "place of business" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) a place from where the business is ordinarily carried on, and includes a warehouse, a`
  line `godown or any other place where a taxable person stores his goods, supplies or receives goods or`
  line `services or both; or`
  line
  line `(b) a place where a taxable person maintains his books of account; or`
  line
  line `(c) a place where a taxable person is engaged in business through an agent, by whatever name`
  line called;
  line
  line `(86) "place of supply" means the place of supply as referred to in Chapter V of the Integrated`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(87) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act on the recommendations of the`
  line Council;
  line
  line `(88) "principal" means a person on whose behalf an agent carries on the business of supply or`
  line `receipt of goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(89) "principal place of business" means the place of business specified as the principal place of`
  line `business in the certificate of registration;`
  line
  line `(90) "principal supply" means the supply of goods or services which constitutes the predominant`
  line `element of a composite supply and to which any other supply forming part of that composite supply is`
  line ancillary;
  line
  line `(91) "proper officer" in relation to any function to be performed under this Act, means the`
  line `Commissioner or the officer of the central tax who is assigned that function by the Commissioner in`
  line `the Board;`
  line
  line `(92) "quarter" shall mean a period comprising three consecutive calendar months, ending on the last`
  line `day of March, June, September and December of a calendar year;`
  line
  line `(93) "recipient" of supply of goods or services or both, means---`
  line
  line `(a) where a consideration is payable for the supply of goods or services or both, the person`
  line `who is liable to pay that consideration;`
  line
  line `(b) where no consideration is payable for the supply of goods, the person to whom the goods`
  line `are delivered or made available, or to whom possession or use of the goods is given or made`
  line `available; and`
  line
  line `(c) where no consideration is payable for the supply of a service, the person to whom the`
  line `service is rendered,`
  line
  line `and any reference to a person to whom a supply is made shall be construed as a reference to the`
  line `recipient of the supply and shall include an agent acting as such on behalf of the recipient in relation`
  line `to the goods or services or both supplied;`
  line
  line `(94) "registered person" means a person who is registered under section 25 but does not include a`
  line `person having a Unique Identity Number;`
  line
  line `(95) "regulations" means the regulations made by the Board under this Act on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council;`
  line
  line `(96) "removal" in relation to goods, means---`
  line
  line `(a) despatch of the goods for delivery by the supplier thereof or by any other person acting on`
  line `behalf of such supplier; or`
  line
  line `(b) collection of the goods by the recipient thereof or by any other person acting on behalf of`
  line `such recipient;`
  line
  line `(97) "return" means any return prescribed or otherwise required to be furnished by or under this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(98) "reverse charge" means the liability to pay tax by the recipient of supply of goods or services`
  line `or both instead of the supplier of such goods or services or both under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 9, or under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 5 of the Integrated Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(99) "Revisional Authority" means an authority appointed or authorised for revision of decision`
  line `or orders as referred to in section 108;`
  line
  line `(100) "Schedule" means a Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(101) "securities" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (h) of section 2 of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(102) "services" means anything other than goods, money and securities but includes activities`
  line `relating to the use of money or its conversion by cash or by any other mode, from one form, currency`
  line `or denomination, to another form, currency or denomination for which a separate consideration is`
  line charged;
  line
  line `^10[Explanation.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression "services"`
  line `includes facilitating or arranging transactions in securities;]`
  line
  line `^11[(102A) "specified actionable claim" means the actionable claim involved in or by way of---`
  line
  line `(i) betting;`
  line
  line `(ii) casinos;`
  line
  line `(iii) gambling;`
  line
  line `(iv) horse racing;`
  line
  line `(v) lottery; or`
  line
  line `(vi) online money gaming;]`
  line
  line `(103) "State" includes a Union territory with Legislature;`
  line
  line `(104) "State tax" means the tax levied under any State Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(105) "supplier" in relation to any goods or services or both, shall mean the person supplying the`
  line `said goods or services or both and shall include an agent acting as such on behalf of such supplier in`
  line `relation to the goods or services or both supplied;`
  line
  line `^11[Provided that a person who organises or arranges, directly or indirectly, supply of specified`
  line `actionable claims, including a person who owns, operates or manages digital or electronic platform`
  line `for such supply, shall be deemed to be a supplier of such actionable claims, whether such actionable`
  line `claims are supplied by him or through him and whether consideration in money or money's worth,`
  line `including virtual digital assets, for supply of such actionable claims is paid or conveyed to him or`
  line `through him or placed at his disposal in any manner, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to`
  line `such supplier of specified actionable claims, as if he is the supplier liable to pay the tax in relation to`
  line `the supply of such actionable claims;]`
  line
  line `(106) "tax period" means the period for which the return is required to be furnished;`
  line
  line `(107) "taxable person" means a person who is registered or liable to be registered under`
  line `section 22 or section 24;`
  line
  line `(108) "taxable supply" means a supply of goods or services or both which is leviable to tax under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(109) "taxable territory" means the territory to which the provisions of this Act apply;`
  line
  line `(110) "telecommunication service" means service of any description (including electronic mail,`
  line `voice mail, data services, audio text services, video text services, radio paging and cellular mobile`
  line `telephone services) which is made available to users by means of any transmission or reception of`
  line `signs, signals, writing, images and sounds or intelligence of any nature, by wire, radio, visual or other`
  line `electromagnetic means;`
  line
  line `(111) "the State Goods and Services Tax Act" means the respective State Goods and Services`
  line `Tax Act, 2017;`
  line
  line `(112) "turnover in State" or "turnover in Union territory" means the aggregate value of all taxable`
  line `supplies (excluding the value of inward supplies on which tax is payable by a person on reverse charge`
  line `basis) and exempt supplies made within a State or Union territory by a taxable person, exports of goods`
  line `or services or both and inter-State supplies of goods or services or both made from the State or Union`
  line `territory by the said taxable person but excludes central tax, State tax, Union territory tax, integrated tax`
  line `and cess;`
  line
  line `(113) "usual place of residence" means---`
  line
  line `(a) in case of an individual, the place where he ordinarily resides;`
  line
  line `(b) in other cases, the place where the person is incorporated or otherwise legally constituted;`
  line
  line `(114) "Union territory" means the territory of---`
  line
  line `(a) the Andaman and Nicobar Islands;`
  line
  line `(b) Lakshadweep;`
  line
  line `^12[(c) Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Daman and Diu;`
  line
  line `(d) Ladakh;]`
  line
  line `(e) Chandigarh; ^13***`
  line
  line `^14[(ea) Ladakh; and;]`
  line
  line `(f) other territory.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this Act, each of the territories specified in sub-clauses (a)`
  line `to (f) shall be considered to be a separate Union territory;`
  line
  line `(115) "Union territory tax" means the Union territory goods and services tax levied under the`
  line `Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(116) "Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act" means the Union Territory Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act, 2017 (14 of 2017);`
  line
  line `(117) "valid return" means a return furnished under sub-section (1) of section 39 on which`
  line `self-assessed tax has been paid in full;`
  line
  line `^15[(117A) "virtual digital asset" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (47A) of`
  line `Section 2 of the Income Tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);]`
  line
  line `(118) "voucher" means an instrument where there is an obligation to accept it as consideration or`
  line `part consideration for a supply of goods or services or both and where the goods or services or both to`
  line `be supplied or the identities of their potential suppliers are either indicated on the instrument itself or`
  line `in related documentation, including the terms and conditions of use of such instrument;`
  line
  line `(119) "works contract" means a contract for building, construction, fabrication, completion,`
  line `erection, installation, fitting out, improvement, modification, repair, maintenance, renovation, alteration`
  line `or commissioning of any immovable property wherein transfer of property in goods (whether as goods`
  line `or in some other form) is involved in the execution of such contract;`
  line
  line `(120) words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Integrated Goods`
  line `and Services Tax Act, the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act and the Goods and Services`
  line `Tax (Compensation to States) Act shall have the same meaning as assigned to them in those Acts;`
  line
  line `^16* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 2, for "Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 2, for "the Appellate Authority and the Appellate Tribunal" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 221, for "Central Board of Excise and Customs" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 2, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Clause (18) omitted by s. 2, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "clause (c)" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 8 of 2024, s. 11, for "clause (61)" (w.e.f. 01-04-2025).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 7 of 2025, s. 121 (w.e.f. 01-04-2025).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 30 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 118, for sub-clauses (c) and (d) (w.e.f. 30-6-2020).`
  line
  line `13. The Word "and" omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide Notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, Notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
  line
  line `* vide Notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide Notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 30 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `16. Clause (121) omitted by the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No. S.O. 1123(E), dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5118)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Officers under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5118&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Government shall, by notification, appoint the following classes of`
  line `officers for the purposes of this Act, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Principal Chief Commissioners of Central Tax or Principal Directors General of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(b) Chief Commissioners of Central Tax or Directors General of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(c) Principal Commissioners of Central Tax or Principal Additional Directors General of Central`
  line Tax,
  line
  line `(d) Commissioners of Central Tax or Additional Directors General of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(e) Additional Commissioners of Central Tax or Additional Directors of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(f) Joint Commissioners of Central Tax or Joint Directors of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(g) Deputy Commissioners of Central Tax or Deputy Directors of Central Tax,`
  line
  line `(h) Assistant Commissioners of Central Tax or Assistant Directors of Central Tax, and`
  line
  line `(i) any other class of officers as it may deem fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officers appointed under the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) shall be deemed`
  line `to be the officers appointed under the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5119)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5119&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, in addition to the officers as may be notified by the`
  line `Government under section 3, appoint such persons as it may think fit to be the officers under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board may, by order, authorise any`
  line `officer referred to in clauses (a) to (h) of section 3 to appoint officers of central tax below the rank of`
  line `Assistant Commissioner of central tax for the administration of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5120)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Powers of officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5120&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions and limitations as the Board may impose, an`
  line `officer of central tax may exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed on him`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) An officer of central tax may exercise the powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed under`
  line `this Act on any other officer of central tax who is subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may, subject to such conditions and limitations as may be specified in this`
  line `behalf by him, delegate his powers to any other officer who is subordinate to him.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, an Appellate Authority shall not exercise the`
  line `powers and discharge the duties conferred or imposed on any other officer of central tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5121)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Authorisation of officers of State tax or Union territory tax as proper officer in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5121&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of this Act, the officers appointed under the`
  line `State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act are authorised to`
  line `be the proper officers for the purposes of this Act, subject to such conditions as the Government shall, on`
  line `the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the conditions specified in the notification issued under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) where any proper officer issues an order under this Act, he shall also issue an order under the`
  line `State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, as authorised`
  line `by the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, as the`
  line `case may be, under intimation to the jurisdictional officer of State tax or Union territory tax;`
  line
  line `(b) where a proper officer under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act has initiated any proceedings on a subject matter, no proceedings shall`
  line `be initiated by the proper officer under this Act on the same subject matter.`
  line
  line `(3) Any proceedings for rectification, appeal and revision, wherever applicable, of any order passed`
  line `by an officer appointed under this Act shall not lie before an officer appointed under the State Goods and`
  line `Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5122)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Scope of supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5122&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the expression "supply" includes---`
  line
  line `(a) all forms of supply of goods or services or both such as sale, transfer, barter, exchange,`
  line `licence, rental, lease or disposal made or agreed to be made for a consideration by a person in the`
  line `course or furtherance of business;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the activities or transactions, by a person, other than an individual, to its members or`
  line `constituents or vice-versa, for cash, deferred payment or other valuable consideration.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this clause, it is hereby clarified that, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or any judgment, decree or order`
  line `of any Court, tribunal or authority, the person and its members or constituents shall be deemed to`
  line `be two separate persons and the supply of activities or transactions inter se shall be deemed to`
  line `take place from one such person to another;]`
  line
  line `(b) import of services for a consideration whether or not in the course or furtherance of business;^2[and]`
  line
  line `(c) the activities specified in Schedule I, made or agreed to be made without a consideration;^3***`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^2[(1A) Where certain activities or transactions constitute a supply in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (1), they shall be treated either as supply of goods or supply of services as referred to in Schedule II.]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),---`
  line
  line `(a) activities or transactions specified in Schedule III; or`
  line
  line `(b) such activities or transactions undertaken by the Central Government, a State Government or`
  line `any local authority in which they are engaged as public authorities, as may be notified by the`
  line `Government on the recommendations of the Council,`
  line
  line `shall be treated neither as a supply of goods nor a supply of services.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of ^5[sub-sections (1), (1A) and (2)], the Government may, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, specify, by notification, the transactions that are to be treated as---`
  line
  line `(a) a supply of goods and not as a supply of services; or`
  line
  line `(b) a supply of services and not as a supply of goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 108 (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Cl. (d) omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "sub-sections (1) and (2)" (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5123)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Tax liability on composite and mixed supplies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5123&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The tax liability on a composite or a mixed`
  line `supply shall be determined in the following manner, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a composite supply comprising two or more supplies, one of which is a principal supply, shall`
  line `be treated as a supply of such principal supply; and`
  line
  line `(b) a mixed supply comprising two or more supplies shall be treated as a supply of that particular`
  line `supply which attracts the highest rate of tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5124)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Levy and collection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5124&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), there shall be levied a tax`
  line `called the central goods and services tax on all intra-State supplies of goods or services or both, except on`
  line `the supply of alcoholic liquor for human consumption ^1[and un-denatured extra neutral alcohol or`
  line `rectified spirit used for manufacture of alcoholic liquor, for human consumption], on the value determined under section 15 and at`
  line `such rates, not exceeding twenty per cent., as may be notified by the Government on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council and collected in such manner as may be prescribed and shall be paid by`
  line `the taxable person.`
  line
  line `(2) The central tax on the supply of petroleum crude, high speed diesel, motor spirit (commonly known as petrol), natural gas and aviation turbine fuel shall be levied with effect from such date as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify categories`
  line `of supply of goods or services or both, the tax on which shall be paid on reverse charge basis by the`
  line `recipient of such goods or services or both and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such recipient`
  line `as if he is the person liable for paying the tax in relation to the supply of such goods or services or both.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify a class of registered persons who shall, in respect of supply of specified categories of goods or services or both received from an unregistered supplier, pay the tax on reverse charge basis as the recipient of such supply of goods or services or both, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such recipient as if he is the person liable for paying the tax in relation to such supply of goods or services or both.]`
  line
  line `(5) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify categories of services the tax on intra-State supplies of which shall be paid by the electronic commerce operator if such services are supplied through it, and all the provisions of this Act shall apply to such electronic commerce operator as if he is the supplier liable for paying the tax in relation to the supply of such services:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an electronic commerce operator does not have a physical presence in the taxable`
  line `territory, any person representing such electronic commerce operator for any purpose in the taxable territory`
  line `shall be liable to pay tax:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where an electronic commerce operator does not have a physical presence in the`
  line `taxable territory and also he does not have a representative in the said territory, such electronic commerce`
  line `operator shall appoint a person in the taxable territory for the purpose of paying tax and such person shall`
  line `be liable to pay tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 4, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5125)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Composition levy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5125&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act but`
  line `subject to the provisions of sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 9, a registered person, whose aggregate`
  line `turnover in the preceding financial year did not exceed fifty lakh rupees, may opt to pay, ^1[in lieu of the`
  line `tax payable by him under sub-section (1) of section 9, an amount of tax calculated at such rate] as may be`
  line `prescribed, but not exceeding,--`
  line
  line `(a) one per cent. of the turnover in State or turnover in Union territory in case of a manufacturer,`
  line
  line `(b) two and a half per cent. of the turnover in State or turnover in Union territory in case of`
  line `persons engaged in making supplies referred to in clause (b) of paragraph 6 of Schedule II, and`
  line
  line `(c) half per cent. of the turnover in State or turnover in Union territory in case of other suppliers,`
  line
  line `subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, by notification, increase the said limit of fifty lakh rupees to such`
  line `higher amount, not exceeding ^2[one crore and fifty lakh rupees], as may be recommended by the Council:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that a person who opts to pay tax under clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) may`
  line `supply services (other than those referred to in clause (b) of paragraph 6 of Schedule II), of value not`
  line `exceeding ten per cent. of turnover in a State or Union territory in the preceding financial year or five lakh`
  line `rupees, whichever is higher.]`
  line
  line `^4[Explanation.--For the purposes of second proviso, the value of exempt supply of services provided`
  line `by way of extending deposits, loans or advances in so far as the consideration is represented by way of`
  line `interest or discount shall not be taken into account for determining the value of turnover in a State or`
  line `Union territory.]`
  line
  line `(2) The registered person shall be eligible to opt under sub-section (1), if:---`
  line
  line `^5[(a) save as provided in sub-section (1), he is not engaged in the supply of services;]`
  line
  line `(b) he is not engaged in making any supply of goods ^6[or services] which are not leviable to tax`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) he is not engaged in making any inter-State outward supplies of goods ^6[or services];`
  line
  line `(d) he is not engaged in making any supply of ^7*** ^6[or services] through an electronic commerce`
  line `operator who is required to collect tax at source under section 52; ^8***`
  line
  line `(e) he is not a manufacturer of such goods as may be notified by the Government on the`
  line `recommendations of the ^9[Council; and]`
  line
  line `^10[(f) he is neither a casual taxable person nor a non-resident taxable person:]`
  line
  line `Provided that where more than one registered persons are having the same Permanent Account Number`
  line `(issued under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the registered person shall not be eligible to opt for the`
  line `scheme under sub-section (1) unless all such registered persons opt to pay tax under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `^10[(2A) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, but subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 9, a registered person, not eligible to opt to pay tax under`
  line `sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), whose aggregate turnover in the preceding financial year did not`
  line `exceed fifty lakh rupees, may opt to pay, in lieu of the tax payable by him under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 9, an amount of tax calculated at such rate as may be prescribed, but not exceeding three per cent.`
  line `of the turnover in State or turnover in Union territory, if he is not---`
  line
  line `(a) engaged in making any supply of goods or services which are not leviable to tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) engaged in making any inter-State outward supplies of goods or services;`
  line
  line `(c) engaged in making any supply of ^7*** services through an electronic commerce operator`
  line `who is required to collect tax at source under section 52;`
  line
  line `(d) a manufacturer of such goods or supplier of such services as may be notified by the`
  line `Government on the recommendations of the Council; and`
  line
  line `(e) a casual taxable person or a non-resident taxable person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where more than one registered person are having the same Permanent Account Number`
  line `issued under the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961), the registered person shall not be eligible to opt for`
  line `the scheme under this sub-section unless all such registered persons opt to pay tax under this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `(3) The option availed of by a registered person under sub-section (1) ^10[or sub-section (2A), as the`
  line `case may be] shall lapse with effect from the day on which his aggregate turnover during a financial year`
  line `exceeds the limit specified under sub-section (1) ^10[or sub-section (2A), as the case may be].`
  line
  line `(4) A taxable person to whom the provisions of sub-section (1) ^10[or, as the case may be, sub-section`
  line `(2A)] apply shall not collect any tax from the recipient on supplies made by him nor shall he be entitled to`
  line `any credit of input tax.`
  line
  line `(5) If the proper officer has reasons to believe that a taxable person has paid tax under sub-section (1)`
  line `^10[or sub-section (2A), as the case may be] despite not being eligible, such person shall, in addition to any`
  line `tax that may be payable by him under any other provisions of this Act, be liable to a penalty and the`
  line `provisions of section 73 or section 74 ^11[or section 74A] shall, mutatis mutandis, apply for determination of tax and penalty.`
  line
  line `^12[Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of computing aggregate turnover of a person for determining his`
  line `eligibility to pay tax under this section, the expression "aggregate turnover" shall include the value of`
  line `supplies made by such person from the 1st day of April of a financial year up to the date when he`
  line `becomes liable for registration under this Act, but shall not include the value of exempt supply of services`
  line `provided by way of extending deposits, loans or advances in so far as the consideration is represented by`
  line `way of interest or discount.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of determining the tax payable by a person under this section, the`
  line `expression "turnover in State or turnover in Union territory" shall not include the value of following`
  line `supplies, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) supplies from the first day of April of a financial year up to the date when such person becomes`
  line `liable for registration under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(ii) exempt supply of services provided by way of extending deposits, loans or advances in so far as`
  line `the consideration is represented by way of interest or discount.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018 s. 5, for "in lieu of the tax payable by him, an amount calculated at such rate" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "one crore rupees" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 5, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 119 (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `7. The Words "goods or" omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 137 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `8. The word "and" omitted by Act 23 of 2019, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 93, ibid., for "Council:" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by s. 93, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 115 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5126)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to grant exemption from tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5126&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Government is satisfied that it is necessary in`
  line `the public interest so to do, it may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, exempt generally,`
  line `either absolutely or subject to such conditions as may be specified therein, goods or services or both of any`
  line `specified description from the whole or any part of the tax leviable thereon with effect from such date as may`
  line `be specified in such notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Government is satisfied that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, it may, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, by special order in each case, under circumstances of an exceptional`
  line `nature to be stated in such order, exempt from payment of tax any goods or services or both on which tax`
  line `is leviable.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government may, if it considers necessary or expedient so to do for the purpose of clarifying`
  line `the scope or applicability of any notification issued under sub-section (1) or order issued under subsection`
  line `(2), insert an explanation in such notification or order, as the case may be, by notification at any`
  line `time within one year of issue of the notification under sub-section (1) or order under sub-section (2), and`
  line `every such explanation shall have effect as if it had always been the part of the first such notification or`
  line `order, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, where an exemption in respect of any goods or`
  line `services or both from the whole or part of the tax leviable thereon has been granted absolutely, the`
  line `registered person supplying such goods or services or both shall not collect the tax, in excess of the`
  line `effective rate, on such supply of goods or services or both.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (96645)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Power not to recover Goods and Services Tax not levied or short-levied as a result of general practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 116 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=96645&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Power not to recover Goods and Services Tax not levied or short-levied as a result of`
  line `general practice.--- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the Government is satisfied that---`
  line
  line `(a) a practice was, or is, generally prevalent regarding levy of central tax (including non-levy thereof)`
  line `on any supply of goods or services or both; and`
  line
  line `(b) such supplies were, or are, liable to,---`
  line
  line `(i) central tax, in cases where according to the said practice, central tax was not, or is not being,`
  line `levied, or`
  line
  line `(ii) a higher amount of central tax than what was, or is being, levied, in accordance with the said`
  line practice,
  line
  line `the Government may, on the recommendation of the Council, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that the whole of the central tax payable on such supplies, or, as the case may be, the central tax in excess of that payable on such supplies, but for the said practice, shall not be required to be paid in`
  line `respect of the supplies on which the central tax was not, or is not being levied, or was, or is being, shortlevied, in accordance with the said practice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5127)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Time of supply of goods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. The words "sub-section (1) of" omitted by Act 31 of 2018, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5127&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability to pay tax on goods shall arise at the time of supply,`
  line `as determined in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The time of supply of goods shall be the earlier of the following dates, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of issue of invoice by the supplier or the last date on which he is required, under`
  line `^1*** section 31, to issue the invoice with respect to the supply; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which the supplier receives the payment with respect to the supply:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the supplier of taxable goods receives an amount up to one thousand rupees in`
  line `excess of the amount indicated in the tax invoice, the time of supply to the extent of such excess amount`
  line `shall, at the option of the said supplier, be the date of issue of invoice in respect of such excess amount.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b), "supply" shall be deemed to have been made`
  line `to the extent it is covered by the invoice or, as the case may be, the payment.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- or the purposes of clause (b), "the date on which the supplier receives the payment"`
  line `shall be the date on which the payment is entered in his books of account or the date on which the payment`
  line `is credited to his bank account, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of supplies in respect of which tax is paid or liable to be paid on reverse charge basis, the`
  line `time of supply shall be the earliest of the following dates, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the date of the receipt of goods; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date of payment as entered in the books of account of the recipient or the date on which the`
  line `payment is debited in his bank account, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(c) the date immediately following thirty days from the date of issue of invoice or any other`
  line `document, by whatever name called, in lieu thereof by the supplier:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not possible to determine the time of supply under clause (a) or clause (b) or`
  line `clause (c), the time of supply shall be the date of entry in the books of account of the recipient of supply.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of supply of vouchers by a supplier, the time of supply shall be---`
  line
  line `(a) the date of issue of voucher, if the supply is identifiable at that point; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date of redemption of voucher, in all other cases.`
  line
  line `(5) Where it is not possible to determine the time of supply under the provisions of sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), the time of supply shall---`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where a periodical return has to be filed, be the date on which such return is to be`
  line `filed; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be the date on which the tax is paid.`
  line
  line `(6) The time of supply to the extent it relates to an addition in the value of supply by way of interest,`
  line `late fee or penalty for delayed payment of any consideration shall be the date on which the supplier`
  line `receives such addition in value.`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5128)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Time of supply of services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5128&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The liability to pay tax on services shall arise at the time of`
  line `supply, as determined in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The time of supply of services shall be the earliest of the following dates, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the date of issue of invoice by the supplier, if the invoice is issued within the period`
  line `prescribed under ^1*** section 31 or the date of receipt of payment, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date of provision of service, if the invoice is not issued within the period prescribed under ^1*** section 31 or the date of receipt of payment, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(c) the date on which the recipient shows the receipt of services in his books of account, in a case where the provisions of clause (a) or clause (b) do not apply:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the supplier of taxable service receives an amount up to one thousand rupees in`
  line `excess of the amount indicated in the tax invoice, the time of supply to the extent of such excess amount`
  line `shall, at the option of the said supplier, be the date of issue of invoice relating to such excess amount.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of clauses (a) and (b)---`
  line
  line `(i) the supply shall be deemed to have been made to the extent it is covered by the invoice or, as`
  line `the case may be, the payment;`
  line
  line `(ii) "the date of receipt of payment" shall be the date on which the payment is entered in the`
  line `books of account of the supplier or the date on which the payment is credited to his bank account,`
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of supplies in respect of which tax is paid or liable to be paid on reverse charge basis, the`
  line `time of supply shall be the earlier of the following dates, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the date of payment as entered in the books of account of the recipient or the date on which the`
  line `payment is debited in his bank account, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date immediately following sixty days from the date of issue of invoice or any other`
  line `document, by whatever name called, in lieu thereof ^2[by the supplier, in cases where invoice is required to be issued by the supplier; or]`
  line
  line `^3[(c) the date of issue of invoice by the recipient, in cases where invoice is to be issued by the`
  line `recipient:]`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not possible to determine the time of supply under clause (a) or clause (b),^3[or clause (c)],`
  line `the time of supply shall be the date of entry in the books of account of the recipient of supply:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of supply by associated enterprises, where the supplier of service is`
  line `located outside India, the time of supply shall be the date of entry in the books of account of the recipient`
  line `of supply or the date of payment, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(4) In case of supply of vouchers by a supplier, the time of supply shall be---`
  line
  line `(a) the date of issue of voucher, if the supply is identifiable at that point; or`
  line
  line `(b) the date of redemption of voucher, in all other cases.`
  line
  line `(5) Where it is not possible to determine the time of supply under the provisions of sub-section (2) or`
  line `sub-section (3) or sub-section (4), the time of supply shall---`
  line
  line `(a) in a case where a periodical return has to be filed, be the date on which such return is to be`
  line `filed; or`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, be the date on which the tax is paid.`
  line
  line `(6) The time of supply to the extent it relates to an addition in the value of supply by way of interest,`
  line `late fee or penalty for delayed payment of any consideration shall be the date on which the supplier`
  line `receives such addition in value.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "sub-section (2) of" omitted by Act 31 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 117, for "by the supplier:" (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by, s. 117, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5129)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Change in rate of tax in respect of supply of goods or services.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5129&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 12 or section 13, the time of supply, where there is a change in the rate of tax in`
  line `respect of goods or services or both, shall be determined in the following manner, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) in case the goods or services or both have been supplied before the change in rate of tax,---`
  line
  line `(i) where the invoice for the same has been issued and the payment is also received after the`
  line `change in rate of tax, the time of supply shall be the date of receipt of payment or the date of issue of`
  line `invoice, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the invoice has been issued prior to the change in rate of tax but payment is`
  line `received after the change in rate of tax, the time of supply shall be the date of issue of invoice; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where the payment has been received before the change in rate of tax, but the invoice for`
  line `the same is issued after the change in rate of tax, the time of supply shall be the date of receipt of`
  line payment;
  line
  line `(b) in case the goods or services or both have been supplied after the change in rate of tax,---`
  line
  line `(i) where the payment is received after the change in rate of tax but the invoice has been`
  line `issued prior to the change in rate of tax, the time of supply shall be the date of receipt of payment;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) where the invoice has been issued and payment is received before the change in rate of`
  line `tax, the time of supply shall be the date of receipt of payment or date of issue of invoice,`
  line `whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where the invoice has been issued after the change in rate of tax but the payment is`
  line `received before the change in rate of tax, the time of supply shall be the date of issue of invoice:`
  line
  line `Provided that the date of receipt of payment shall be the date of credit in the bank account if`
  line `such credit in the bank account is after four working days from the date of change in the rate of`
  line tax.
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, "the date of receipt of payment" shall be the date on`
  line `which the payment is entered in the books of account of the supplier or the date on which the payment is`
  line `credited to his bank account, whichever is earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5130)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Value of taxable supply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5130&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The value of a supply of goods or services or both shall be the`
  line `transaction value, which is the price actually paid or payable for the said supply of goods or services or`
  line `both where the supplier and the recipient of the supply are not related and the price is the sole`
  line `consideration for the supply.`
  line
  line `(2) The value of supply shall include---`
  line
  line `(a) any taxes, duties, cesses, fees and charges levied under any law for the time being in force`
  line `other than this Act, the State Goods and Services Tax Act, the Union Territory Goods and Services`
  line `Tax Act and the Goods and Services Tax (Compensation to States) Act, if charged separately by the`
  line supplier;
  line
  line `(b) any amount that the supplier is liable to pay in relation to such supply but which has been`
  line `incurred by the recipient of the supply and not included in the price actually paid or payable for the`
  line `goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(c) incidental expenses, including commission and packing, charged by the supplier to the`
  line `recipient of a supply and any amount charged for anything done by the supplier in respect of the`
  line `supply of goods or services or both at the time of, or before delivery of goods or supply of services;`
  line
  line `(d) interest or late fee or penalty for delayed payment of any consideration for any supply; and`
  line
  line `(e) subsidies directly linked to the price excluding subsidies provided by the Central Government`
  line `and the State Governments.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this sub-section, the amount of subsidy shall be included in the`
  line `value of supply of the supplier who receives the subsidy.`
  line
  line `(3) The value of the supply shall not include any discount which is given---`
  line
  line `(a) before or at the time of the supply if such discount has been duly recorded in the invoice`
  line `issued in respect of such supply; and`
  line
  line `(b) after the supply has been effected, if---`
  line
  line `(i) such discount is established in terms of an agreement entered into at or before the time of`
  line `such supply and specifically linked to relevant invoices; and`
  line
  line `(ii) input tax credit as is attributable to the discount on the basis of document issued by the`
  line `supplier has been reversed by the recipient of the supply.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the value of the supply of goods or services or both cannot be determined under`
  line `sub-section (1), the same shall be determined in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (4), the value of such`
  line `supplies as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council shall be`
  line `determined in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation---For the purposes of this Act,---`
  line
  line `(a) persons shall be deemed to be "related persons" if---`
  line
  line `(i) such persons are officers or directors of one another's businesses;`
  line
  line `(ii) such persons are legally recognised partners in business;`
  line
  line `(iii) such persons are employer and employee;`
  line
  line `(iv) any person directly or indirectly owns, controls or holds twenty-five per cent. or more of`
  line `the outstanding voting stock or shares of both of them;`
  line
  line `(v) one of them directly or indirectly controls the other;`
  line
  line `(vi) both of them are directly or indirectly controlled by a third person;`
  line
  line `(vii) together they directly or indirectly control a third person; or`
  line
  line `(viii) they are members of the same family;`
  line
  line `(b) the term "person" also includes legal persons;`
  line
  line `(c) persons who are associated in the business of one another in that one is the sole agent or sole`
  line `distributor or sole concessionaire, howsoever described, of the other, shall be deemed to be related.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5131)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Eligibility and conditions for taking input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5131&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered person shall,`
  line `subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed and in the manner specified in section 49, be entitled to take credit of input tax charged on any supply of goods or services or both to him which are used or intended to be used in the course or furtherance of his business and the said amount shall be credited to the electronic credit ledger of such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no registered person shall be entitled to the`
  line `credit of any input tax in respect of any supply of goods or services or both to him unless,---`
  line
  line `(a) he is in possession of a tax invoice or debit note issued by a supplier registered under this Act, or such other tax paying documents as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) the details of the invoice or debit note referred to in clause (a) has been furnished by the supplier in the statement of outward supplies and such details have been communicated to the recipient of such invoice or debit note in the manner specified under section 37.]`
  line
  line `(b) he has received the goods or services or both.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation--For the purposes of this clause, it shall be deemed that the registered person has received the goods or, as the case may be, services --`
  line
  line `(i) where the goods are delivered by the supplier to a recipient or any other person on the direction of such registered person, whether acting as an agent or otherwise, before or during movement of goods, either by way of transfer of documents of title to goods or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the services are provided by the supplier to any person on the direction of and on account of such registered person.];`
  line
  line `^3[(ba) the details of input tax credit in respect of the said supply communicated to such registered person under Section 38 has not been restricted;]`
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provisions of ^4[section 41 ^5***], the tax charged in respect of such supply has been actually paid to the Government, either in cash or through utilisation of input tax credit admissible in respect of the said supply; and`
  line
  line `(d) he has furnished the return under section 39:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the goods against an invoice are received in lots or instalments, the registered person shall be entitled to take credit upon receipt of the last lot or instalment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where a recipient fails to pay to the supplier of goods or services or both, other than the supplies on which tax is payable on reverse charge basis, the amount towards the value of supply along with tax payable thereon within a period of one hundred and eighty days from the date of issue of invoice by the supplier, an amount equal to the input tax credit availed by the recipient shall be ^6[paid by him along with interest payable under section 50], in such manner as may be prescribed::`
  line
  line `Provided also that the recipient shall be entitled to avail of the credit of input tax on payment made by him ^7[to the supplier] of the amount towards the value of supply of goods or services or both along with tax payable thereon..`
  line
  line `(3) Where the registered person has claimed depreciation on the tax component of the cost of capital goods and plant and machinery under the provisions of the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961), the input tax credit on the said tax component shall not be allowed.`
  line
  line `(4) A registered person shall not be entitled to take input tax credit in respect of any invoice or debit note for supply of goods or services or both after the ^8[thirtieth day of November] following the end of financial year to which such invoice or ^9*** debit note pertains or furnishing of the relevant annual return, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `^10[Provided that the registered person shall be entitled to take input tax credit after the due date of furnishing of the return under section 39 for the month of September, 2018 till the due date of furnishing of the return under the said section for the month of March, 2019 in respect of any invoice or invoice relating to such debit note for supply of goods or services or both made during the financial year 2017-18, the details of which have been uploaded by the supplier under sub-section (1) of section 37 till the due date for furnishing the details under sub-section (1) of said section for the month of March, 2019.]`
  line
  line `^11[(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4), in respect of an invoice or debit note for supply of goods or services or both pertaining to the Financial Years 2017-18, 2018-19, 2019-20 and 2020-21, the registered person shall be entitled to take input tax credit in any return under section 39 which is filed up to the thirtieth day of November, 2021.`
  line
  line `(6) Where registration of a registered person is cancelled under section 29 and subsequently the cancellation of registration is revoked by any order, either under section 30 or pursuant to any order made by the Appellate Authority or the Appellate Tribunal or court and where availment of input tax credit in respect of an invoice or debit note was not restricted under sub-section (4) on the date of order of cancellation of registration, the said person shall be entitled to take the input tax credit in respect of such invoice or debit note for supply of goods or services or both, in a return under section 39,---`
  line
  line `(i) filed up to thirtieth day of November following the financial year to which such invoice or debit note pertains or furnishing of the relevant annual return, whichever is earlier; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for the period from the date of cancellation of registration or the effective date of cancellation of registration, as the case may be, till the date of order of revocation of cancellation of registration, where such return is filed within thirty days from the date of order of revocation of cancellation of registration,`
  line
  line `whichever is later.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 109 (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `2. subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 8 for The Explanation (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 8, for "section 41" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `5. The words, "or section 43A" omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 138, for "added to his output tax liability, along with interest thereon" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by s. 138, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 100, for "due date of furnishing of the return under section 39 for the month of September" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `9. The words "invoice relation to such" omitted by Act 12 of 2020, s. 120 (w.e.f. 1-01-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Order No. 02/2018-Central Tax dated 31-12-2018.`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 118 (w.e.f. 1-07-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5132)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Apportionment of credit and blocked credits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5132&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the goods or services or both are used`
  line `by the registered person partly for the purpose of any business and partly for other purposes, the amount of`
  line `credit shall be restricted to so much of the input tax as is attributable to the purposes of his business.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the goods or services or both are used by the registered person partly for effecting taxable`
  line `supplies including zero-rated supplies under this Act or under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act and`
  line `partly for effecting exempt supplies under the said Acts, the amount of credit shall be restricted to so much of`
  line `the input tax as is attributable to the said taxable supplies including zero-rated supplies.`
  line
  line `(3) The value of exempt supply under sub-section (2) shall be such as may be prescribed, and shall`
  line `include supplies on which the recipient is liable to pay tax on reverse charge basis, transactions in`
  line `securities, sale of land and, subject to clause (b) of paragraph 5 of Schedule II, sale of building.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "value of exempt supply" shall not include the value of activities or transactions specified in Schedule III, except , ^2[except,---`
  line
  line `(i) the value of activities or transactions specified in paragraph 5 of the said Schedule; and.`
  line
  line `(ii) the value of such activities or transactions as may be prescribed in respect of clause (a) of`
  line `paragraph 8 of the said Schedule.]`
  line
  line `(4) A banking company or a financial institution including a non-banking financial company, engaged in supplying services by way of accepting deposits, extending loans or advances shall have the option to either comply with the provisions of sub-section (2), or avail of, every month, an amount equal to fifty per cent. of the eligible input tax credit on inputs, capital goods and input services in that month and the rest shall lapse:`
  line
  line `Provided that the option once exercised shall not be withdrawn during the remaining part of the financial year:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the restriction of fifty per cent. shall not apply to the tax paid on supplies made by one registered person to another registered person having the same Permanent Account Number.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) of section 16 and sub-section (1) of section 18, input tax credit shall not be available in respect of the following, namely:---`
  line
  line `^3[(a) motor vehicles for transportation of persons having approved seating capacity of not more than thirteen persons (including the driver), except when they are used for making the following taxable supplies, namely:---`
  line
  line `(A) further supply of such motor vehicles; or`
  line
  line `(B) transportation of passengers; or`
  line
  line `(C) imparting training on driving such motor vehicles;`
  line
  line `(aa) vessels and aircraft except when they are used---`
  line
  line `(i) for making the following taxable supplies, namely:---`
  line
  line `(A) further supply of such vessels or aircraft; or`
  line
  line `(B) transportation of passengers; or`
  line
  line `(C) imparting training on navigating such vessels; or`
  line
  line `(D) imparting training on flying such aircraft;`
  line
  line `(ii) for transportation of goods;`
  line
  line `(ab) services of general insurance, servicing, repair and maintenance in so far as they relate to`
  line `motor vehicles, vessels or aircraft referred to in clause (a) or clause (aa):`
  line
  line `Provided that the input tax credit in respect of such services shall be available---`
  line
  line `(i) where the motor vehicles, vessels or aircraft referred to in clause (a) or clause (aa) are`
  line `used for the purposes specified therein;`
  line
  line `(ii) where received by a taxable person engaged---`
  line
  line `(I) in the manufacture of such motor vehicles, vessels or aircraft; or`
  line
  line `(II) in the supply of general insurance services in respect of such motor vehicles, vessels`
  line `or aircraft insured by him;`
  line
  line `(b) the following supply of goods or services or both---`
  line
  line `(i) food and beverages, outdoor catering, beauty treatment, health services, cosmetic and`
  line `plastic surgery, leasing, renting or hiring of motor vehicles, vessels or aircraft referred to in clause (a) or clause (aa) except when used for the purposes specified therein, life insurance and health insurance:`
  line
  line `Provided that the input tax credit in respect of such goods or services or both shall be`
  line `available where an inward supply of such goods or services or both is used by a registered person for making an outward taxable supply of the same category of goods or services or both or as an element of a taxable composite or mixed supply;`
  line
  line `(ii) membership of a club, health and fitness centre; and`
  line
  line `(iii) travel benefits extended to employees on vacation such as leave or home travel`
  line `concession:`
  line
  line `Provided that the input tax credit in respect of such goods or services or both shall be`
  line `available, where it is obligatory for an employer to provide the same to its employees under any law for the time being in force.]`
  line
  line `(c) works contract services when supplied for construction of an immovable property (other than plant and machinery) except where it is an input service for further supply of works contract service;`
  line
  line `(d) goods or services or both received by a taxable person for construction of an immovable property (other than ^4[plant and machinery]) on his own account including when such goods or services or both are used in the course or furtherance of business.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of clauses (c) and (d), the expression "construction" includes re-construction, renovation, additions or alterations or repairs, to the extent of capitalisation, to the said immovable property;`
  line
  line `(e) goods or services or both on which tax has been paid under section 10;`
  line
  line `(f) goods or services or both received by a non-resident taxable person except on goods imported by him;`
  line
  line `^5[(fa) goods or services or both received by a taxable person, which are used or intended to be`
  line `used for activities relating to his obligations under corporate social responsibility referred to in`
  line `section 135 of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013);]`
  line
  line `(g) goods or services or both used for personal consumption;`
  line
  line `(h) goods lost, stolen, destroyed, written off or disposed of by way of gift or free samples; and`
  line
  line `(i) any tax paid in accordance with the provisions of ^6[section 74 in respect of any period upto`
  line `Financial Year 2023-24].`
  line
  line `(6) The Government may prescribe the manner in which the credit referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) may be attributed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this Chapter and Chapter VI, the expression "plant and machinery" means apparatus, equipment, and machinery fixed to earth by foundation or structural support that are used for making outward supply of goods or services or both and includes such foundation and structural supports but excludes---`
  line
  line `(i) land, building or any other civil structures;`
  line
  line `(ii) telecommunication towers; and`
  line
  line `(iii) pipelines laid outside the factory premises.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 9, (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 139, for "except those specified in paragraph 5 of the said Schedule"(w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018 s. 9, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 7 of 2025, s. 124, for "plant or machinery" (w.e.f. 01-07-2017).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 139 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 119, for "sections 74, 129 and 130" (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5133)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Availability of credit in special circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5133&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions and restrictions`
  line `as may be prescribed---`
  line
  line `(a) a person who has applied for registration under this Act within thirty days from the date on`
  line `which he becomes liable to registration and has been granted such registration shall be entitled to take`
  line `credit of input tax in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished`
  line `goods held in stock on the day immediately preceding the date from which he becomes liable to pay`
  line `tax under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) a person who takes registration under sub-section (3) of section 25 shall be entitled to take`
  line `credit of input tax in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished`
  line `goods held in stock on the day immediately preceding the date of grant of registration;`
  line
  line `(c) where any registered person ceases to pay tax under section 10, he shall be entitled to take credit of`
  line `input tax in respect of inputs held in stock, inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock`
  line `and on capital goods on the day immediately preceding the date from which he becomes liable to pay tax`
  line `under section 9:`
  line
  line `Provided that the credit on capital goods shall be reduced by such percentage points as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(d) where an exempt supply of goods or services or both by a registered person becomes a taxable`
  line `supply, such person shall be entitled to take credit of input tax in respect of inputs held in stock and`
  line `inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock relatable to such exempt supply and on`
  line `capital goods exclusively used for such exempt supply on the day immediately preceding the date from`
  line `which such supply becomes taxable:`
  line
  line `Provided that the credit on capital goods shall be reduced by such percentage points as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(2) A registered person shall not be entitled to take input tax credit under sub-section (1) in respect of`
  line `any supply of goods or services or both to him after the expiry of one year from the date of issue of tax`
  line `invoice relating to such supply.`
  line
  line `(3) Where there is a change in the constitution of a registered person on account of sale, merger, demerger,`
  line `amalgamation, lease or transfer of the business with the specific provisions for transfer of liabilities, the said`
  line `registered person shall be allowed to transfer the input tax credit which remains unutilised in his electronic`
  line `credit ledger to such sold, merged, demerged, amalgamated, leased or transferred business in such manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any registered person who has availed of input tax credit opts to pay tax under section 10 or,`
  line `where the goods or services or both supplied by him become wholly exempt, he shall pay an amount, by`
  line `way of debit in the electronic credit ledger or electronic cash ledger, equivalent to the credit of input tax in`
  line `respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock and on`
  line `capital goods, reduced by such percentage points as may be prescribed, on the day immediately preceding`
  line `the date of exercising of such option or, as the case may be, the date of such exemption:`
  line
  line `Provided that after payment of such amount, the balance of input tax credit, if any, lying in his`
  line `electronic credit ledger shall lapse.`
  line
  line `(5) The amount of credit under sub-section (1) and the amount payable under sub-section (4) shall be`
  line `calculated in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) In case of supply of capital goods or plant and machinery, on which input tax credit has been taken,`
  line `the registered person shall pay an amount equal to the input tax credit taken on the said capital goods or plant`
  line `and machinery reduced by such percentage points as may be prescribed or the tax on the transaction value of`
  line `such capital goods or plant and machinery determined under section 15, whichever is higher:`
  line
  line `Provided that where refractory bricks, moulds and dies, jigs and fixtures are supplied as scrap, the`
  line `taxable person may pay tax on the transaction value of such goods determined under section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5134)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Taking input tax credit in respect of inputs and capital goods sent for job work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5134&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `principal shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, be allowed input tax`
  line `credit on inputs sent to a job worker for job work.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 16, the principal shall be`
  line `entitled to take credit of input tax on inputs even if the inputs are directly sent to a job worker for job work`
  line `without being first brought to his place of business.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the inputs sent for job work are not received back by the principal after completion of job`
  line `work or otherwise or are not supplied from the place of business of the job worker in accordance with`
  line `clause (a) or clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 143 within one year of being sent out, it shall be`
  line `deemed that such inputs had been supplied by the principal to the job worker on the day when the said`
  line `inputs were sent out:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the inputs are sent directly to a job worker, the period of one year shall be`
  line `counted from the date of receipt of inputs by the job worker.`
  line
  line `(4) The principal shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, be allowed input`
  line `tax credit on capital goods sent to a job worker for job work.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (b) of sub-section (2) of section 16, the principal`
  line `shall be entitled to take credit of input tax on capital goods even if the capital goods are directly sent to a`
  line `job worker for job work without being first brought to his place of business.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the capital goods sent for job work are not received back by the principal within a period of`
  line `three years of being sent out, it shall be deemed that such capital goods had been supplied by the principal`
  line `to the job worker on the day when the said capital goods were sent out:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the capital goods are sent directly to a job worker, the period of three years shall`
  line `be counted from the date of receipt of capital goods by the job worker.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing contained in sub-section (3) or sub-section (6) shall apply to moulds and dies, jigs and`
  line `fixtures, or tools sent out to a job worker for job work.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this section, "principal" means the person referred to in`
  line `section 143.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5135)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Manner of distribution of credit by Input Service Distributor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5135&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[20. Manner of distribution of credit by Input Service Distributor.--- (1) Any office of the`
  line `supplier of goods or services or both which receives tax invoices towards the receipt of input services,`
  line `including invoices in respect of services liable to tax under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 9`
  line `^2[of this Act or under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 5 of the Integrated Goods and Services`
  line `Tax Act, 2017 (13 of 2017)], for or on behalf of distinct persons referred to in section 25, shall be`
  line `required to be registered as Input Service Distributor under clause (viii) of section 24 and shall distribute`
  line `the input tax credit in respect of such invoices.`
  line
  line `(2) The Input Service Distributor shall distribute the credit of central tax or integrated tax charged on`
  line `invoices received by him, including the credit of central or integrated tax in respect of services subject to`
  line `levy of tax under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of section 9 ^2[of this Act or under sub-section (3) or`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 5 of the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (13 of 2017),] paid by a`
  line `distinct person registered in the same State as the said Input Service Distributor, in such manner, within`
  line `such time and subject to such restrictions and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The credit of central tax shall be distributed as central tax or integrated tax and integrated tax as`
  line `integrated tax or central tax, by way of issue of a document containing the amount of input tax credit, in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2024, s. 12, for section 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-2025).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 7 of 2025, s. 125 (w.e.f. 1-4-2025).`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5136)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Manner of recovery of credit distributed in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 120 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5136&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where the Input Service Distributor`
  line `distributes the credit in contravention of the provisions contained in section 20 resulting in excess distribution of credit to one or more recipients of credit, the excess credit so distributed shall be`
  line `recovered from such recipients along with interest, and the provisions of section 73 or`
  line `section 74 ^1[or section 74A], as the case may be, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply for determination of`
  line `amount to be recovered.`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5137)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Persons liable for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5137&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every supplier shall be liable to be registered under this Act`
  line `in the State or Union territory, other than special category States, from where he makes a taxable supply`
  line `of goods or services or both, if his aggregate turnover in a financial year exceeds twenty lakh rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person makes taxable supplies of goods or services or both from any of the`
  line `special category States, he shall be liable to be registered if his aggregate turnover in a financial year`
  line `exceeds ten lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that the Government may, at the request of a special category State and on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, enhance the aggregate turnover referred to in the first proviso from ten`
  line `lakh rupees to such amount, not exceeding twenty lakh rupees and subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, as may be so notified.]`
  line
  line `^2[Provided also that the Government may, at the request of a State and on the recommendations of the`
  line `Council, enhance the aggregate turnover from twenty lakh rupees to such amount not exceeding forty lakh`
  line `rupees in case of supplier who is engaged exclusively in the supply of goods, subject to such conditions`
  line `and limitations, as may be notified.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be considered to be engaged`
  line `exclusively in the supply of goods even if he is engaged in exempt supply of services provided by way of`
  line `extending deposits, loans or advances in so far as the consideration is represented by way of interest or`
  line discount.]
  line
  line `(2) Every person who, on the day immediately preceding the appointed day, is registered or holds a`
  line `licence under an existing law, shall be liable to be registered under this Act with effect from the appointed`
  line day.
  line
  line `(3) Where a business carried on by a taxable person registered under this Act is transferred, whether`
  line `on account of succession or otherwise, to another person as a going concern, the transferee or the`
  line `successor, as the case may be, shall be liable to be registered with effect from the date of such transfer or`
  line succession.
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (3), in a case of transfer pursuant to`
  line `sanction of a scheme or an arrangement for amalgamation or, as the case may be, demerger of two or more`
  line `companies pursuant to an order of a High Court, Tribunal or otherwise, the transferee shall be liable to be`
  line `registered, with effect from the date on which the Registrar of Companies issues a certificate of`
  line `incorporation giving effect to such order of the High Court or Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "aggregate turnover" shall include all supplies made by the taxable person,`
  line `whether on his own account or made on behalf of all his principals;`
  line
  line `(ii) the supply of goods, after completion of job work, by a registered job worker shall be treated`
  line `as the supply of goods by the principal referred to in section 143, and the value of such goods shall`
  line `not be included in the aggregate turnover of the registered job worker;`
  line
  line `(iii) the expression "special category States" shall mean the States as specified in sub-clause (g)`
  line `of clause (4) of article 279A of the Constitution ^3[except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*] ^4[and`
  line `States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Himachal Pradesh, Meghalaya, Sikkim and Uttarakhand].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018 s. 11, (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 2017, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-7-2017).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5138)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Persons not liable for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `3. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 140, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5138&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons shall not be liable to registration,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) any person engaged exclusively in the business of supplying goods or services or both that are`
  line `not liable to tax or wholly exempt from tax under this Act or under the Integrated Goods and Services`
  line `Tax Act;`
  line
  line `(b) an agriculturist, to the extent of supply of produce out of cultivation of land.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in sub-section (1) of section 22 or`
  line `section 24, the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject to such`
  line `conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, specify the category of persons who may be`
  line `exempted from obtaining registration under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5139)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Compulsory registration in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5139&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 22, the following categories of persons shall be required to be registered under`
  line `this Act,---`
  line
  line `(i) persons making any inter-State taxable supply;`
  line
  line `(ii) casual taxable persons making taxable supply;`
  line
  line `(iii) persons who are required to pay tax under reverse charge;`
  line
  line `(iv) person who are required to pay tax under sub-section (5) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(v) non-resident taxable persons making taxable supply;`
  line
  line `(vi) persons who are required to deduct tax under section 51, whether or not separately registered`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(vii) persons who make taxable supply of goods or services or both on behalf of other taxable`
  line `persons whether as an agent or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(viii) Input Service Distributor, whether or not separately registered under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ix) persons who supply goods or services or both, other than supplies specified under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 9, through such electronic commerce operator who is required to collect tax`
  line `at source under section 52;`
  line
  line `(x) every electronic commerce operator; ^1[who is required to collect tax at source under section`
  line 52];
  line
  line `(xi) every person supplying online information and database access or retrieval services from a`
  line `place outside India to a person in India, other than a registered person; ^2***`
  line
  line `^3[(xia) every person supplying online money gaming from a place outside India to a person in`
  line `India; and]`
  line
  line `(xii) such other person or class of persons as may be notified by the Government on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s.12 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by Act 30 of 2023, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5140)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Procedure for registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5140&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who is liable to be registered under section 22 or`
  line `section 24 shall apply for registration in every such State or Union territory in which he is so liable within`
  line `thirty days from the date on which he becomes liable to registration, in such manner and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a casual taxable person or a non-resident taxable person shall apply for registration at`
  line `least five days prior to the commencement of business.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that a person having a unit, as defined in the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005,`
  line `(28 of 2005) in a Special Economic Zone or being a Special Economic Zone developer shall have to apply`
  line `for a separate registration, as distinct from his place of business located outside the Special Economic`
  line `Zone in the same State or Union territory.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Every person who makes a supply from the territorial waters of India shall obtain`
  line `registration in the coastal State or Union territory where the nearest point of the appropriate baseline is`
  line located.
  line
  line `(2) A person seeking registration under this Act shall be granted a single registration in a State or`
  line `Union territory:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that a person having multiple places of business in a State or Union territory may be`
  line `granted a separate registration for each such place of business, subject to such conditions as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line
  line `(3) A person, though not liable to be registered under section 22 or section 24 may get himself`
  line `registered voluntarily, and all provisions of this Act, as are applicable to a registered person, shall apply to`
  line `such person.`
  line
  line `(4) A person who has obtained or is required to obtain more than one registration, whether in one`
  line `State or Union territory or more than one State or Union territory shall, in respect of each such`
  line `registration, be treated as distinct persons for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Where a person who has obtained or is required to obtain registration in a State or Union territory`
  line `in respect of an establishment, has an establishment in another State or Union territory, then such`
  line `establishments shall be treated as establishments of distinct persons for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) Every person shall have a Permanent Account Number issued under the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961) in order to be eligible for grant of registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person required to deduct tax under section 51 may have, in lieu of a Permanent`
  line `Account Number, a Tax Deduction and Collection Account Number issued under the said Act in order to`
  line `be eligible for grant of registration.`
  line
  line `^3[(6A) Every registered person shall undergo authentication, or furnish proof of possession of Aadhaar`
  line `number, in such form and manner and within such time as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an Aadhaar number is not assigned to the registered person, such person shall be`
  line `offered alternate and viable means of identification in such manner as Government may, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, prescribe:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case of failure to undergo authentication or furnish proof of possession of`
  line `Aadhaar number or furnish alternate and viable means of identification, registration allotted to such`
  line `person shall be deemed to be invalid and the other provisions of this Act shall apply as if such person`
  line `does not have a registration.`
  line
  line `(6B) On and from the date of notification, every individual shall, in order to be eligible for grant of`
  line `registration, undergo authentication, or furnish proof of possession of Aadhaar number, in such manner as`
  line `the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, specify in the said notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that if an Aadhaar number is not assigned to an individual, such individual shall be offered`
  line `alternate and viable means of identification in such manner as the Government may, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, specify in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(6C) On and from the date of notification, every person, other than an individual, shall, in order to be`
  line `eligible for grant of registration, undergo authentication, or furnish proof of possession of Aadhaar`
  line `number of the Karta, Managing Director, whole time Director, such number of partners, Members of`
  line `Managing Committee of Association, Board of Trustees, authorised representative, authorised signatory`
  line `and such other class of persons, in such manner, as the Government may, on the recommendations of the`
  line `Council, specify in the said notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person or class of persons have not been assigned the Aadhaar Number, such`
  line `person or class of persons shall be offered alternate and viable means of identification in such manner as`
  line `the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, specify in the said notification.`
  line
  line `(6D) The provisions of sub-section (6A) or sub-section (6B) or sub-section (6C) shall not apply to`
  line `such person or class of persons or any State or Union territory or part thereof, as the Government may, on`
  line `the recommendations of the Council, specify by notification.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, the expression "Aadhaar number" shall have the same`
  line `meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of section 2 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and`
  line `Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016).]`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6), a non-resident taxable person may be`
  line `granted registration under sub-section (1) on the basis of such other documents as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a person who is liable to be registered under this Act fails to obtain registration, the proper`
  line `officer may, without prejudice to any action which may be taken under this Act or under any other law for`
  line `the time being in force, proceed to register such person in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) any specialised agency of the United Nations Organisation or any Multilateral Financial`
  line `Institution and Organisation notified under the United Nations (Privileges and Immunities) Act, 1947`
  line `(46 of 1947), Consulate or Embassy of foreign countries; and`
  line
  line `(b) any other person or class of persons, as may be notified by the Commissioner,`
  line
  line `shall be granted a Unique Identity Number in such manner and for such purposes, including refund of`
  line `taxes on the notified supplies of goods or services or both received by them, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(10) The registration or the Unique Identity Number shall be granted or rejected after due verification`
  line `in such manner and within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(11) A certificate of registration shall be issued in such form and with effect from such date as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(12) A registration or a Unique Identity Number shall be deemed to have been granted after the expiry`
  line `of the period prescribed under sub-section (10), if no deficiency has been communicated to the applicant`
  line `within that period.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The proviso ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s.13, (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5141)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Deemed registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5141&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The grant of registration or the Unique Identity Number under the State`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act shall be deemed to be a`
  line `grant of registration or the Unique Identity Number under this Act subject to the condition that the application`
  line `for registration or the Unique Identity Number has not been rejected under this Act within the time specified`
  line `in sub-section (10) of section 25.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (10) of section 25, any rejection of application`
  line `for registration or the Unique Identity Number under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act shall be deemed to be a rejection of application for registration`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5142)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Special provisions relating to casual taxable person and non-resident taxable person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5142&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The certificate of registration issued to a casual taxable person or a non-resident taxable person shall be`
  line `valid for the period specified in the application for registration or ninety days from the effective date of`
  line `registration, whichever is earlier and such person shall make taxable supplies only after the issuance of`
  line `the certificate of registration:`
  line
  line `Provided that the proper officer may, on sufficient cause being shown by the said taxable person,`
  line `extend the said period of ninety days by a further period not exceeding ninety days.`
  line
  line `(2) A casual taxable person or a non-resident taxable person shall, at the time of submission of`
  line `application for registration under sub-section (1) of section 25, make an advance deposit of tax in an`
  line `amount equivalent to the estimated tax liability of such person for the period for which the registration is`
  line `sought:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any extension of time is sought under sub-section (1), such taxable person shall`
  line `deposit an additional amount of tax equivalent to the estimated tax liability of such person for the period`
  line `for which the extension is sought.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount deposited under sub-section (2) shall be credited to the electronic cash ledger of`
  line `such person and shall be utilised in the manner provided under section 49.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5143)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Amendment of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5143&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `1) Every registered person and a person to whom a Unique`
  line `Identity Number has been assigned shall inform the proper officer of any changes in the information`
  line `furnished at the time of registration or subsequent thereto, in such form and manner and within such`
  line `period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer may, on the basis of information furnished under sub-section (1) or as`
  line `ascertained by him, approve or reject amendments in the registration particulars in such manner and`
  line `within such period as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that approval of the proper officer shall not be required in respect of amendment of such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the proper officer shall not reject the application for amendment in the registration`
  line `particulars without giving the person an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(3) Any rejection or approval of amendments under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the`
  line `Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be a rejection or`
  line `approval under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5144)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Cancellation or suspension of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5144&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `29. Cancellation ^1[or suspension] of registration--- (1) The proper officer may, either on his own motion or on an`
  line `application filed by the registered person or by his legal heirs, in case of death of such person, cancel the`
  line `registration, in such manner and within such period as may be prescribed, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances where,--`
  line
  line `(a) the business has been discontinued, transferred fully for any reason including death of the`
  line `proprietor, amalgamated with other legal entity, demerged or otherwise disposed of; or`
  line
  line `(b) there is any change in the constitution of the business; or`
  line
  line `^1[(c) the taxable person is no longer liable to be registered under section 22 or section 24 or`
  line `intends to optout of the registration voluntarily made under sub-section (3) of section 25:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that during pendency of the proceedings relating to cancellation of registration filed by the registered person, the registration may be suspended for such period and in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer may cancel the registration of a person from such date, including any`
  line `retrospective date, as he may deem fit, where,---`
  line
  line `(a) a registered person has contravened such provisions of the Act or the rules made thereunder as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(b) a person paying tax under section 10 has not furnished ^4[the return for a financial year beyond three months from the due date of furnishing the said return]; or`
  line
  line `(c) any registered person, other than a person specified in clause (b), has not furnished returns for ^5[such continuous tax period as may be prescribed]; or`
  line
  line `(d) any person who has taken voluntary registration under sub-section (3) of section 25 has not commenced business within six months from the date of registration; or`
  line
  line `(e) registration has been obtained by means of fraud, wilful misstatement or suppression of facts:`
  line
  line `Provided that the proper officer shall not cancel the registration without giving the person an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that during pendency of the proceedings relating to cancellation of registration, the proper officer may suspend the registration for such period and in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) The cancellation of registration under this section shall not affect the liability of the person to pay tax`
  line `and other dues under this Act or to discharge any obligation under this Act or the rules made thereunder for`
  line `any period prior to the date of cancellation whether or not such tax and other dues are determined before or`
  line `after the date of cancellation.`
  line
  line `(4) The cancellation of registration under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be a cancellation of`
  line `registration under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Every registered person whose registration is cancelled shall pay an amount, by way of debit in the`
  line `electronic credit ledger or electronic cash ledger, equivalent to the credit of input tax in respect of inputs`
  line `held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock or capital goods or plant and machinery on the day immediately preceding the date of such cancellation or the output tax payable on`
  line `such goods, whichever is higher, calculated in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case of capital goods or plant and machinery, the taxable person shall pay an amount`
  line `equal to the input tax credit taken on the said capital goods or plant and machinery, reduced by such`
  line `percentage points as may be prescribed or the tax on the transaction value of such capital goods or plant`
  line `and machinery under section 15, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(6) The amount payable under sub-section (5) shall be calculated in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 121, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 101, for "returns for three consecutive tax periods" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 101, ibid., for "a continuous period of six months" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5145)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Revocation of cancellation of registration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5145&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed,`
  line `any registered person, whose registration is cancelled by the proper officer on his own motion, may apply to`
  line `such officer for revocation of cancellation of the registration in ^1[such manner, within such time and subject`
  line `to such conditions and restrictions, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer may, in such manner and within such period as may be prescribed, by order, either`
  line `revoke cancellation of the registration or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the application for revocation of cancellation of registration shall not be rejected unless`
  line `the applicant has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that such revocation of cancellation of registration shall be subject to such`
  line `conditions and restrictions, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) The revocation of cancellation of registration under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the`
  line `Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, as the case may be, shall be deemed to be a revocation of`
  line `cancellation of registration under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 141, for "the prescribed manner within thirty days from the date of service of the cancellation`
  line `order:"(w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 141, (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 121 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5146)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Tax invoice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5146&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered person supplying taxable goods shall, before or at the time of,---`
  line
  line `(a) removal of goods for supply to the recipient, where the supply involves movement of goods;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) delivery of goods or making available thereof to the recipient, in any other case,`
  line
  line `issue a tax invoice showing the description, quantity and value of goods, the tax charged thereon and such`
  line `other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify`
  line `the categories of goods or supplies in respect of which a tax invoice shall be issued, within such time and`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person supplying taxable services shall, before or after the provision of service but`
  line `within a prescribed period, issue a tax invoice, showing the description, value, tax charged thereon and such`
  line `other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification,---`
  line
  line `(a) specify the categories of services or supplies in respect of which a tax invoice shall be issued,`
  line `within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) subject to the condition mentioned therein, specify the categories of services in respect of`
  line which---
  line
  line `(i) any other document issue in relation to the supply shall be deemed to be a tax invoice; or`
  line
  line `(ii) tax invoice may not be issued.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and(2).---`
  line
  line `(a) a registered person may, within one month from the date of issuance of certificate of registration`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed, issue a revised invoice against the invoice already issued during`
  line `the period beginning with the effective date of registration till the date of issuance of certificate of`
  line `registration to him;`
  line
  line `(b) a registered person may not issue a tax invoice if the value of the goods or services or both`
  line `supplied is less than two hundred rupees subject to such conditions and in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(c) a registered person supplying exempted goods or services or both or paying tax under the`
  line `provisions of section 10 shall issue, instead of a tax invoice, a bill of supply containing such particulars`
  line `and in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered person may not issue a bill of supply if the value of the goods or`
  line `services or both supplied is less than two hundred rupees subject to such conditions and in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(d) a registered person shall, on receipt of advance payment with respect to any supply of goods or`
  line `services or both, issue a receipt voucher or any other document, containing such particulars as may be`
  line `prescribed, evidencing receipt of such payment;`
  line
  line `(e) where, on receipt of advance payment with respect to any supply of goods or services or both`
  line `the registered person issues a receipt voucher, but subsequently no supply is made and no tax invoice`
  line `is issued in pursuance thereof, the said registered person may issue to the person who had made the`
  line `payment, a refund voucher against such payment;`
  line
  line `(f) a registered person who is liable to pay tax under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 9 shall issue an invoice in respect of goods or services or both received by him from the`
  line `supplier who is not registered on the date of receipt of goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(g) a registered person who is liable to pay tax under sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 9 shall issue a payment voucher at the time of making payment to the supplier.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.---For the purposes of clause (f), the expression "supplier who is not registered"`
  line `shall include the supplier who is registered solely for the purpose of deduction of tax under`
  line `section 51.]`
  line
  line `(4) In case of continuous supply of goods, where successive statements of accounts or successive`
  line `payments are involved, the invoice shall be issued before or at the time each such statement is issued or,`
  line `as the case may be, each such payment is received.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of clause (d) of sub-section (3), in case of continuous supply of`
  line services,---
  line
  line `(a) where the due date of payment is ascertainable from the contract, the invoice shall be issued`
  line `on or before the due date of payment;`
  line
  line `(b) where the due date of payment is not ascertainable from the contract, the invoice shall be`
  line `issued before or at the time when the supplier of service receives the payment;`
  line
  line `(c) where the payment is linked to the completion of an event, the invoice shall be issued on or`
  line `before the date of completion of that event.`
  line
  line `(6) In a case where the supply of services ceases under a contract before the completion of the supply,`
  line `the invoice shall be issued at the time when the supply ceases and such invoice shall be issued to the`
  line `extent of the supply made before such cessation.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where the goods being sent or taken on`
  line `approval for sale or return are removed before the supply takes place, the invoice shall be issued before or`
  line `at the time of supply or six months from the date of removal, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section, the expression "tax invoice" shall include any revised`
  line `invoice issued by the supplier in respect of a supply made earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 123 (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 122 (w.e.f. 27-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_a:
  sectionId (50221)
  sectionNo 31A
  orderNo 33
  title `Facility of digital payment to recipient.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=50221&sectionno=31A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_31_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[31A. Facility of digital payment to recipient.-- The Government may, on the recommendations of`
  line `the Council, prescribe a class of registered persons who shall provide prescribed modes of electronic`
  line `payment to the recipient of supply of goods or services or both made by him and give option to such`
  line `recipient to make payment accordingly, in such manner and subject to such conditions and restrictions, as`
  line `may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5147)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Prohibition of unauthorised collection of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5147&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person who is not a registered person`
  line `shall not collect in respect of any supply of goods or services or both any amount by way of tax under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) No registered person shall collect tax except in accordance with the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (5148)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Amount of tax to be indicated in tax invoice and other documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5148&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, where any supply is made for a`
  line `consideration, every person who is liable to pay tax for such supply shall prominently indicate in all`
  line `documents relating to assessment, tax invoice and other like documents, the amount of tax which shall`
  line `form part of the price at which such supply is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (5149)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Credit and debit notes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5149&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Where one or more tax invoices have] been issued for supply of any goods or services or both and the taxable value or tax charged in that tax invoice is found to exceed the taxable value or tax payable in respect of such supply, or where the goods supplied are returned by the recipient, or where goods or services or both supplied are found to be deficient, the registered person, who has supplied such goods or services or both, may issue to the recipient ^2 [one or more credit notes for supplies made in a financial year] containing such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any registered person who issues a credit note in relation to a supply of goods or services or both shall declare the details of such credit note in the return for the month during which such credit note has been issued but not later than ^3[the thirtieth day of November] following the end of the financial year in which such supply was made, or the date of furnishing of the relevant annual return, whichever is earlier, and the tax liability shall be adjusted in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no reduction in output tax liability of the supplier shall be permitted, if the incidence of tax and interest on such supply has been passed on to any other person.`
  line
  line `(3) ^1[Where one or more tax invoices have] been issued for supply of any goods or services or both and the taxable value or tax charged in that tax invoice is found to be less than the taxable value or tax payable in respect of such supply, the registered person, who has supplied such goods or services or both, shall issue to the recipient ^4[one or more debit notes for supplies made in a financial year] containing such particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Any registered person who issues a debit note in relation to a supply of goods or services or both shall declare the details of such debit note in the return for the month during which such debit note has been issued and the tax liability shall be adjusted in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this Act, the expression "debit note" shall include a supplementary`
  line invoice.
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 15, for "Where a tax invoice has" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 15,ibid., for "a credit note" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 102, for "September" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for "a debit note" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (5150)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Accounts and other records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5150&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered person shall keep and maintain, at his`
  line `principal place of business, as mentioned in the certificate of registration, a true and correct account of---`
  line
  line `(a) production or manufacture of goods;`
  line
  line `(b) inward and outward supply of goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(c) stock of goods;`
  line
  line `(d) input tax credit availed;`
  line
  line `(e) output tax payable and paid; and`
  line
  line `(f) such other particulars as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where more than one place of business is specified in the certificate of registration, the`
  line `accounts relating to each place of business shall be kept at such places of business:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the registered person may keep and maintain such accounts and other particulars`
  line `in electronic form in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every owner or operator of warehouse or godown or any other place used for storage of goods and`
  line `every transporter, irrespective of whether he is a registered person or not, shall maintain records of the`
  line `consigner, consignee and other relevant details of the goods in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may notify a class of taxable persons to maintain additional accounts or`
  line `documents for such purpose as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the Commissioner considers that any class of taxable person is not in a position to keep`
  line `and maintain accounts in accordance with the provisions of this section, he may, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, permit such class of taxable persons to maintain accounts in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any department of the Central Government or a State Government or a local authority, whose books of account are subject to audit by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or an auditor appointed for auditing the accounts of local authorities under any law for the time being in force.]`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of clause (h) of sub-section (5) of section 17, where the registered person fails to account for the goods or services or both in accordance with the provisions of subsection (1), the proper officer shall determine the amount of tax payable on the goods or services or both that are not accounted for, as if such goods or services or both had been supplied by such person and the provisions of section 73 or section 74 ^3[or section 74A], as the case may be, shall, mutatis mutandis, apply for determination of such tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (5) omitted by Act 13 of 2021, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 16 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 123 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (5151)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Period of retention of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5151&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Every registered person required to keep and maintain books`
  line `of account or other records in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 35 shall retain`
  line `them until the expiry of seventy-two months from the due date of furnishing of annual return for the year`
  line `pertaining to such accounts and records:`
  line
  line `Provided that a registered person, who is a party to an appeal or revision or any other proceedings`
  line `before any Appellate Authority or Revisional Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court, whether filed by him`
  line `or by the Commissioner, or is under investigation for an offence under Chapter XIX, shall retain the books`
  line `of account and other records pertaining to the subject matter of such appeal or revision or proceedings or`
  line `investigation for a period of one year after final disposal of such appeal or revision or proceedings or`
  line `investigation, or for the period specified above, whichever is later.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (5152)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Furnishing details of outward supplies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5152&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered person, other than an Input Service Distributor, a non-resident taxable person and a person paying tax under the provisions of section 10 or section 51 or section 52, shall furnish, electronically, ^1[subject to such conditions and restrictions and] in such form and manner as may be prescribed, the details of outward supplies of goods or services or both effected during a tax period on or before the tenth day of the month succeeding the said tax period and such details ^2[shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, be communicated to the recipient of the said supplies:]`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that] the Commissioner may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by notification, extend the time limit for furnishing such details for such class of taxable persons as may be specified therein:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided further that] any extension of time limit notified by the Commissioner of State tax or Commissioner of Union territory tax shall be deemed to be notified by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Any registered person, who has furnished the details under sub-section (1) for any tax period ^7***, shall, upon discovery of any error or omission therein, rectify such error or omission in such manner as may be prescribed, and shall pay the tax and interest, if any, in case there is a short payment of tax on account of such error or omission, in the return to be furnished for such tax period:`
  line
  line `Provided that no rectification of error or omission in respect of the details furnished under sub-section (1) shall be allowed after ^8[the thirtieth day of November] following the end of the financial year to which such details pertain, or furnishing of the relevant annual return, whichever is earlier..`
  line
  line `^9[Provided further that the rectification of error or omission in respect of the details furnished under sub-section (1) shall be allowed after furnishing of the return under section 39 for the month of September, 2018 till the due date for furnishing the details under sub-section (1) for the month of March, 2019 or for the quarter January, 2019 to March, 2019.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this Chapter, the expression "details of outward supplies" shall include details of invoices, debit notes, credit notes and revised invoices issued in relation to outward supplies made during any tax period.`
  line
  line `^10[(4) A registered person shall not be allowed to furnish the details of outward supplies under sub-section (1) for a tax period, if the details of outward supplies for any of the previous tax periods has not been furnished by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow a registered person or a class of registered persons to furnish the details of outward supplies under sub-section (1), even if he has not furnished the details of outward supplies for one or more previous tax periods.]`
  line
  line `^11[(5) A registered person shall not be allowed to furnish the details of outward supplies under`
  line `sub-section (1) for a tax period after the expiry of a period of three years from the due date of furnishing`
  line `the said details:`
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject`
  line `to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow a registered person or a class of`
  line `registered persons to furnish the details of outward supplies for a tax period under sub-section (1), even`
  line `after the expiry of the said period of three years from the due date of furnishing the said details.]`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `3. First Proviso omitted by s. 103 ibid (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., for "Provided further that" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., "Provided also that"(w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (2) omitted by, s. 103, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `7. The words and figures "and which have remained unmatched under section 42 or section 43" omitted by s. 103, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., "furnishing of the return under section 39 for the month of September" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by vide Order No. 02/2018-Central Tax dated 31-12-2018.`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 10, (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 142 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (5153)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Communication of details of inward supplies and input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 104, for section 38 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5153&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[38. Communication of details of inward supplies input tax credit.--- (1) The details of outward supplies furnished by the registered persons under sub-section (1) of section 37 and of such other supplies as may be prescribed, and an auto-generated statement containing the details of input tax credit shall be made available electronically to the recipients of such supplies in such form and manner, within such time, and subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The auto-generated statement under sub-section (1) shall consist of---`
  line
  line `(a) details of inward supplies in respect of which credit of input tax may be available to the recipient; and`
  line
  line `(b) details of supplies in respect of which such credit cannot be availed, whether wholly or partly, by the recipient, on account of the details of the said supplies being furnished under sub-section (1) of section 37,---`
  line
  line `(i) by any registered person within such period of taking registration as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(ii) by any registered person, who has defaulted in payment of tax and where such default has continued for such period as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(iii) by any registered person, the output tax payable by whom in accordance with the statement of outward supplies furnished by him under the said sub-section during such period, as may be prescribed, exceeds the output tax paid by him during the said period by such limit as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(iv) by any registered person who, during such period as may be prescribed, has availed credit of input tax of an amount that exceeds the credit that can be availed by him in accordance with clause (a), by such limit as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(v) by any registered person, who has defaulted in discharging his tax liability in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (12) of section 49 subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(vi) by such other class of persons as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (5154)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Furnishing of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5154&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every registered person, other than an Input Service Distributor or`
  line `a non-resident taxable person or a person paying tax under the provisions of section 10 or section 51 or section 52 shall, for every calendar month or part thereof, furnish, a return, electronically, of inward and outward supplies of goods or services or both, input tax credit availed, tax payable, tax paid and such other particulars, in such form and manner, and within such time, as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, notify certain class of registered persons who shall furnish a return for every quarter or part thereof, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person paying tax under the provisions of section 10, shall, for each financial year or part thereof, furnish a return, electronically, of turnover in the State or Union territory, inward supplies of goods or services or both, tax payable, tax paid and such other particulars in such form and manner, and within such time, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every registered person required to deduct tax at source under section 51 shall electronically`
  line `furnish a return for every calendar month of the deductions made during the month in such form and`
  line `manner and within such time as may be prescribed:`
  line `Provided that the said registered person shall furnish a return for every calendar month whether or not`
  line `any deductions have been made during the said month.]`
  line
  line `(4) Every taxable person registered as an Input Service Distributor shall, for every calendar month or part thereof, furnish, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, a return, electronically, within thirteen days after the end of such month.`
  line
  line `(5) Every registered non-resident taxable person shall, for every calendar month or part thereof, furnish, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, a return, electronically, within ^3[thirteen] days after the end of a calendar month or within seven days after the last day of the period of registration specified under sub-section (1) of section 27, whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(6) The Commissioner may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by notification, extend the time limit for furnishing the returns under this section for such class of registered persons as may be specified therein:`
  line
  line `Provided that any extension of time limit notified by the Commissioner of State tax or Union territory tax shall be deemed to be notified by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `^4[(7) Every registered person who is required to furnish a return under sub-section (1), other than the person referred to in the proviso thereto, or sub-section (3) or sub-section (5), shall pay to the Government the tax due as per such return not later than the last date on which he is required to furnish such return:`
  line
  line `^5[Provided that every registered person furnishing return under the proviso to sub-section (1) shall pay to the Government, in such form and manner, and within such time, as may be prescribed,`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to the tax due taking into account inward and outward supplies of goods or services or both, input tax credit availed, tax payable and such other particulars during a month; or`
  line
  line `(b) in lieu of the amount referred to in clause (a), an amount determined in such manner and subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `Provided further that every registered person furnishing return under sub-section (2) shall pay to the`
  line `Government, the tax due taking into account turnover in the State or Union territory, inward supplies of`
  line `goods or services or both, tax payable, and such other particulars during a quarter, in such form and`
  line `manner, and within such time, as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(8) Every registered person who is required to furnish a return under sub-section (1) or sub-section`
  line `(2) shall furnish a return for every tax period whether or not any supplies of goods or services or both`
  line `have been made during such tax period.`
  line
  line `(9) ^6[Where] any registered person after furnishing a return`
  line `under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) discovers`
  line `any omission or incorrect particulars therein, other than as a result of scrutiny, audit, inspection or`
  line `enforcement activity by the tax authorities, he shall rectify such omission or incorrect particulars ^7[in such form and manner as may prescribed], subject to payment of interest under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rectification of any omission or incorrect particulars shall be allowed after ^8[the thirtieth day of November ] following ^9[the end of the financial year to which such details pertain], or the actual date of furnishing of relevant annual return,`
  line `whichever is earlier.`
  line
  line `(10) A registered person shall not be allowed to furnish a return for a tax period if the return for any of the previous tax periods ^10[or the details of outward supplies under sub-section (1) of section 37 for the said tax period has not been furnished by him:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow a registered person or a class of registered persons to furnish the return, even if he has not furnished the returns for one or more previous tax periods or has not furnished the details of outward supplies under sub-section (1) of section 37 for the said tax period.]`
  line
  line `^11[(11) A registered person shall not be allowed to furnish a return for a tax period after the expiry of a`
  line `period of three years from the due date of furnishing the said return:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject`
  line `to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow a registered person or a class of`
  line `registered persons to furnish the return for a tax period, even after the expiry of the said period of three`
  line `years from the due date of furnishing the said return.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 97, for sub-section (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 10-11-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 124, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 105, for "twenty" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 97, for sub-section (7) (w.e.f. 10-11-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 105, for the first proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 105, ibid. for "Subject to the provisions of sections 37 and 38, if" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 17, for "in the return to be furnished for the month or quarter during which such omission or incorrect particulars are noticed" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 105 for "the due date for furnishing of return for the month of September or second quarter" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 17, for "the end of the financial year" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 105, for "has not been furnished by him" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 143 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (5155)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `First return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5155&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Every registered person who has made outward supplies in the period between the`
  line `date on which he became liable to registration till the date on which registration has been granted shall`
  line `declare the same in the first return furnished by him after grant of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (5156)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Availment of input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 106, for "section 41" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5156&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[41. Availment of input tax credit.--- (1) Every registered person shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, be entitled to avail the credit of eligible input tax, as self-assessed, in his return and such amount shall be credited to his electronic credit ledger.`
  line
  line `(2) The credit of input tax availed by a registered person under sub-section (1) in respect of such supplies of goods or services or both, the tax payable whereon has not been paid by the supplier, shall be reversed along with applicable interest, by the said person in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the said supplier makes payment of the tax payable in respect of the aforesaid supplies, the said registered person may re-avail the amount of credit reversed by him in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (5157)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title Omitted.
  content `42. [Matching, reversal and reclaim of input tax credit].---Omitted by the Finance Act, 2022 (6 of 2022), s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5157&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (5158)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title Omitted.
  content `43. [Matching, reversal and reclaim of reduction in output tax liability].--- Omitted by the Finance Act, 2022 (6 of 2022), s. 107 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5158&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43_a:
  sectionId (51462)
