obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (5159)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 47
  title `Annual return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5159&sectionno=44&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[44. Annual return.--- ^2[(1)] Every registered person, other than an Input Service Distributor, a`
  line `person paying tax under section 51 or section 52, a casual taxable person and a non-resident taxable`
  line `person shall furnish an annual return which may include a self-certified reconciliation statement,`
  line `reconciling the value of supplies declared in the return furnished for the financial year, with the audited`
  line `annual financial statement for every financial year electronically, within such time and in such form and`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Commissioner may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification,`
  line `exempt any class of registered persons from filing annual return under this section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this section shall apply to any department of the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or a local authority, whose books of account are subject to audit by`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or an auditor appointed for auditing the accounts of local`
  line `authorities under any law for the time being in force.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) A registered person shall not be allowed to furnish an annual return under sub-section (1) for a`
  line `financial year after the expiry of a period of three years from the due date of furnishing the said annual`
  line `return:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, and`
  line `subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow a registered person or a class`
  line `of registered persons to furnish an annual return for a financial year under sub-section (1), even after the`
  line `expiry of the said period of three years from the due date of furnishing the said annual return.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 111, for section 44 (w.e.f. 1-8-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Section 44 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 8 of 2023, s. 144 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023)`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 144 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023)`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (5160)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 48
  title `Final return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5160&sectionno=45&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Every registered person who is required to furnish a return under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 39 and whose registration has been cancelled shall furnish a final return within three months of`
  line `the date of cancellation or date of order of cancellation, whichever is later, in such form and manner as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (5161)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 49
  title `Notice to return defaulters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5161&sectionno=46&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Where a registered person fails to furnish a return under section`
  line `39 or section 44 or section 45, a notice shall be issued requiring him to furnish such return within fifteen`
  line `days in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (5162)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 50
  title `Levy of late fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5162&sectionno=47&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any registered person who fails to furnish the details of outward ^1*** supplies required under section 37 ^2*** or returns required under section 39 or`
  line `section 45 ^3[or section 52] by the due date shall pay a late fee of one hundred rupees for every day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum amount of five thousand rupees..`
  line
  line `(2) Any registered person who fails to furnish the return required under section 44 by the due date shall be liable to pay a late fee of one hundred rupees for every day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of an amount calculated at a quarter per cent. of his turnover in the State or Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "or inward" omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 108 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or section 38" omitted by s. 108, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 108, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (5163)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 51
  title `Goods and services tax practitioners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5163&sectionno=48&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) The manner of approval of goods and services tax`
  line `practitioners, their eligibility conditions, duties and obligations, manner of removal and other conditions relevant for their functioning shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person may authorise an approved goods and services tax practitioner to furnish the details of outward supplies under section 37 ^1*** and the return under section 39 or section 44 or section 45 ^2[and to perform such other functions] in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the responsibility for correctness of any particulars furnished in the return or other details filed by the goods and services tax practitioners shall continue to rest with the registered person on whose behalf such return and details are furnished.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ", the details of inward supplies under section 38" omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 109 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (5164)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 52
  title `Payment of tax, interest, penalty and other amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5164&sectionno=49&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every deposit made towards tax,`
  line `interest, penalty, fee or any other amount by a person by internet banking or by using credit or debit cards or National Electronic Fund Transfer or Real Time Gross Settlement or by such other mode and subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, shall be credited to the electronic cash ledger of such person to be maintained in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The input tax credit as self-assessed in the return of a registered person shall be credited to his electronic credit ledger, in accordance with ^1[section 41 ^2***] to be maintained in such manner as may be prescribed..`
  line
  line `(3) The amount available in the electronic cash ledger may be used for making any payment towards`
  line `tax, interest, penalty, fees or any other amount payable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder in such manner and subject to such conditions and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The amount available in the electronic credit ledger may be used for making any payment towards output tax under this Act or under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act in such manner and subject to such conditions ^3[and restrictions] and within such time as may be prescribed..`
  line
  line `(5) The amount of input tax credit available in the electronic credit ledger of the registered person on`
  line `account of---`
  line
  line `(a) integrated tax shall first be utilised towards payment of integrated tax and the amount`
  line `remaining, if any, may be utilised towards the payment of central tax and State tax, or as the case may`
  line `be, Union territory tax, in that order;`
  line
  line `(b) the central tax shall first be utilised towards payment of central tax and the amount remaining, if`
  line `any, may be utilised towards the payment of integrated tax;`
  line
  line `(c) the State tax shall first be utilised towards payment of State tax and the amount remaining, if`
  line `any, may be utilised towards payment of integrated tax;`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that the input tax credit on account of State tax shall be utilised towards payment of`
  line `integrated tax only where the balance of the input tax credit on account of central tax is not available`
  line `for payment of integrated tax;]`
  line
  line `(d) the Union territory tax shall first be utilised towards payment of Union territory tax and the amount`
  line `remaining, if any, may be utilised towards payment of integrated tax;`
  line
  line `^4]Provided that the input tax credit on account of Union territory tax shall be utilised towards`
  line `payment of integrated tax only where the balance of the input tax credit on account of central tax is`
  line `not available for payment of integrated tax;]`
  line
  line `(e) the central tax shall not be utilised towards payment of State tax or Union territory tax; and`
  line
  line `(f) the State tax or Union territory tax shall not be utilised towards payment of central tax.`
  line
  line `(6) The balance in the electronic cash ledger or electronic credit ledger after payment of tax, interest,`
  line `penalty, fee or any other amount payable under this Act or the rules made thereunder may be refunded in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 54.`
  line
  line `(7) All liabilities of a taxable person under this Act shall be recorded and maintained in an electronic`
  line `liability register in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) Every taxable person shall discharge his tax and other dues under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder in the following order, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) self-assessed tax, and other dues related to returns of previous tax periods;`
  line
  line `(b) self-assessed tax, and other dues related to the return of the current tax period;`
  line
  line `(c) any other amount payable under this Act or the rules made thereunder including the demand`
  line `determined under section 73 or section 74 ^5[or section 74A].`
  line
  line `(9) Every person who has paid the tax on goods or services or both under this Act shall, unless the`
  line `contrary is proved by him, be deemed to have passed on the full incidence of such tax to the recipient of`
  line `such goods or services or both.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) the date of credit to the account of the Government in the authorised bank shall be deemed to`
  line `be the date of deposit in the electronic cash ledger;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression,---`
  line
  line `(i) "tax dues" means the tax payable under this Act and does not include interest, fee and`
  line `penalty; and`
  line
  line `(ii) "other dues" means interest, penalty, fee or any other amount payable under this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `^6[^7[(10) A registered person may, on the common portal, transfer any amount of tax, interest, penalty, fee or any other amount available in the electronic cash ledger under this Act, to the electronic cash ledger for,---`
  line
  line `(a) integrated tax, central tax, State tax, Union territory tax or cess; or`
  line
  line `(b) integrated tax or central tax of a distinct person as specified in sub-section (4) or sub-section (5) of section 25,`
  line
  line `in such form and manner and subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed and such transfer shall be deemed to be a refund from the electronic cash ledger under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such transfer under clause (b) shall be allowed if the said registered person has any unpaid liability in his electronic liability register.]`
  line
  line `(11) Where any amount has been transferred to the electronic cash ledger under this Act, the same`
  line `shall be deemed to be deposited in the said ledger as provided in sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `^8(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, subject to such conditions and restrictions, specify such maximum proportion of output tax liability under this Act or under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act, 2017 (13 of 2017) which may be discharged through the electronic credit ledger by a registered person or a class of registered persons, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 20, ibid., for "section 41" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or section 43A" omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 110, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 20, (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 125 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 99 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 110, for sub-section 10 (w.e.f. 5-7-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 110, ibid. (w.e.f. 5-7-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_a:
  sectionId (49428)
  sectionNo 49A
  orderNo 53
  title `Utilisation of input tax credit subject to certain conditions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=49428&sectionno=49A&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_49_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[49A. Utilisation of input tax credit subject to certain conditions.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in section 49, the input tax credit on account of central tax, State tax or Union territory tax shall be utilised towards payment of integrated tax, central tax, State tax or Union territory tax, as the case may be, only`
  line `after the input tax credit available on account of integrated tax has first been utilised fully towards such payment.]`
obj_root_law_sections_49_b:
  sectionId (49429)
  sectionNo 49B
  orderNo 54
  title `Order of utilisation of input tax credit.`
  content `^1[49B. Order of utilisation of input tax credit.--- Notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter and subject to the provisions of clause (e) and clause (f) of sub-section (5) of section 49, the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, prescribe the order and manner of utilisation of the input tax credit on account of integrated tax, central tax, State tax or Union territory tax, as the case may be, towards payment of any such tax.]`
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=49429&sectionno=49B&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (5165)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 55
  title `Interest on delayed payment of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5165&sectionno=50&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who is liable to pay tax in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, but fails to pay the tax or any part thereof to the`
  line `Government within the period prescribed, shall for the period for which the tax or any part thereof remains unpaid, pay, on his own, interest at such rate, not exceeding eighteen per cent., as may be notified by the`
  line `Government on the recommendations of the Council.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the interest on tax payable in respect of supplies made during a tax period and declared in the return for the said period furnished after the due date in accordance with the provisions of section 39, except where such return is furnished after commencement of any proceedings under section 73 or section 74 ^2[or section 74A] in respect of the said period, shall be payable on that portion of the tax which is paid by debiting the electronic cash ledger.]`
  line
  line `(2) The interest under sub-section (1) shall be calculated, in such manner as may be prescribed, from the day succeeding the day on which such tax was due to be paid.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Where the input tax credit has been wrongly availed and utilised, the registered person shall pay interest on such input tax credit wrongly availed and utilised, at such rate not exceeding twenty-four per cent. as may be notified by the Government, on the recommendations of the Council, and the interest shall be calculated, in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by 13 of 2021, s. 112, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2021), vide notification S.O. 2129 (E) Dated (1-6-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024)`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 111, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 5-7-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (5166)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 56
  title `Tax deductions at source.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5166&sectionno=51&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act,`
  line `the Government may mandate,--`
  line
  line `(a) a department or establishment of the Central Government or State Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) local authority; or`
  line
  line `(c) Governmental agencies; or`
  line
  line `(d) such persons or category of persons as may be notified by the Government on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council,`
  line
  line `(hereafter in this section referred to as "the deductor"), to deduct tax at the rate of one per cent. from the`
  line `payment made or credited to the supplier (hereafter in this section referred to as "the deductee") of`
  line `taxable goods or services or both, where the total value of such supply, under a contract, exceeds two lakh`
  line `and fifty thousand rupees:`
  line
  line `Provided that no deduction shall be made if the location of the supplier and the place of supply is in a`
  line `State or Union territory which is different from the State or as the case may be, Union territory of`
  line `registration of the recipient.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of deduction of tax specified above, the value of supply shall be taken`
  line `as the amount excluding the central tax, State tax, Union territory tax, integrated tax and cess indicated in`
  line `the invoice.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount deducted as tax under this section shall be paid to the Government by the deductor`
  line `within ten days after the end of the month in which such deduction is made, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `^1[(3) A certificate of tax deduction at source shall be issued in such form and in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(5) The deductee shall claim credit, in his electronic cash ledger, of the tax deducted and reflected in`
  line `the return of the deductor furnished under sub-section (3) of section 39, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(6) If any deductor fails to pay to the Government the amount deducted as tax under sub-section (1),`
  line `he shall pay interest in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 50, in addition to the`
  line `amount of tax deducted.`
  line
  line `(7) The determination of the amount in default under this section shall be made in the manner`
  line `specified in section 73 or section 74 ^3[or section 74A].`
  line
  line `(8)The refund to the deductor or the deductee arising on account of excess or erroneous deduction`
  line `shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of section 54:`
  line
  line `Provided that no refund to the deductor shall be granted, if the amount deducted has been credited to`
  line `the electronic cash ledger of the deductee.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 124, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (4) omitted by s. 124, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 127 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (5167)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 57
  title `Collection of tax at stores.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5167&sectionno=52&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act,`
  line `every electronic commerce operator (hereafter in this section referred to as the "operator"), not being an`
  line `agent, shall collect an amount calculated at such rate not exceeding one per cent., as may be notified by`
  line `the Government on the recommendations of the Council, of the net value of taxable supplies made`
  line `through it by other suppliers where the consideration with respect to such supplies is to be collected by`
  line `the operator.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "net value of taxable supplies"`
  line `shall mean the aggregate value of taxable supplies of goods or services or both, other than services`
  line `notified under sub-section (5) of section 9, made during any month by all registered persons through the`
  line `operator reduced by the aggregate value of taxable supplies returned to the suppliers during the said`
  line month.
  line
  line `(2) The power to collect the amount specified in sub-section (1) shall be without prejudice to any`
  line `other mode of recovery from the operator.`
  line
  line `(3) The amount collected under sub-section (1) shall be paid to the Government by the operator`
  line `within ten days after the end of the month in which such collection is made, in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) Every operator who collects the amount specified in sub-section (1) shall furnish a statement,`
  line `electronically, containing the details of outward supplies of goods or services or both effected through it,`
  line `including the supplies of goods or services or both returned through it, and the amount collected under`
  line `sub-section (1) during a month, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, within ten days after the`
  line `end of such month.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Commissioner may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, by notification, extend`
  line `the time limit for furnishing the statement for such class of registered persons as may be specified therein:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any extension of time limit notified by the Commissioner of State tax or the`
  line `Commissioner of Union territory tax shall be deemed to be notified by the Commissioner.]`
  line
  line `(5) Every operator who collects the amount specified in sub-section (1) shall furnish an annual`
  line `statement, electronically, containing the details of outward supplies of goods or services or both effected`
  line `through it, including the supplies of goods or services or both returned through it, and the amount`
  line `collected under the said sub-section during the financial year, in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, before the thirty first day of December following the end of such financial year.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Commissioner may, on the recommendations of the Council and for reasons to be`
  line `recorded in writing, by notification, extend the time limit for furnishing the annual statement for such`
  line `class of registered persons as may be specified therein:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any extension of time limit notified by the Commissioner of State tax or the`
  line `Commissioner of Union territory tax shall be deemed to be notified by the Commissioner.]`
  line
  line `(6) If any operator after furnishing a statement under sub-section (4) discovers any omission or`
  line `incorrect particulars therein, other than as a result of scrutiny, audit, inspection or enforcement activity by`
  line `the tax authorities, he shall rectify such omission or incorrect particulars in the statement to be furnished`
  line `for the month during which such omission or incorrect particulars are noticed, subject to payment of`
  line `interest, as specified in sub-section (1) of section 50:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rectification of any omission or incorrect particulars shall be allowed after the ^2[thirtieth day of November] following the end of the financial year or the actual date of furnishing of the relevant annual statement, whichever is earlier..`
  line
  line `(7) The supplier who has supplied the goods or services or both through the operator shall claim`
  line `credit, in his electronic cash ledger, of the amount collected and reflected in the statement of the operator`
  line `furnished under sub-section (4), in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) The details of supplies furnished by every operator under sub-section (4) shall be matched with the`
  line `corresponding details of outward supplies furnished by the concerned supplier registered under this Act in such`
  line `manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the details of outward supplies furnished by the operator under sub-section (4) do not`
  line `match with the corresponding details furnished by the supplier under ^3[section 37 or section 39], the`
  line `discrepancy shall be communicated to both persons in such manner and within such time as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(10) The amount in respect of which any discrepancy is communicated under sub-section (9) and`
  line `which is not rectified by the supplier in his valid return or the operator in his statement for the month in`
  line `which discrepancy is communicated, shall be added to the output tax liability of the said supplier, where`
  line `the value of outward supplies furnished by the operator is more than the value of outward supplies`
  line `furnished by the supplier, in his return for the month succeeding the month in which the discrepancy is`
  line `communicated in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(11) The concerned supplier, in whose output tax liability any amount has been added under subsection (10), shall pay the tax payable in respect of such supply along with interest, at the rate specified`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 50 on the amount so added from the date such tax was due till the date of`
  line `its payment.`
  line
  line `(12) Any authority not below the rank of Deputy Commissioner may serve a notice, either before or`
  line `during the course of any proceedings under this Act, requiring the operator to furnish such details relating`
  line to---
  line
  line `(a) supplies of goods or services or both effected through such operator during any period; or`
  line
  line `(b) stock of goods held by the suppliers making supplies through such operator in the godowns or`
  line `warehouses, by whatever name called, managed by such operator and declared as additional places of`
  line `business by such suppliers,`
  line
  line `as may be specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(13) Every operator on whom a notice has been served under sub-section (12) shall furnish the`
  line `required information within fifteen working days of the date of service of such notice.`
  line
  line `(14) Any person who fails to furnish the information required by the notice served under`
  line `sub-section (12) shall, without prejudice to any action that may be taken under section 122, be liable to a`
  line `penalty which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the expression "concerned supplier" shall mean the`
  line `supplier of goods or services or both making supplies through the operator.`
  line
  line `^4[(15) The operator shall not be allowed to furnish a statement under sub-section (4) after the expiry`
  line `of a period of three years from the due date of furnishing the said statement:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, subject`
  line `to such conditions and restrictions as may be specified therein, allow an operator or a class of operators to`
  line `furnish a statement under sub-section (4), even after the expiry of the said period of three years from the`
  line `due date of furnishing the said statement.]`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 112, for "due date for furnishing of statement for the month of September" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 22 for "section 37" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 145 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (5168)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 58
  title `Transfer of input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5168&sectionno=53&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `On utilisation of input tax credit availed under this Act for`
  line `payment of tax dues under the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (5) of section 49, as reflected in the valid return furnished under sub-section (1) of section`
  line `39, the amount collected as central tax shall stand reduced by an amount equal to such credit so utilised and the Central Government shall transfer an amount equal to the amount so reduced from the central tax`
  line `account to the integrated tax account in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53_a:
  sectionId (50222)
  sectionNo 53A
  orderNo 59
  title `Transfer of certain amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 102 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=50222&sectionno=53A&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_53_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[53A. Transfer of certain amounts.--- Where any amount has been transferred from the electronic`
  line `cash ledger under this Act to the electronic cash ledger under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the`
  line `Union territory Goods and Services Tax Act, the Government shall, transfer to the State tax account or the`
  line `Union territory tax account, an amount equal to the amount transferred from the electronic cash ledger, in`
  line `such manner and within such time as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (5169)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 60
  title `Refund of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5169&sectionno=54&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person claiming refund of any tax and interest, if any, paid on such tax`
  line `or any other amount paid by him, may make an application before the expiry of two years from the`
  line `relevant date in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that a registered person, claiming refund of any balance in the electronic cash ledger in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (6) of section 49, may claim such refund in ^1 [such from and] manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A specialised agency of the United Nations Organisation or any Multilateral Financial Institution and Organisation notified under the United Nations (Privileges and Immunities) Act, 1947 (46 of 1947), Consulate or Embassy of foreign countries or any other person or class of persons, as notified under section 55, entitled to a refund of tax paid by it on inward supplies of goods or services or both, may make an application for such refund, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, before the expiry of ^2[two years] from the last day of the quarter in which such supply was received.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (10), a registered person may claim refund of any`
  line `unutilised input tax credit at the end of any tax period:`
  line
  line `Provided that no refund of unutilised input tax credit shall be allowed in cases other than---`
  line
  line `(i) zero rated supplies made without payment of tax;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the credit has accumulated on account of rate of tax on inputs being higher than the rate`
  line `of tax on output supplies (other than nil rated or fully exempt supplies), except supplies of goods or`
  line `services or both as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council:`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `Provided also that no refund of input tax credit shall be allowed, if the supplier of goods or services or`
  line `both avails of drawback in respect of central tax or claims refund of the integrated tax paid on such`
  line supplies.
  line
  line `(4) The application shall be accompanied by---`
  line
  line `(a) such documentary evidence as may be prescribed to establish that a refund is due to the`
  line `applicant; and`
  line
  line `(b) such documentary or other evidence (including the documents referred to in section 33) as the`
  line `applicant may furnish to establish that the amount of tax and interest, if any, paid on such tax or any`
  line `other amount paid in relation to which such refund is claimed was collected from, or paid by, him and`
  line `the incidence of such tax and interest had not been passed on to any other person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the amount claimed as refund is less than two lakh rupees, it shall not be`
  line `necessary for the applicant to furnish any documentary and other evidences but he may file a declaration,`
  line `based on the documentary or other evidences available with him, certifying that the incidence of such tax`
  line `and interest had not been passed on to any other person.`
  line
  line `(5) If, on receipt of any such application, the proper officer is satisfied that the whole or part of the`
  line `amount claimed as refund is refundable, he may make an order accordingly and the amount so determined`
  line `shall be credited to the Fund referred to in section 57.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5), the proper officer may, in the case of any`
  line `claim for refund on account of zero-rated supply of goods or services or both made by registered persons,`
  line `other than such category of registered persons as may be notified by the Government on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, refund on a provisional basis, ninety per cent. of the total amount so`
  line `claimed, ^4*** in such manner and subject to such conditions, limitations and safeguards as may be prescribed and thereafter make an order under`
  line `sub-section (5) for final settlement of the refund claim after due verification of documents furnished by`
  line `the applicant.`
  line
  line `(7) The proper officer shall issue the order under sub-section (5) within sixty days from the date of`
  line `receipt of application complete in all respects.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (5), the refundable amount shall, instead of being credited to the Fund, be paid to the applicant, if such amount is relatable to---`
  line
  line `(a) refund of tax paid on ^5[export] of goods or services or both or on inputs or input services used in making such ^5[exports];`
  line
  line `(b) refund of unutilised input tax credit under sub-section (3);`
  line
  line `(c) refund of tax paid on a supply which is not provided, either wholly or partially, and for which`
  line `invoice has not been issued, or where a refund voucher has been issued;`
  line
  line `(d) refund of tax in pursuance of section 77;`
  line
  line `(e) the tax and interest, if any, or any other amount paid by the applicant, if he had not passed on the incidence of such tax and interest to any other person; or`
  line
  line `(f) the tax or interest borne by such other class of applicants as the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `^6[(8A) The Government may disburse the refund of the State tax in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any judgment, decree, order or direction of the Appellate Tribunal or any court or in any other provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or in any other law for the time being in force, no refund shall be made except in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (8).`
  line
  line `(10) Where any refund is due ^7*** to a registered person who has defaulted in furnishing any return or who is required to pay any tax, interest or penalty, which has not been stayed by any court, Tribunal or Appellate Authority by the specified date, the proper officer may---`
  line
  line `(a) withhold payment of refund due until the said person has furnished the return or paid the tax,`
  line `interest or penalty, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) deduct from the refund due, any tax, interest, penalty, fee or any other amount which the`
  line `taxable person is liable to pay but which remains unpaid under this Act or under the existing law.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "specified date" shall mean the`
  line `last date for filing an appeal under this Act.`
  line
  line `(11) Where an order giving rise to a refund is the subject matter of an appeal or further proceedings or`
  line `where any other proceedings under this Act is pending and the Commissioner is of the opinion that grant of`
  line `such refund is likely to adversely affect the revenue in the said appeal or other proceedings on account of`
  line `malfeasance or fraud committed, he may, after giving the taxable person an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `withhold the refund till such time as he may determine.`
  line
  line `(12) Where a refund is withheld under sub-section (11), the taxable person shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in section 56, be entitled to interest at such rate not exceeding six per cent. as may be`
  line `notified on the recommendations of the Council, if as a result of the appeal or further proceedings he`
  line `becomes entitled to refund.`
  line
  line `(13) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this section, the amount of advance tax`
  line `deposited by a casual taxable person or a non-resident taxable person under sub-section (2) of section 27,`
  line `shall not be refunded unless such person has, in respect of the entire period for which the certificate of`
  line `registration granted to him had remained in force, furnished all the returns required under section 39.`
  line
  line `(14) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no refund under sub-section (5) or sub-section (6)`
  line `shall be paid to an applicant, if the amount is less than one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^8[(15) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no refund of unutilised input tax credit on`
  line `account of zero rated supply of goods or of integrated tax paid on account of zero rated supply of goods`
  line `shall be allowed where such zero rated supply of goods is subjected to export duty.]`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(1) "refund" includes refund of tax paid on zero-rated supplies of goods or services or both or on`
  line `inputs or input services used in making such zero-rated supplies, or refund of tax on the supply of`
  line `goods regarded as deemed exports, or refund of unutilised input tax credit as provided under subsection`
  line `(3).`
  line
  line `(2) "relevant date" means---`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of goods exported out of India where a refund of tax paid is available in`
  line `respect of goods themselves or, as the case may be, the inputs or input services used in such`
  line goods,---
  line
  line `(i) if the goods are exported by sea or air, the date on which the ship or the aircraft in`
  line `which such goods are loaded, leaves India; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if the goods are exported by land, the date on which such goods pass the frontier; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if the goods are exported by post, the date of despatch of goods by the Post Office`
  line `concerned to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of supply of goods regarded as deemed exports where a refund of tax paid is`
  line `available in respect of the goods, the date on which the return relating to such deemed exports is`
  line furnished;
  line
  line `^9[(ba) in case of zero-rated supply of goods or services or both to a Special Economic Zone developer or a Special Economic Zone unit where a refund of tax paid is available in respect of such supplies themselves, or as the case may be, the inputs or input services used in such supplies, the due date for furnishing of return under section 39 in respect of such supplies; ]`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of services exported out of India where a refund of tax paid is available in`
  line `respect of services themselves or, as the case may be, the inputs or input services used in such`
  line `services, the date of---`
  line
  line `(i) receipt of payment in convertible foreign exchange, ^10[or in Indian rupees wherever`
  line `permitted by the Reserve Bank of India] where the supply of services had been completed prior to the receipt of such payment; or`
  line
  line `(ii) issue of invoice, where payment for the services had been received in advance prior to`
  line `the date of issue of the invoice;`
  line
  line `(d) in case where the tax becomes refundable as a consequence of judgment, decree, order or`
  line `direction of the Appellate Authority, Appellate Tribunal or any court, the date of communication of such`
  line `judgment, decree, order or direction;`
  line
  line `^11[(e) in the case of refund of unutilised input tax credit under clause (ii) of the first proviso to sub-section (3), the due date for furnishing of return under section 39 for the period in which such claim for refund arises;]`
  line
  line `(f) in the case where tax is paid provisionally under this Act or the rules made thereunder, the date of adjustment of tax after the final assessment thereof;`
  line
  line `(g) in the case of a person, other than the supplier, the date of receipt of goods or services or both by such person; and`
  line
  line `(h) in any other case, the date of payment of tax.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line `1.. Subs. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 113, for "the return furnished under section 39 in such" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 113, ibid., for "six months" (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Second proviso omitted by Act 15 of 2024, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Certain words omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 146 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 23 for "zero-rated supplies" (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 103, (w.e.f. 1-9-2019).`
  line
  line `7. The words, "under sub-section (3)" omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 113 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 6 of 2022, s. 113, (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 23, ibid., for sub-clause (e) (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (5170)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 61
  title `Refund in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5170&sectionno=55&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by`
  line `notification, specify any specialised agency of the United Nations Organisation or any Multilateral Financial`
  line `Institution and Organisation notified under the United Nations (Privileges and Immunities) Act, 1947 (46 of`
  line `1947), Consulate or Embassy of foreign countries and any other person or class of persons as may be specified in`
  line `this behalf, who shall, subject to such conditions and restrictions as may be prescribed, be entitled to claim a`
  line `refund of taxes paid on the notified supplies of goods or services or both received by them.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (5171)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 62
  title `Interest on delayed refunds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 147, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5171&sectionno=56&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `If any tax ordered to be refunded under sub-section (5) of section 54`
  line `to any applicant is not refunded within sixty days from the date of receipt of application under sub-section (1)`
  line `of that section, interest at such rate not exceeding six per cent. as may be specified in the notification issued`
  line `by the Government on the recommendations of the Council shall be payable in respect of such refund ^1[for the period of delay beyond sixty days from the date of receipt of such application till`
  line `the date of refund of such tax, to be computed in such manner and subject to such conditions and`
  line `restrictions as may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any claim of refund arises from an order passed by an adjudicating authority or`
  line `Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court which has attained finality and the same is not refunded`
  line `within sixty days from the date of receipt of application filed consequent to such order, interest at such rate not`
  line `exceeding nine per cent. as may be notified by the Government on the recommendations of the Council shall be`
  line `payable in respect of such refund from the date immediately after the expiry of sixty days from the date of`
  line `receipt of application till the date of refund.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, where any order of refund is made by an Appellate`
  line `Authority, Appellate Tribunal or any court against an order of the proper officer under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 54, the order passed by the Appellate Authority, Appellate Tribunal or by the court shall be`
  line `deemed to be an order passed under the said sub-section (5).`
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (5172)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 63
  title `Consumer Welfare Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5172&sectionno=57&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The Government shall constitute a Fund, to be called the Consumer`
  line `Welfare Fund and there shall be credited to the Fund,---`
  line
  line `(a) the amount referred to in sub-section (5) of section 54;`
  line
  line `(b) any income from investment of the amount credited to the Fund; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other monies received by it,`
  line
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (5173)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 64
  title `Utilisation of Fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5173&sectionno=58&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `(1) All sums credited to the Fund shall be utilised by the Government for`
  line `the welfare of the consumers in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government or the authority specified by it shall maintain proper and separate account and`
  line `other relevant records in relation to the Fund and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as`
  line `may be prescribed in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (5174)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 65
  title Self-assessment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5174&sectionno=59&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Every registered person shall self-assess the taxes payable under this Act and`
  line `furnish a return for each tax period as specified under section 39.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (5175)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 66
  title `Provisional assessment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5175&sectionno=60&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), where the taxable person`
  line `is unable to determine the value of goods or services or both or determine the rate of tax applicable thereto,`
  line `he may request the proper officer in writing giving reasons for payment of tax on a provisional basis and the`
  line `proper officer shall pass an order, within a period not later than ninety days from the date of receipt of such`
  line `request, allowing payment of tax on provisional basis at such rate or on such value as may be specified by`
  line him.
  line
  line `(2) The payment of tax on provisional basis may be allowed, if the taxable person executes a bond in such`
  line `form as may be prescribed, and with such surety or security as the proper officer may deem fit, binding the`
  line `taxable person for payment of the difference between the amount of tax as may be finally assessed and the`
  line `amount of tax provisionally assessed.`
  line
  line `(3) The proper officer shall, within a period not exceeding six months from the date of the`
  line `communication of the order issued under sub-section (1), pass the final assessment order after taking into`
  line `account such information as may be required for finalizing the assessment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period specified in this sub-section may, on sufficient cause being shown and for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, be extended by the Joint Commissioner or Additional Commissioner`
  line `for a further period not exceeding six months and by the Commissioner for such further period not`
  line `exceeding four years.`
  line
  line `(4) The registered person shall be liable to pay interest on any tax payable on the supply of goods or`
  line `services or both under provisional assessment but not paid on the due date specified under sub-section (7) of`
  line `section 39 or the rules made thereunder, at the rate specified under sub-section (1) of section 50, from the first day after the due date of payment of tax in respect of the said supply of goods or services or both till the date of`
  line `actual payment, whether such amount is paid before or after the issuance of order for final assessment.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the registered person is entitled to a refund consequent to the order of final assessment`
  line `under sub-section (3), subject to the provisions of sub-section (8) of section 54, interest shall be paid on`
  line `such refund as provided in section 56.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (5176)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 67
  title `Scrutiny of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 129 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5176&sectionno=61&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proper officer may scrutinize the return and related particulars furnished`
  line `by the registered person to verify the correctness of the return and inform him of the discrepancies noticed, if`
  line `any, in such manner as may be prescribed and seek his explanation thereto.`
  line
  line `(2) In case the explanation is found acceptable, the registered person shall be informed accordingly`
  line `and no further action shall be taken in this regard.`
  line
  line `(3) In case no satisfactory explanation is furnished within a period of thirty days of being informed by`
  line `the proper officer or such further period as may be permitted by him or where the registered person, after`
  line `accepting the discrepancies, fails to take the corrective measure in his return for the month in which the`
  line `discrepancy is accepted, the proper officer may initiate appropriate action including those under section 65`
  line `or section 66 or section 67, or proceed to determine the tax and other dues under section 73 or section 74^1[or section 74A].`
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (5177)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 68
  title `Assessment of non-filers of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5177&sectionno=62&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A], where a registered person fails to furnish the return under section 39 or section 45,`
  line `even after the service of a notice under section 46, the proper officer may proceed to assess the tax liability of`
  line `the said person to the best of his judgment taking into account all the relevant material which is available or`
  line `which he has gathered and issue an assessment order within a period of five years from the date specified`
  line `under section 44 for furnishing of the annual return for the financial year to which the tax not paid relates.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the registered person furnishes a valid return within ^2[sixty days] of the service of the`
  line `assessment order under sub-section (1), the said assessment order shall be deemed to have been`
  line `withdrawn but the liability for payment of interest under sub-section (1) of section 50 or for payment of`
  line `late fee under section 47 shall continue.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where the registered person fails to furnish a valid return within sixty days of the`
  line `service of the assessment order under sub-section (1), he may furnish the same within a further period of`
  line `sixty days on payment of an additional late fee of one hundred rupees for each day of delay beyond sixty`
  line `days of the service of the said assessment order and in case he furnishes valid return within such extended`
  line `period, the said assessment order shall be deemed to have been withdrawn, but the liability to pay interest`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 50 or to pay late fee under section 47 shall continue.]`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 130 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 148, for "thirty days" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 148, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (5178)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 69
  title `Assessment of unregistered persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 131 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5178&sectionno=63&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in`
  line `section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A], where a taxable person fails to obtain registration even though liable to do so or`
  line `whose registration has been cancelled under sub-section (2) of section 29 but who was liable to pay tax,`
  line `the proper officer may proceed to assess the tax liability of such taxable person to the best of his judgment`
  line `for the relevant tax periods and issue an assessment order within a period of five years from the date`
  line `specified under section 44 for furnishing of the annual return for the financial year to which the tax not`
  line `paid relates:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such assessment order shall be passed without giving the person an opportunity of`
  line `being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (5179)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 70
  title `Summary assessment in certain special cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 132 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5179&sectionno=64&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proper officer may, on any evidence`
  line `showing a tax liability of a person coming to his notice, with the previous permission of Additional`
  line `Commissioner or Joint Commissioner, proceed to assess the tax liability of such person to protect the`
  line `interest of revenue and issue an assessment order, if he has sufficient grounds to believe that any delay in`
  line `doing so may adversely affect the interest of revenue:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the taxable person to whom the liability pertains is not ascertainable and such`
  line `liability pertains to supply of goods, the person in charge of such goods shall be deemed to be the taxable`
  line `person liable to be assessed and liable to pay tax and any other amount due under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) On an application made by the taxable person within thirty days from the date of receipt of order`
  line `passed under sub-section (1) or on his own motion, if the Additional Commissioner or Joint`
  line `Commissioner considers that such order is erroneous, he may withdraw such order and follow the`
  line `procedure laid down in section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A].`
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (5180)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 71
  title `Audit by tax authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 133 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5180&sectionno=65&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commissioner or any officer authorised by him, by way of a`
  line `general or a specific order, may undertake audit of any registered person for such period, at such`
  line `frequency and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The officers referred to in sub-section (1) may conduct audit at the place of business of the`
  line `registered person or in their office.`
  line
  line `(3) The registered person shall be informed by way of a notice not less than fifteen working days`
  line `prior to the conduct of audit in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The audit under sub-section (1) shall be completed within a period of three months from the date`
  line `of commencement of the audit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner is satisfied that audit in respect of such registered person`
  line `cannot be completed within three months, he may, for the reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the`
  line `period by a further period not exceeding six months.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "commencement of audit" shall`
  line `mean the date on which the records and other documents, called for by the tax authorities, are made`
  line `available by the registered person or the actual institution of audit at the place of business, whichever is`
  line later.
  line
  line `(5) During the course of audit, the authorised officer may require the registered person,--`
  line
  line `(i) to afford him the necessary facility to verify the books of account or other documents as he`
  line `may require;`
  line
  line `(ii) to furnish such information as he may require and render assistance for timely completion of`
  line `the audit.`
  line
  line `(6) On conclusion of audit, the proper officer shall, within thirty days, inform the registered person,`
  line `whose records are audited, about the findings, his rights and obligations and the reasons for such findings.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the audit conducted under sub-section (1) results in detection of tax not paid or short paid`
  line `or erroneously refunded, or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised, the proper officer may initiate`
  line `action under section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A].`
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (5181)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 72
  title `Special audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 134 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5181&sectionno=66&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) If at any stage of scrutiny, inquiry, investigation or any other proceedings before`
  line `him, any officer not below the rank of Assistant Commissioner, having regard to the nature and complexity of`
  line `the case and the interest of revenue, is of the opinion that the value has not been correctly declared or the credit`
  line `availed is not within the normal limits, he may, with the prior approval of the Commissioner, direct such`
  line `registered person by a communication in writing to get his records including books of account examined and`
  line `audited by a chartered accountant or a cost accountant as may be nominated by the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The chartered accountant or cost accountant so nominated shall, within the period of ninety days,`
  line `submit a report of such audit duly signed and certified by him to the said Assistant Commissioner`
  line `mentioning therein such other particulars as may be specified:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Assistant Commissioner may, on an application made to him in this behalf by the`
  line `registered person or the chartered accountant or cost accountant or for any material and sufficient reason,`
  line `extend the said period by a further period of ninety days.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall have effect notwithstanding that the accounts of the`
  line `registered person have been audited under any other provisions of this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force.`
  line
  line `(4) The registered person shall be given an opportunity of being heard in respect of any material`
  line `gathered on the basis of special audit under sub-section (1) which is proposed to be used in any proceedings`
  line `against him under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(5) The expenses of the examination and audit of records under sub-section (1), including the`
  line `remuneration of such chartered accountant or cost accountant, shall be determined and paid by the`
  line `Commissioner and such determination shall be final.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the special audit conducted under sub-section (1) results in detection of tax not paid or`
  line `short paid or erroneously refunded, or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised, the proper officer may`
  line `initiate action under section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A].`
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (5182)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 73
  title `Power of inspection, search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5182&sectionno=67&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the proper officer, not below the rank of`
  line `Joint Commissioner, has reasons to believe that--`
  line
  line `(a) a taxable person has suppressed any transaction relating to supply of goods or services or both or`
  line `the stock of goods in hand, or has claimed input tax credit in excess of his entitlement under this Act or`
  line `has indulged in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder to evade`
  line `tax under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person engaged in the business of transporting goods or an owner or operator of a`
  line `warehouse or a godown or any other place is keeping goods which have escaped payment of tax or`
  line `has kept his accounts or goods in such a manner as is likely to cause evasion of tax payable under this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `he may authorise in writing any other officer of central tax to inspect any places of business of the taxable`
  line `person or the persons engaged in the business of transporting goods or the owner or the operator of`
  line `warehouse or godown or any other place.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the proper officer, not below the rank of Joint Commissioner, either pursuant to an inspection`
  line `carried out under sub-section (1) or otherwise, has reasons to believe that any goods liable to confiscation or`
  line `any documents or books or things, which in his opinion shall be useful for or relevant to any proceedings under`
  line `this Act, are secreted in any place, he may authorise in writing any other officer of central tax to search and`
  line `seize or may himself search and seize such goods, documents or books or things:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any such goods, the proper officer, or any officer`
  line `authorised by him, may serve on the owner or the custodian of the goods an order that he shall not`
  line `remove, part with, or otherwise deal with the goods except with the previous permission of such officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the documents or books or things so seized shall be retained by such officer only`
  line `for so long as may be necessary for their examination and for any inquiry or proceedings under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The documents, books or things referred to in sub-section (2) or any other documents, books or`
  line `things produced by a taxable person or any other person, which have not been relied upon for the issue of`
  line `notice under this Act or the rules made thereunder, shall be returned to such person within a period not`
  line `exceeding thirty days of the issue of the said notice.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer authorised under sub-section (2) shall have the power to seal or break open the door of any`
  line `premises or to break open any almirah, electronic devices, box, receptacle in which any goods, accounts,`
  line `registers or documents of the person are suspected to be concealed, where access to such premises, almirah,`
  line `electronic devices, box or receptacle is denied.`
  line
  line `(5) The person from whose custody any documents are seized under sub-section (2) shall be entitled to`
  line `make copies thereof or take extracts therefrom in the presence of an authorised officer at such place and`
  line `time as such officer may indicate in this behalf except where making such copies or taking such extracts`
  line `may, in the opinion of the proper officer, prejudicially affect the investigation.`
  line
  line `(6) The goods so seized under sub-section (2) shall be released, on a provisional basis, upon`
  line `execution of a bond and furnishing of a security, in such manner and of such quantum, respectively, as`
  line `may be prescribed or on payment of applicable tax, interest and penalty payable, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any goods are seized under sub-section (2) and no notice in respect thereof is given within`
  line `six months of the seizure of the goods, the goods shall be returned to the person from whose possession`
  line `they were seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line `proper officer for a further period not exceeding six months.`
  line
  line `(8) The Government may, having regard to the perishable or hazardous nature of any goods,`
  line `depreciation in the value of the goods with the passage of time, constraints of storage space for the goods`
  line `or any other relevant considerations, by notification, specify the goods or class of goods which shall, as`
  line `soon as may be after its seizure under sub-section (2), be disposed of by the proper officer in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any goods, being goods specified under sub-section (8), have been seized by a proper`
  line `officer, or any officer authorised by him under sub-section (2), he shall prepare an inventory of such`
  line `goods in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(10) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to search and seizure,`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to search and seizure under this section subject to the modification that subsection`
  line `(5) of section 165 of the said Code shall have effect as if for the word "Magistrate", wherever it`
  line `occurs, the word "Commissioner" were substituted.`
  line
  line `(11) Where the proper officer has reasons to believe that any person has evaded or is attempting to evade`
  line `the payment of any tax, he may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, seize the accounts, registers or`
  line `documents of such person produced before him and shall grant a receipt for the same, and shall retain the same`
  line `for so long as may be necessary in connection with any proceedings under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder for prosecution.`
  line
  line `(12) The Commissioner or an officer authorised by him may cause purchase of any goods or services`
  line `or both by any person authorised by him from the business premises of any taxable person, to check the`
  line `issue of tax invoices or bills of supply by such taxable person, and on return of goods so purchased by`
  line `such officer, such taxable person or any person in charge of the business premises shall refund the amount`
  line `so paid towards the goods after cancelling any tax invoice or bill of supply issued earlier.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (5183)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 74
  title `Inspection of goods in movement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5183&sectionno=68&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may require the person in charge of a`
  line `conveyance carrying any consignment of goods of value exceeding such amount as may be specified to`
  line `carry with him such documents and such devices as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The details of documents required to be carried under sub-section (1) shall be validated in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any conveyance referred to in sub-section (1) is intercepted by the proper officer at any`
  line `place, he may require the person in charge of the said conveyance to produce the documents prescribed`
  line `under the said sub-section and devices for verification, and the said person shall be liable to produce the`
  line `documents and devices and also allow the inspection of goods.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (5184)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 75
  title `Power to arrest.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5184&sectionno=69&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Commissioner has reasons to believe that a person has`
  line `committed any offence specified in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 132 which is punishable under clause (i) or (ii) of sub-section (1), or sub-section (2) of the said`
  line `section, he may, by order, authorise any officer of central tax to arrest such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person is arrested under sub-section (1) for an offence specified under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 132, the officer authorised to arrest the person shall inform such person of the grounds of arrest and`
  line `produce him before a Magistrate within twenty-four hours.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973(2 of 1974),---`
  line
  line `(a) where a person is arrested under sub-section (1) for any offence specified under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 132, he shall be admitted to bail or in default of bail, forwarded to the`
  line `custody of the Magistrate;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a non-cognizable and bailable offence, the Deputy Commissioner or the Assistant`
  line `Commissioner shall, for the purpose of releasing an arrested person on bail or otherwise, have the same`
  line `powers and be subject to the same provisions as an officer-in-charge of a police station.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (5185)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 76
  title `Power to summon persons to give evidence and produce documents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 135 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5185&sectionno=70&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `(1) The proper officer`
  line `under this Act shall have power to summon any person whose attendance he considers necessary either to`
  line `give evidence or to produce a document or any other thing in any inquiry in the same manner, as provided`
  line `in the case of a civil court under the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) All persons summoned under sub-section (1) shall be bound to attend, either in person or by an`
  line `authorised representative, as such officer may direct, and the person so appearing shall state the truth`
  line `during examination or make statements or produce such documents and other things as may be required.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every such inquiry referred to in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a "judicial proceedings"`
  line `within the meaning of section 193 and section 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (5186)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 77
  title `Access to business premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5186&sectionno=71&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any officer under this Act, authorised by the proper officer not`
  line `below the rank of Joint Commissioner, shall have access to any place of business of a registered person to`
  line `inspect books of account, documents, computers, computer programs, computer software whether installed in`
  line `a computer or otherwise and such other things as he may require and which may be available at such place,`
  line `for the purposes of carrying out any audit, scrutiny, verification and checks as may be necessary to safeguard`
  line `the interest of revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person in charge of place referred to in sub-section (1) shall, on demand, make available to`
  line `the officer authorised under sub-section (1) or the audit party deputed by the proper officer or a cost`
  line `accountant or chartered accountant nominated under section 66---`
  line
  line `(i) such records as prepared or maintained by the registered person and declared to the proper`
  line `officer in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(ii) trial balance or its equivalent;`
  line
  line `(iii) statements of annual financial accounts, duly audited, wherever required;`
  line
  line `(iv) cost audit report, if any, under section 148 of the Companies Act, 2013(18 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(v) the income-tax audit report, if any, under section 44AB of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961); and`
  line
  line `(vi) any other relevant record,`
  line
  line `for the scrutiny by the officer or audit party or the chartered accountant or cost accountant within a period`
  line `not exceeding fifteen working days from the day when such demand is made, or such further period as`
  line `may be allowed by the said officer or the audit party or the chartered accountant or cost accountant.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (5187)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 78
  title `Officers to assist proper officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5187&sectionno=72&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) All officers of Police, Railways, Customs, and those`
  line `officers engaged in the collection of land revenue, including village officers, officers of State tax and`
  line `officers of Union territory tax shall assist the proper officers in the implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Government may, by notification, empower and require any other class of officers to assist`
  line `the proper officers in the implementation of this Act when called upon to do so by the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (5188)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 79
  title `Determination of tax, pertaining to the period up to Financial Year 2023-24, not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised for any reason other than fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 136 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5188&sectionno=73&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `73. Determination of tax ^1[, pertaining to the period up to Financial Year 2023-24,] not paid or`
  line `short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised for any reason`
  line `other than fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts.--- (1) Where it appears to the proper officer that any tax has not been paid or short paid or`
  line `erroneously refunded, or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised for any reason, other`
  line `than the reason of fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax, he shall serve notice`
  line `on the person chargeable with tax which has not been so paid or which has been so short paid or to whom`
  line `the refund has erroneously been made, or who has wrongly availed or utilised input tax credit, requiring him`
  line `to show cause as to why he should not pay the amount specified in the notice along with interest payable`
  line `thereon under section 50 and a penalty leviable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer shall issue the notice under sub-section (1) at least three months prior to the`
  line `time limit specified in sub-section (10) for issuance of order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notice has been issued for any period under sub-section (1), the proper officer may serve`
  line `a statement, containing the details of tax not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit`
  line `wrongly availed or utilised for such periods other than those covered under sub-section (1), on the person`
  line `chargeable with tax.`
  line
  line `(4) The service of such statement shall be deemed to be service of notice on such person under`
  line `sub-section (1), subject to the condition that the grounds relied upon for such tax periods other than those`
  line `covered under sub-section (1) are the same as are mentioned in the earlier notice.`
  line
  line `(5) The person chargeable with tax may, before service of notice under sub-section (1) or, as the case`
  line `may be, the statement under sub-section (3), pay the amount of tax along with interest payable thereon`
  line `under section 50 on the basis of his own ascertainment of such tax or the tax as ascertained by the proper`
  line `officer and inform the proper officer in writing of such payment.`
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer, on receipt of such information, shall not serve any notice under sub-section (1)`
  line `or, as the case may be, the statement under sub-section (3), in respect of the tax so paid or any penalty`
  line `payable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the proper officer is of the opinion that the amount paid under sub-section (5) falls short of`
  line `the amount actually payable, he shall proceed to issue the notice as provided for in sub-section (1) in`
  line `respect of such amount which falls short of the amount actually payable.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any person chargeable with tax under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) pays the said tax`
  line `along with interest payable under section 50 within thirty days of issue of show cause notice, no penalty`
  line `shall be payable and all proceedings in respect of the said notice shall be deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `(9) The proper officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by person chargeable`
  line `with tax, determine the amount of tax, interest and a penalty equivalent to ten per cent. of tax or ten`
  line `thousand rupees, whichever is higher, due from such person and issue an order.`
  line
  line `(10) The proper officer shall issue the order under sub-section (9) within three years from the due date`
  line `for furnishing of annual return for the financial year to which the tax not paid or short paid or input tax`
  line `credit wrongly availed or utilised relates to or within three years from the date of erroneous refund.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (6) or sub-section (8), penalty under`
  line `sub-section (9) shall be payable where any amount of self-assessed tax or any amount collected as tax has`
  line `not been paid within a period of thirty days from the due date of payment of such tax.`
  line
  line `^1[(12) The provisions of this section shall be applicable for determination of tax pertaining to the`
  line `period up to Financial Year 2023-24.]`
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (5189)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 80
  title `Determination of tax, pertaining to the period up to Financial Year 2023-24, not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised by reason of fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5189&sectionno=74&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `74. Determination of tax ^1[, pertaining to the period up to Financial Year 2023-24,] not paid or`
  line `short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised by reason of fraud`
  line `or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts.--- (1) Where it appears to the proper officer that any tax has not been paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or`
  line `where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised by reason of fraud, or any wilful-misstatement or`
  line `suppression of facts to evade tax, he shall serve notice on the person chargeable with tax which has not been`
  line `so paid or which has been so short paid or to whom the refund has erroneously been made, or who has`
  line `wrongly availed or utilised input tax credit, requiring him to show cause as to why he should not pay the`
  line `amount specified in the notice along with interest payable thereon under section 50 and a penalty equivalent`
  line `to the tax specified in the notice.`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer shall issue the notice under sub-section (1) at least six months prior to the time`
  line `limit specified in sub-section (10) for issuance of order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notice has been issued for any period under sub-section (1), the proper officer may serve`
  line `a statement, containing the details of tax not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit`
  line `wrongly availed or utilised for such periods other than those covered under sub-section (1), on the person`
  line `chargeable with tax.`
  line
  line `(4) The service of statement under sub-section (3) shall be deemed to be service of notice under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 73, subject to the condition that the grounds relied upon in the said statement,`
  line `except the ground of fraud, or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax, for periods`
  line `other than those covered under sub-section (1) are the same as are mentioned in the earlier notice.`
  line
  line `(5) The person chargeable with tax may, before service of notice under sub-section (1), pay the`
  line `amount of tax along with interest payable under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to fifteen per cent. of`
  line `such tax on the basis of his own ascertainment of such tax or the tax as ascertained by the proper officer`
  line `and inform the proper officer in writing of such payment.`
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer, on receipt of such information, shall not serve any notice under`
  line `sub-section (1), in respect of the tax so paid or any penalty payable under the provisions of this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the proper officer is of the opinion that the amount paid under sub-section (5) falls short of`
  line `the amount actually payable, he shall proceed to issue the notice as provided for in sub-section (1) in`
  line `respect of such amount which falls short of the amount actually payable.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any person chargeable with tax under sub-section (1) pays the said tax along with interest`
  line `payable under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to twenty-five per cent. of such tax within thirty days`
  line `of issue of the notice, all proceedings in respect of the said notice shall be deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `(9) The proper officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by the person`
  line `chargeable with tax, determine the amount of tax, interest and penalty due from such person and issue an`
  line order.
  line
  line `(10) The proper officer shall issue the order under sub-section (9) within a period of five years from`
  line `the due date for furnishing of annual return for the financial year to which the tax not paid or short paid or`
  line `input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised relates to or within five years from the date of erroneous`
  line refund.
  line
  line `(11) Where any person served with an order issued under sub-section(9) pays the tax along with`
  line `interest payable thereon under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to fifty per cent. of such tax within`
  line `thirty days of communication of the order, all proceedings in respect of the said notice shall be deemed to`
  line `be concluded.`
  line
  line `^1[(12) The provisions of this section shall be applicable for determination of tax pertaining to the`
  line `period up to Financial Year 2023-24.]`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of section 73 and this section,---`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "all proceedings in respect of the said notice" shall not include proceedings`
  line `under section 132;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the notice under the same proceedings is issued to the main person liable to pay tax and`
  line `some other persons, and such proceedings against the main person have been concluded under section`
  line `73 or section 74, the proceedings against all the persons liable to pay penalty under ^2[sections 122 and`
  line `125] are deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 137 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 113, for "sections 122, 125, 129 and 130" (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Explanation 2 omitted by Act 15 of 2024, s. 137 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_74_a:
  sectionId (96647)
  sectionNo 74A
  orderNo 81
  title `Determination of tax not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised for any reason pertaining to Financial Year 2024-25 onward.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 138 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=96647&sectionno=74A&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_74_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[74A. Determination of tax not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit`
  line `wrongly availed or utilised for any reason pertaining to Financial Year 2024-25 onward.--- (1)`
  line `Where it appears to the proper officer that any tax has not been paid or short paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded, or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised, he shall serve notice on the`
  line `person chargeable with tax which has not been so paid or which has been so short paid or to whom the`
  line `refund has erroneously been made, or who has wrongly availed or utilised input tax credit, requiring him`
  line `to show cause as to why he should not pay the amount specified in the notice along with interest payable`
  line `thereon under section 50 and a penalty leviable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that no notice shall be issued, if the tax which has not been paid or short paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised in a financial year is less than one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) The proper officer shall issue the notice under sub-section (1) within forty-two months from the`
  line `due date for furnishing of annual return for the financial year to which the tax not paid or short paid or`
  line `input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised relates to or within forty-two months from the date of`
  line `erroneous refund.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a notice has been issued for any period under sub-section (1), the proper officer may serve`
  line `a statement, containing the details of tax not paid or short paid or erroneously refunded or input tax credit`
  line `wrongly availed or utilised for such periods other than those covered under sub-section (1), on the person`
  line `chargeable with tax.`
  line
  line `(4) The service of such statement shall be deemed to be service of notice on such person under`
  line `sub-section (1), subject to the condition that the grounds relied upon for such tax periods other than those`
  line `covered under sub-section (1) are the same as are mentioned in the earlier notice.`
  line
  line `(5) The penalty in case where any tax which has not been paid or short paid or erroneously refunded,`
  line `or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised,---`
  line
  line `(i) for any reason, other than the reason of fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of`
  line `facts to evade tax, shall be equivalent to ten per cent. of tax due from such person or ten thousand`
  line `rupees, whichever is higher;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the reason of fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax shall be`
  line `equivalent to the tax due from such person.`
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by the person`
  line `chargeable with tax, determine the amount of tax, interest and penalty due from such person and issue an`
  line order.
  line
  line `(7) The proper officer shall issue the order under sub-section (6) within twelve months from the date`
  line `of issuance of notice specified in sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that where the proper officer is not able to issue the order within the specified period, the`
  line `Commissioner, or an officer authorised by the Commissioner senior in rank to the proper officer but not`
  line `below the rank of Joint Commissioner of Central Tax, may, having regard to the reasons for delay in`
  line `issuance of the order under sub-section (6), to be recorded in writing, before the expiry of the specified`
  line `period, extend the said period further by a maximum of six months.`
  line
  line `(8) The person chargeable with tax where any tax has not been paid or short paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded, or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised for any reason, other than the`
  line `reason of fraud or any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax, may,---`
  line
  line `(i) before service of notice under sub-section (1), pay the amount of tax along with interest`
  line `payable under section 50 of such tax on the basis of his own ascertainment of such tax or the tax as`
  line `ascertained by the proper officer and inform the proper officer in writing of such payment, and the`
  line `proper officer, on receipt of such information shall not serve any notice under sub-section (1) or the`
  line `statement under sub-section (3), as the case may be, in respect of the tax so paid or any penalty`
  line `payable under the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(ii) pay the said tax along with interest payable under section 50 within sixty days of issue of`
  line `show cause notice, and on doing so, no penalty shall be payable and all proceedings in respect of the`
  line `said notice shall be deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `(9) The person chargeable with tax, where any tax has not been paid or short paid or erroneously`
  line `refunded or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised by reason of fraud, or any wilfulmisstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax, may,---`
  line
  line `(i) before service of notice under sub-section (1), pay the amount of tax along with interest`
  line `payable under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to fifteen per cent. of such tax on the basis of his`
  line `own ascertainment of such tax or the tax as ascertained by the proper officer and inform the proper`
  line `officer in writing of such payment, and the proper officer, on receipt of such information, shall not`
  line `serve any notice under sub-section (1), in respect of the tax so paid or any penalty payable under the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(ii) pay the said tax along with interest payable under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to`
  line `twenty-five per cent. of such tax within sixty days of issue of the notice, and on doing so, all`
  line `proceedings in respect of the said notice shall be deemed to be concluded;`
  line
  line `(iii) pay the tax along with interest payable thereon under section 50 and a penalty equivalent to`
  line `fifty per cent. of such tax within sixty days of communication of the order, and on doing so, all`
  line `proceedings in respect of the said notice shall be deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `(10) Where the proper officer is of the opinion that the amount paid under clause (i) of sub-section (8)`
  line `or clause (i) of sub-section (9) falls short of the amount actually payable, he shall proceed to issue the`
  line `notice as provided for in sub-section (1) in respect of such amount which falls short of the amount`
  line `actually payable.`
  line
  line `(11) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (i) or clause (ii) of sub-section (8), penalty under`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (5) shall be payable where any amount of self-assessed tax or any amount`
  line `collected as tax has not been paid within a period of thirty days from the due date of payment of such tax.`
  line
  line `(12) The provisions of this section shall be applicable for determination of tax pertaining to the`
  line `Financial Year 2024-25 onwards.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--- For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "all proceedings in respect of the said notice" shall not include proceedings`
  line `under section 132;`
  line
  line `(ii) where the notice under the same proceedings is issued to the main person liable to pay tax and`
  line `some other persons, and such proceedings against the main person have been concluded under this`
  line `section, the proceedings against all the persons liable to pay penalty under sections 122 and 125 are`
  line `deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of this Act, the expression "suppression" shall mean nondeclaration of facts or information which a taxable person is required to declare in the return, statement,`
  line `report or any other document furnished under this Act or the rules made thereunder, or failure to furnish`
  line `any information on being asked for, in writing, by the proper officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (5190)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 82
  title `General provisions relating to determination of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5190&sectionno=75&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the service of notice or`
  line `issuance of order is stayed by an order of a court or Appellate Tribunal, the period of such stay shall be`
  line `excluded in computing the period specified in sub-sections (2) and (10) of section 73 or sub-sections (2)`
  line `and(10) of section 74 ^1[or sub-sections (2) and (7) of section 74A], as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court concludes that the notice issued`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 74 is not sustainable for the reason that the charges of fraud or any`
  line `willful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax has not been established against the person to`
  line `whom the notice was issued, the proper officer shall determine the tax payable by such person, deeming`
  line `as if the notice were issued under sub-section (1) of section 73.`
  line
  line `^1[(2A) Where any Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court concludes that the penalty under`
  line `clause (ii) of sub-section (5) of section 74A is not sustainable for the reason that the charges of fraud or`
  line `any wilful-misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax has not been established against the person to`
  line `whom the notice was issued, the penalty shall be payable by such person, under clause (i) of sub-section`
  line `(5) of section 74A.]`
  line
  line `(3) Where any order is required to be issued in pursuance of the direction of the Appellate Authority`
  line `or Appellate Tribunal or a court, such order shall be issued within two years from the date of`
  line `communication of the said direction.`
  line
  line `(4) An opportunity of hearing shall be granted where a request is received in writing from the person`
  line `chargeable with tax or penalty, or where any adverse decision is contemplated against such person.`
  line
  line `(5) The proper officer shall, if sufficient cause is shown by the person chargeable with tax, grant time`
  line `to the said person and adjourn the hearing for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted for more than three times to a person during the`
  line proceedings.
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer, in his order, shall set out the relevant facts and the basis of his decision.`
  line
  line `(7) The amount of tax, interest and penalty demanded in the order shall not be in excess of the amount`
  line `specified in the notice and no demand shall be confirmed on the grounds other than the grounds specified`
  line `in the notice.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court modifies the amount of tax`
  line `determined by the proper officer, the amount of interest and penalty shall stand modified accordingly,`
  line `taking into account the amount of tax so modified.`
  line
  line `(9) The interest on the tax short paid or not paid shall be payable whether or not specified in the order`
  line `determining the tax liability.`
  line
  line `^1[(10) The adjudication proceedings shall be deemed to be concluded, if the order is not issued within`
  line `the period specified in sub-section (10) of section 73 or in sub-section (10) of section 74 or in`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 74A;]`
  line
  line `(11) An issue on which the Appellate Authority or the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court has given`
  line `its decision which is prejudicial to the interest of revenue in some other proceedings and an appeal to the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal or the High Court or the Supreme Court against such decision of the Appellate Authority`
  line `or the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court is pending, the period spent between the date of the decision of`
  line `the Appellate Authority and that of the Appellate Tribunal or the date of decision of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal and that of the High Court or the date of the decision of the High Court and that of the Supreme`
  line `Court shall be excluded in computing the period referred to in sub-section (10) of section 73 or`
  line `sub-section (10) of section 74 ^1[or sub-section (7) of section 74A] where proceedings are initiated by way of issue of a show cause notice`
  line `under the said sections.`
  line
  line `(12) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A], where any amount of self-assessed`
  line `tax in accordance with a return furnished under section 39 remains unpaid, either wholly or partly, or any`
  line `amount of interest payable on such tax remains unpaid, the same shall be recovered under the provisions of`
  line `section 79.`
  line
  line `^2[Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "self-assessed tax" shall include`
  line `the tax payable in respect of details of outward supplies furnished under section 37, but not included in`
  line `the return furnished under section 39.]`
  line
  line `(13) Where any penalty is imposed under section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A], no penalty for the same act or`
  line `omission shall be imposed on the same person under any other provision of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 139 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (5191)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 83
  title `Tax collected but not paid to Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5191&sectionno=76&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained in any order or direction of any Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or court or in any`
  line `other provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or any other law for the time being in force,`
  line `every person who has collected from any other person any amount as representing the tax under this Act,`
  line `and has not paid the said amount to the Government, shall forthwith pay the said amount to the`
  line `Government, irrespective of whether the supplies in respect of which such amount was collected are`
  line `taxable or not.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any amount is required to be paid to the Government under sub-section (1), and which has`
  line `not been so paid, the proper officer may serve on the person liable to pay such amount a notice requiring`
  line `him to show cause as to why the said amount as specified in the notice, should not be paid by him to the`
  line `Government and why a penalty equivalent to the amount specified in the notice should not be imposed on`
  line `him under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The proper officer shall, after considering the representation, if any, made by the person on whom`
  line `the notice is served under sub-section (2), determine the amount due from such person and thereupon`
  line `such person shall pay the amount so determined.`
  line
  line `(4) The person referred to in sub-section (1) shall in addition to paying the amount referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) also be liable to pay interest thereon at the rate specified under section`
  line `50 from the date such amount was collected by him to the date such amount is paid by him to the`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(5) An opportunity of hearing shall be granted where a request is received in writing from the person`
  line `to whom the notice was issued to show cause.`
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer shall issue an order within one year from the date of issue of the notice.`
  line
  line `(7) Where the issuance of order is stayed by an order of the court or Appellate Tribunal, the period of`
  line `such stay shall be excluded in computing the period of one year.`
  line
  line `(8) The proper officer, in his order, shall set out the relevant facts and the basis of his decision.`
  line
  line `(9) The amount paid to the Government under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) shall be adjusted`
  line `against the tax payable, if any, by the person in relation to the supplies referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(10) Where any surplus is left after the adjustment under sub-section (9), the amount of such surplus`
  line `shall either be credited to the Fund or refunded to the person who has borne the incidence of such amount.`
  line
  line `(11) The person who has borne the incidence of the amount, may apply for the refund of the same in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of section 54.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (5192)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 84
  title `Tax wrongfully collected and paid to Central Government or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5192&sectionno=77&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered person who has paid the Central tax and State tax or, as the case may be, the central tax and the`
  line `Union territory tax on a transaction considered by him to be an intra-State supply, but which is`
  line `subsequently held to be an inter-State supply, shall be refunded the amount of taxes so paid in such`
  line `manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person who has paid integrated tax on a transaction considered by him to be an`
  line `inter-State supply, but which is subsequently held to be an intra-State supply, shall not be required to pay`
  line `any interest on the amount of central tax and State tax or, as the case may be, the Central tax and the`
  line `Union territory tax payable.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (5193)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 85
  title `Initiation of recovery proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5193&sectionno=78&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `Any amount payable by a taxable person in pursuance of`
  line `an order passed under this Act shall be paid by such person within a period of three months from the date`
  line `of service of such order failing which recovery proceedings shall be initiated:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the proper officer considers it expedient in the interest of revenue, he may, for`
  line `reasons to be recorded in writing, require the said taxable person to make such payment within such period less`
  line `than a period of three months as may be specified by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (5194)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 86
  title `Recovery of tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5194&sectionno=79&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any amount payable by a person to the Government under any of`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder is not paid, the proper officer shall proceed to`
  line `recover the amount by one or more of the following modes, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the proper officer may deduct or may require any other specified officer to deduct the amount`
  line `so payable from any money owing to such person which may be under the control of the proper`
  line `officer or such other specified officer;`
  line
  line `(b) the proper officer may recover or may require any other specified officer to recover the amount so`
  line `payable by detaining and selling any goods belonging to such person which are under the control of the`
  line `proper officer or such other specified officer;`
  line
  line `(c) (i) the proper officer may, by a notice in writing, require any other person from whom money is`
  line `due or may become due to such person or who holds or may subsequently hold money for or on account`
  line `of such person, to pay to the Government either forthwith upon the money becoming due or being held, or`
  line `within the time specified in the notice not being before the money becomes due or is held, so much of the`
  line `money as is sufficient to pay the amount due from such person or the whole of the money when it is equal`
  line `to or less than that amount;`
  line
  line `(ii) every person to whom the notice is issued under sub-clause (i) shall be bound to comply with`
  line `such notice, and in particular, where any such notice is issued to a post office, banking company or an`
  line `insurer, it shall not be necessary to produce any pass book, deposit receipt, policy or any other`
  line `document for the purpose of any entry, endorsement or the like being made before payment is made,`
  line `notwithstanding any rule, practice or requirement to the contrary;`
  line
  line `(iii) in case the person to whom a notice under sub-clause (i) has been issued, fails to make the`
  line `payment in pursuance thereof to the Government, he shall be deemed to be a defaulter in respect of`
  line `the amount specified in the notice and all the consequences of this Act or the rules made thereunder`
  line `shall follow;`
  line
  line `(iv) the officer issuing a notice under sub-clause (i) may, at any time, amend or revoke such`
  line `notice or extend the time for making any payment in pursuance of the notice;`
  line
  line `(v) any person making any payment in compliance with a notice issued under sub-clause (i) shall be`
  line `deemed to have made the payment under the authority of the person in default and such payment being`
  line `credited to the Government shall be deemed to constitute a good and sufficient discharge of the liability`
  line `of such person to the person in default to the extent of the amount specified in the receipt;`
  line
  line `(vi) any person discharging any liability to the person in default after service on him of the notice`
  line `issued under sub-clause (i) shall be personally liable to the Government to the extent of the liability`
  line `discharged or to the extent of the liability of the person in default for tax, interest and penalty, whichever is`
  line less;
  line
  line `(vii) where a person on whom a notice is served under sub-clause (i) proves to the satisfaction of`
  line `the officer issuing the notice that the money demanded or any part thereof was not due to the person`
  line `in default or that he did not hold any money for or on account of the person in default, at the time the`
  line `notice was served on him, nor is the money demanded or any part thereof, likely to become due to the`
  line `said person or be held for or on account of such person, nothing contained in this section shall be`
  line `deemed to require the person on whom the notice has been served to pay to the Government any such`
  line `money or part thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) the proper officer may, in accordance with the rules to be made in this behalf, distrain any`
  line `movable or immovable property belonging to or under the control of such person, and detain the same`
  line `until the amount payable is paid; and in case, any part of the said amount payable or of the cost of the`
  line `distress or keeping of the property, remains unpaid for a period of thirty days next after any such distress,`
  line `may cause the said property to be sold and with the proceeds of such sale, may satisfy the amount payable`
  line `and the costs including cost of sale remaining unpaid and shall render the surplus amount, if any, to such`
  line person;
  line
  line `(e) the proper officer may prepare a certificate signed by him specifying the amount due from`
  line `such person and send it to the Collector of the district in which such person owns any property or`
  line `resides or carries on his business or to any officer authorised by the Government and the said`
  line `Collector or the said officer, on receipt of such certificate, shall proceed to recover from such person`
  line `the amount specified thereunder as if it were an arrear of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(f) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `proper officer may file an application to the appropriate Magistrate and such Magistrate shall proceed`
  line `to recover from such person the amount specified thereunder as if it were a fine imposed by him.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the terms of any bond or other instrument executed under this Act or any rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder provide that any amount due under such instrument may be recovered in the`
  line `manner laid down in sub-section (1), the amount may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery,`
  line `be recovered in accordance with the provisions of that sub-section.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any amount of tax, interest or penalty is payable by a person to the Government under any`
  line `of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder and which remains unpaid, the proper officer of`
  line `State tax or Union territory tax, during the course of recovery of said tax arrears, may recover the amount`
  line `from the said person as if it were an arrear of State tax or Union territory tax and credit the amount so`
  line `recovered to the account of the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the amount recovered under sub-section (3) is less than the amount due to the Central`
  line `Government and State Government, the amount to be credited to the account of the respective`
  line `Governments shall be in proportion to the amount due to each such Government.`
  line
  line `^1[Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the word person shall include "distinct persons" as referred to in sub-section (4) or, as the case may be, sub-section (5) of section 25.]`
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (5195)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 87
  title `Payment of tax and other amount in instalments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5195&sectionno=80&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `On an application filed by a taxable person,`
  line `the Commissioner may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the time for payment or allow payment of`
  line `any amount due under this Act, other than the amount due as per the liability self-assessed in any return, by such person in monthly instalments not exceeding twenty four, subject to payment of interest under section 50`
  line `and subject to such conditions and limitations as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where there is default in payment of any one instalment on its due date, the whole`
  line `outstanding balance payable on such date shall become due and payable forthwith and shall, without any`
  line `further notice being served on the person, be liable for recovery.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (5196)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 88
  title `Transfer of property to be void in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5196&sectionno=81&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `Where a person, after any amount has`
  line `become due from him, creates a charge on or parts with the property belonging to him or in his possession`
  line `by way of sale, mortgage, exchange, or any other mode of transfer whatsoever of any of his properties in`
  line `favour of any other person with the intention of defrauding the Government revenue, such charge or`
  line `transfer shall be void as against any claim in respect of any tax or any other sum payable by the said`
  line `person:`
  line
  line `Provided that, such charge or transfer shall not be void if it is made for adequate consideration, in`
  line `good faith and without notice of the pendency of such proceedings under this Act or without notice of`
  line `such tax or other sum payable by the said person, or with the previous permission of the proper officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (5197)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 89
  title `Tax to be first charge on property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5197&sectionno=82&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force, save as otherwise provided in the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016`
  line `(31 of 2016), any amount payable by a taxable person or any other person on account of tax, interest or`
  line `penalty which he is liable to pay to the Government shall be a first charge on the property of such taxable`
  line `person or such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (5198)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 90
  title `Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 115, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5198&sectionno=83&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where, after the initiation`
  line `of any proceeding under Chapter XII, Chapter XIV or Chapter XV, the Commissioner is of the opinion`
  line `that for the purpose of protecting the interest of the Government revenue it is necessary so to do, he may,`
  line `by order in writing, attach provisionally, any property, including bank account, belonging to the taxable`
  line `person or any person specified in sub-section (1A) of section 122, in such manner as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every such provisional attachment shall cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of one`
  line `year from the date of the order made under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (5199)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 91
  title `Continuation and validation of certain recovery proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5199&sectionno=84&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `Where any notice of demand in`
  line `respect of any tax, penalty, interest or any other amount payable under this Act, (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as "Government dues"), is served upon any taxable person or any other person and any appeal or`
  line `revision application is filed or any other proceedings is initiated in respect of such Government dues, then---`
  line
  line `(a) where such Government dues are enhanced in such appeal, revision or other proceedings, the`
  line `Commissioner shall serve upon the taxable person or any other person another notice of demand in`
  line `respect of the amount by which such Government dues are enhanced and any recovery proceedings in`
  line `relation to such Government dues as are covered by the notice of demand served upon him before the`
  line `disposal of such appeal, revision or other proceedings may, without the service of any fresh notice of`
  line `demand, be continued from the stage at which such proceedings stood immediately before such`
  line disposal;
  line
  line `(b) where such Government dues are reduced in such appeal, revision or in other proceedings--`
  line
  line `(i) it shall not be necessary for the Commissioner to serve upon the taxable person a fresh`
  line `notice of demand;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Commissioner shall give intimation of such reduction to him and to the appropriate`
  line `authority with whom recovery proceedings is pending;`
  line
  line `(iii) any recovery proceedings initiated on the basis of the demand served upon him prior to the`
  line `disposal of such appeal, revision or other proceedings may be continued in relation to the amount so`
  line `reduced from the stage at which such proceedings stood immediately before such disposal.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (5200)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 92
  title `Liability in case of transfer of business.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5200&sectionno=85&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a taxable person, liable to pay tax under`
  line `this Act, transfers his business in whole or in part, by sale, gift, lease, leave and license, hire or in any other`
  line `manner whatsoever, the taxable person and the person to whom the business is so transferred shall, jointly`
  line `and severally, be liable wholly or to the extent of such transfer, to pay the tax, interest or any penalty due`
  line `from the taxable person up to the time of such transfer, whether such tax, interest or penalty has been`
  line `determined before such transfer, but has remained unpaid or is determined thereafter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the transferee of a business referred to in sub-section (1) carries on such business either`
  line `in his own name or in some other name, he shall be liable to pay tax on the supply of goods or services or`
  line `both effected by him with effect from the date of such transfer and shall, if he is a registered person under`
  line `this Act, apply within the prescribed time for amendment of his certificate of registration.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (5201)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 93
  title `Liability of agent and principal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5201&sectionno=86&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `Where an agent supplies or receives any taxable goods on`
  line `behalf of his principal, such agent and his principal shall, jointly and severally, be liable to pay the tax`
  line `payable on such goods under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (5202)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 94
  title `Liability in case of amalgamation or merger of companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5202&sectionno=87&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) When two or more companies`
  line `are amalgamated or merged in pursuance of an order of court or of Tribunal or otherwise and the order is to`
  line `take effect from a date earlier to the date of the order and any two or more of such companies have supplied`
  line `or received any goods or services or both to or from each other during the period commencing on the date`
  line `from which the order takes effect till the date of the order, then such transactions of supply and receipt shall`
  line `be included in the turnover of supply or receipt of the respective companies and they shall be liable to pay`
  line `tax accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the said order, for the purposes of this Act, the said two or`
  line `more companies shall be treated as distinct companies for the period up to the date of the said order and`
  line `the registration certificates of the said companies shall be cancelled with effect from the date of the said`
  line order.
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (5203)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 95
  title `Liability in case of company in liquidation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5203&sectionno=88&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) When any company is being wound up`
  line `whether under the orders of a court or Tribunal or otherwise, every person appointed as receiver of any`
  line `assets of a company (hereafter in this section referred to as the "liquidator"), shall, within thirty days after`
  line `his appointment, give intimation of his appointment to the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner shall, after making such inquiry or calling for such information as he may deem`
  line `fit, notify the liquidator within three months from the date on which he receives intimation of the appointment`
  line `of the liquidator, the amount which in the opinion of the Commissioner would be sufficient to provide for any`
  line `tax, interest or penalty which is then, or is likely thereafter to become, payable by the company.`
  line
  line `(3) When any private company is wound up and any tax, interest or penalty determined under this Act on`
  line `the company for any period, whether before or in the course of or after its liquidation, cannot be recovered,`
  line `then every person who was a director of such company at any time during the period for which the tax was due`
  line `shall, jointly and severally, be liable for the payment of such tax, interest or penalty, unless he proves to the`
  line `satisfaction of the Commissioner that such non-recovery cannot be attributed to any gross neglect, misfeasance`
  line `or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the company.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (5204)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 96
  title `Liability of directors of private company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5204&sectionno=89&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the`
  line `Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013), where any tax, interest or penalty due from a private company in respect`
  line `of any supply of goods or services or both for any period cannot be recovered, then, every person who was a`
  line `director of the private company during such period shall, jointly and severally, be liable for the payment of`
  line `such tax, interest or penalty unless he proves that the non-recovery cannot be attributed to any gross`
  line `neglect, misfeasance or breach of duty on his part in relation to the affairs of the company.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a private company is converted into a public company and the tax, interest or penalty in`
  line `respect of any supply of goods or services or both for any period during which such company was a private company cannot be recovered before such conversion, then, nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall apply`
  line `to any person who was a director of such private company in relation to any tax, interest or penalty in respect`
  line `of such supply of goods or services or both of such private company:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall apply to any personal penalty imposed on`
  line `such director.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (5205)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 97
  title `Liability of partners of firm to pay tax.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5205&sectionno=90&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any contract to the contrary and any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, where any firm is liable to pay any tax, interest or penalty under this`
  line `Act, the firm and each of the partners of the firm shall, jointly and severally, be liable for such payment:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any partner retires from the firm, he or the firm, shall intimate the date of`
  line `retirement of the said partner to the Commissioner by a notice in that behalf in writing and such partner`
  line `shall be liable to pay tax, interest or penalty due up to the date of his retirement whether determined or`
  line `not, on that date:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if no such intimation is given within one month from the date of retirement, the`
  line `liability of such partner under the first proviso shall continue until the date on which such intimation is`
  line `received by the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (5206)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 98
  title `Liability of guardians, trustees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5206&sectionno=91&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `Where the business in respect of which any tax, interest or`
  line `penalty is payable under this Act is carried on by any guardian, trustee or agent of a minor or other`
  line `incapacitated person on behalf of and for the benefit of such minor or other incapacitated person, the tax,`
  line `interest or penalty shall be levied upon and recoverable from such guardian, trustee or agent in like manner`
  line `and to the same extent as it would be determined and recoverable from any such minor or other incapacitated`
  line `person, as if he were a major or capacitated person and as if he were conducting the business himself, and all`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (5207)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 99
  title `Liability of Court of Wards, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5207&sectionno=92&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Where the estate or any portion of the estate of a taxable person`
  line `owning a business in respect of which any tax, interest or penalty is payable under this Act is under the control`
  line `of the Court of Wards, the Administrator General, the Official Trustee or any receiver or manager (including`
  line `any person, whatever be his designation, who in fact manages the business) appointed by or under any order of`
  line `a court, the tax, interest or penalty shall be levied upon and be recoverable from such Court of Wards,`
  line `Administrator General, Official Trustee, receiver or manager in like manner and to the same extent as it would`
  line `be determined and be recoverable from the taxable person as if he were conducting the business himself, and`
  line `all the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (5208)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 100
  title `Special provisions regarding liability to pay tax, interest or penalty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5208&sectionno=93&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016),`
  line `where a person, liable to pay tax, interest or penalty under this Act, dies, then---`
  line
  line `(a) if a business carried on by the person is continued after his death by his legal representative or any other person, such legal representative or other person, shall be liable to pay tax, interest or penalty due from such person under this Act; and`
  line
  line `(b) if the business carried on by the person is discontinued, whether before or after his death, his`
  line `legal representative shall be liable to pay, out of the estate of the deceased, to the extent to which the`
  line `estate is capable of meeting the charge, the tax, interest or penalty due from such person under this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `whether such tax, interest or penalty has been determined before his death but has remained unpaid or is`
  line `determined after his death.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), where a`
  line `taxable person, liable to pay tax, interest or penalty under this Act, is a Hindu Undivided Family or an`
  line `association of persons and the property of the Hindu Undivided Family or the association of persons is`
  line `partitioned amongst the various members or groups of members, then, each member or group of members`
  line `shall, jointly and severally, be liable to pay the tax, interest or penalty due from the taxable person under this`
  line `Act up to the time of the partition whether such tax, penalty or interest has been determined before partition`
  line `but has remained unpaid or is determined after the partition.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise provided in the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), where a`
  line `taxable person, liable to pay tax, interest or penalty under this Act, is a firm, and the firm is dissolved, then,`
  line `every person who was a partner shall, jointly and severally, be liable to pay the tax, interest or penalty due`
  line `from the firm under this Act up to the time of dissolution whether such tax, interest or penalty has been`
  line `determined before the dissolution, but has remained unpaid or is determined after dissolution.`
  line
  line `(4) Save as otherwise provided in the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code, 2016 (31 of 2016), where a`
  line `taxable person liable to pay tax, interest or penalty under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) is the guardian of a ward on whose behalf the business is carried on by the guardian; or`
  line
  line `(b) is a trustee who carries on the business under a trust for a beneficiary,`
  line
  line `then, if the guardianship or trust is terminated, the ward or the beneficiary shall be liable to pay the tax,`
  line `interest or penalty due from the taxable person upto the time of the termination of the guardianship or`
  line `trust, whether such tax, interest or penalty has been determined before the termination of guardianship or`
  line `trust but has remained unpaid or is determined thereafter.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (5209)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 101
  title `Liability in other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5209&sectionno=94&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a taxable person is a firm or an association of persons or a`
  line `Hindu Undivided Family and such firm, association or family has discontinued business---`
  line
  line `(a) the tax, interest or penalty payable under this Act by such firm, association or family up to the`
  line `date of such discontinuance may be determined as if no such discontinuance had taken place; and`
  line
  line `(b) every person who, at the time of such discontinuance, was a partner of such firm, or a member`
  line `of such association or family, shall, notwithstanding such discontinuance, jointly and severally, be`
  line `liable for the payment of tax and interest determined and penalty imposed and payable by such firm,`
  line `association or family, whether such tax and interest has been determined or penalty imposed prior to`
  line `or after such discontinuance and subject as aforesaid, the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply as if every such person or partner or member were himself a taxable person.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a change has occurred in the constitution of a firm or an association of persons, the`
  line `partners of the firm or members of association, as it existed before and as it exists after the reconstitution,`
  line `shall, without prejudice to the provisions of section 90, jointly and severally, be liable to pay tax, interest`
  line `or penalty due from such firm or association for any period before its reconstitution.`
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall, so far as may be, apply where the taxable person, being a firm`
  line `or association of persons is dissolved or where the taxable person, being a Hindu Undivided Family, has`
  line `effected partition with respect to the business carried on by it and accordingly references in that sub-section to`
  line `discontinuance shall be construed as reference to dissolution or to partition.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this Chapter,---`
  line
  line `(i) a "Limited Liability Partnership" formed and registered under the provisions of the Limited`
  line `Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009) shall also be considered as a firm;`
  line
  line `(ii) "court" means the District Court, High Court or Supreme Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (5210)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 102
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 104 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5210&sectionno=95&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "advance ruling" means a decision provided by the Authority or the Appellate Authority ^1[or the`
  line `National Appellate Authority] to an applicant on matters or on questions specified in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 97 or sub-section (1) of section 100 ^1[or of section 101C], in relation to the supply of goods or`
  line `services or both being undertaken or proposed to be undertaken by the applicant;`
  line
  line `(b) "Appellate Authority" means the Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling referred to in`
  line `section 99;`
  line
  line `(c) "applicant" means any person registered or desirous of obtaining registration under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "application" means an application made to the Authority under sub-section (1) of section 97;`
  line
  line `(e) "Authority" means the Authority for Advance Ruling referred to in section 96.`
  line
  line `^1[(f) "National Appellate Authority" means the National Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling`
  line `referred to in section 101A.]`
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (5211)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 103
  title `Authority for advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5211&sectionno=96&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, for the purposes of this`
  line `Act, the Authority for advance ruling constituted under the provisions of a State Goods and Services Tax Act`
  line `or Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act shall be deemed to be the Authority for advance ruling in`
  line `respect of that State or Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (5212)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 104
  title `Application for advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5212&sectionno=97&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) An applicant desirous of obtaining an advance ruling`
  line `under this Chapter may make an application in such form and manner and accompanied by such fee as`
  line `may be prescribed, stating the question on which the advance ruling is sought.`
  line
  line `(2) The question on which the advance ruling is sought under this Act, shall be in respect of,--`
  line
  line `(a) classification of any goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(b) applicability of a notification issued under the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) determination of time and value of supply of goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(d) admissibility of input tax credit of tax paid or deemed to have been paid;`
  line
  line `(e) determination of the liability to pay tax on any goods or services or both;`
  line
  line `(f) whether applicant is required to be registered;`
  line
  line `(g) whether any particular thing done by the applicant with respect to any goods or services or`
  line `both amounts to or results in a supply of goods or services or both, within the meaning of that term.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (5213)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 105
  title `Procedure on receipt of application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5213&sectionno=98&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of an application, the Authority shall cause`
  line `a copy thereof to be forwarded to the concerned officer and, if necessary, call upon him to furnish the`
  line `relevant records:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any records have been called for by the Authority in any case, such records shall,`
  line `as soon as possible, be returned to the said concerned officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority may, after examining the application and the records called for and after hearing`
  line `the applicant or his authorised representative and the concerned officer or his authorised representative,`
  line `by order, either admit or reject the application:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Authority shall not admit the application where the question raised in the`
  line `application is already pending or decided in any proceedings in the case of an applicant under any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no application shall be rejected under this sub-section unless an opportunity of`
  line `hearing has been given to the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the application is rejected, the reasons for such rejection shall be specified`
  line `in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) A copy of every order made under sub-section (2) shall be sent to the applicant and to the`
  line `concerned officer.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an application is admitted under sub-section (2), the Authority shall, after examining such`
  line `further material as may be placed before it by the applicant or obtained by the Authority and after providing`
  line `an opportunity of being heard to the applicant or his authorised representative as well as to the concerned`
  line `officer or his authorised representative, pronounce its advance ruling on the question specified in the`
  line application.
  line
  line `(5) Where the members of the Authority differ on any question on which the advance ruling is sought,`
  line `they shall state the point or points on which they differ and make a reference to the Appellate Authority`
  line `for hearing and decision on such question.`
  line
  line `(6) The Authority shall pronounce its advance ruling in writing within ninety days from the date of`
  line `receipt of application.`
  line
  line `(7) A copy of the advance ruling pronounced by the Authority duly signed by the members and`
  line `certified in such manner as may be prescribed shall be sent to the applicant, the concerned officer and the`
  line `jurisdictional officer after such pronouncement.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (5214)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 106
  title `Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5214&sectionno=99&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Chapter, for the`
  line `purposes of this Act, the Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling constituted under the provisions of a State`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act or a Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act shall be deemed to be the`
  line `Appellate Authority in respect of that State or Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (5215)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 107
  title `Appeal to Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5215&sectionno=100&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) The concerned officer, the jurisdictional officer or an`
  line `applicant aggrieved by any advance ruling pronounced under sub-section (4) of section 98, may appeal to`
  line `the Appellate Authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be filed within a period of thirty days from the date on which`
  line `the ruling sought to be appealed against is communicated to the concerned officer, the jurisdictional`
  line `officer and the applicant:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Appellate Authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by a`
  line `sufficient cause from presenting the appeal within the said period of thirty days, allow it to be presented`
  line `within a further period not exceeding thirty days.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be in such form, accompanied by such fee and verified in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (5216)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 108
  title `Orders of Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5216&sectionno=101&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Authority may, after giving the parties to`
  line `the appeal or reference an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as it thinks fit, confirming or`
  line `modifying the ruling appealed against or referred to.`
  line
  line `(2) The order referred to in sub-section (1) shall be passed within a period of ninety days from the`
  line `date of filing of the appeal under section 100 or a reference under sub-section (5) of section 98.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the members of the Appellate Authority differ on any point or points referred to in appeal`
  line `or reference, it shall be deemed that no advance ruling can be issued in respect of the question under the`
  line `appeal or reference.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the advance ruling pronounced by the Appellate Authority duly signed by the Members`
  line `and certified in such manner as may be prescribed shall be sent to the applicant, the concerned officer, the`
  line `jurisdictional officer and to the Authority after such pronouncement.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101_a:
  sectionId (51463)
  sectionNo 101A
  orderNo 109
  title `Constitution of National Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 105 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=51463&sectionno=101A&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_101_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[101A. Constitution of National Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling.--- (1) The Government`
  line `shall, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification, constitute, with effect from such date as`
  line `may be specified therein, an Authority known as the National Appellate Authority for Advance Ruling for`
  line `hearing appeals made under section 101B.`
  line
  line `(2) The National Appellate Authority shall consist of---`
  line
  line `(i) the President, who has been a Judge of the Supreme Court or is or has been the Chief Justice`
  line `of a High Court, or is or has been a Judge of a High Court for a period not less than five years;`
  line
  line `(ii) a Technical Member (Centre) who is or has been a member of Indian Revenue (Customs and`
  line `Central Excise) Service, Group A, and has completed at least fifteen years of service in Group A;`
  line
  line `(iii) a Technical Member (State) who is or has been an officer of the State Government not below`
  line `the rank of Additional Commissioner of Value Added Tax or the Additional Commissioner of State`
  line `tax with at least three years of experience in the administration of an existing law or the State Goods`
  line `and Services Tax Act or in the field of finance and taxation.`
  line
  line `(3) The President of the National Appellate Authority shall be appointed by the Government after`
  line `consultation with the Chief Justice of India or his nominee:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the President by the`
  line `reason of his death, resignation or otherwise, the senior most Member of the National Appellate Authority`
  line `shall act as the President until the date on which a new President, appointed in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the President is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness`
  line `or any other cause, the senior most Member of the National Appellate Authority shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the President until the date on which the President resumes his duties.`
  line
  line `(4) The Technical Member (Centre) and Technical Member (State) of the National Appellate`
  line `Authority shall be appointed by the Government on the recommendations of a Selection Committee`
  line `consisting of such persons and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) No appointment of the Members of the National Appellate Authority shall be invalid merely by`
  line `the reason of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(6) Before appointing any person as the President or Members of the National Appellate Authority,`
  line `the Government shall satisfy itself that such person does not have any financial or other interests which`
  line `are likely to prejudicially affect his functions as such President or Member.`
  line
  line `(7) The salary, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the President and the`
  line `Members of the National Appellate Authority shall be such as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither salary and allowances nor other terms and conditions of service of the President`
  line `or Members of the National Appellate Authority shall be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(8) The President of the National Appellate Authority shall hold office for a term of three years from`
  line `the date on which he enters upon his office, or until he attains the age of seventy years, whichever is`
  line `earlier and shall also be eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(9) The Technical Member (Centre) or Technical Member (State) of the National Appellate Authority`
  line `shall hold office for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office, or until he`
  line `attains the age of sixty-five years, whichever is earlier and shall also be eligible for reappointment.`
  line
  line `(10) The President or any Member may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Government, resign from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or Member shall continue to hold office until the expiry of three months`
  line `from the date of receipt of such notice by the Government, or until a person duly appointed as his`
  line `successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `(11) The Government may, after consultation with the Chief Justice of India, remove from the office`
  line `such President or Member, who---`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of such Government involves moral`
  line `turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as such President or Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `such President or Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or the Member shall not be removed on any of the grounds specified in`
  line `clauses (d) and (e), unless he has been informed of the charges against him and has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(12) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (11), the President and Technical Members of`
  line `the National Appellate Authority shall not be removed from their office except by an order made by the`
  line `Government on the ground of proven misbehaviour or incapacity after an inquiry made by a Judge of the`
  line `Supreme Court nominated by the Chief Justice of India on a reference made to him by the Government`
  line `and such President or Member had been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(13) The Government, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of India, may suspend from office,`
  line `the President or Technical Members of the National Appellate Authority in respect of whom a reference`
  line `has been made to the Judge of the Supreme Court under sub-section (12).`
  line
  line `(14) Subject to the provisions of article 220 of the Constitution, the President or Members of the`
  line `National Appellate Authority, on ceasing to hold their office, shall not be eligible to appear, act or plead`
  line `before the National Appellate Authority where he was the President or, as the case may be, a Member.]`
obj_root_law_sections_101_b:
  sectionId (51464)
  sectionNo 101B
  orderNo 110
  title `Appeal to National Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 105 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=51464&sectionno=101B&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_101_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[101B. Appeal to National Appellate Authority.--- (1) Where, in respect of the questions referred to`
  line `in sub-section (2) of section 97, conflicting Advance Rulings are given by the Appellate Authorities of`
  line `two or more States or Union territories or both under sub-section (1) or sub-section (3) of section 101, any`
  line `officer authorised by the Commissioner or an applicant, being distinct person referred to in section 25`
  line `aggrieved by such Advance Ruling, may prefer an appeal to National Appellate Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officer shall be from the States in which such Advance Rulings have been given.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under this section shall be filed within a period of thirty days from the date on which`
  line `the ruling sought to be appealed against is communicated to the applicants, concerned officers and`
  line `jurisdictional officers:`
  line
  line `Provided that the officer authorised by the Commissioner may file appeal within a period of ninety`
  line `days from the date on which the ruling sought to be appealed against is communicated to the concerned`
  line `officer or the jurisdictional officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the National Appellate Authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was`
  line `prevented by a sufficient cause from presenting the appeal within the said period of thirty days, or as the`
  line `case may be, ninety days, allow such appeal to be presented within a further period not exceeding thirty`
  line days.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For removal of doubts, it is clarified that the period of thirty days or as the case may`
  line `be, ninety days shall be counted from the date of communication of the last of the conflicting rulings`
  line `sought to be appealed against.`
  line
  line `(3) Every appeal under this section shall be in such form, accompanied by such fee and verified in`
  line `such manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_101_c:
  sectionId (51465)
  sectionNo 101C
  orderNo 111
  title `Order of National Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_c_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 105 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=51465&sectionno=101C&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_101_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[101C. Order of National Appellate Authority.--- (1) The National Appellate Authority may, after`
  line `giving an opportunity of being heard to the applicant, the officer authorised by the Commissioner, all`
  line `Principal Chief Commissioners, Chief Commissioners of Central tax and Chief Commissioner and`
  line `Commissioner of State tax of all States and Chief Commissioner and Commissioner of Union territory tax`
  line `of all Union territories, pass such order as it thinks fit, confirming or modifying the rulings appealed`
  line against.
  line
  line `(2) If the members of the National Appellate Authority differ in opinion on any point, it shall be`
  line `decided according to the opinion of the majority.`
  line
  line `(3) The order referred to in sub-section (1) shall be passed as far as possible within a period of ninety`
  line `days from the date of filing of the appeal under section 101B.`
  line
  line `(4) A copy of the Advance Ruling pronounced by the National Appellate Authority shall be duly`
  line `signed by the Members and certified in such manner as may be prescribed and shall be sent to the`
  line `applicant, the officer authorised by the Commissioner, the Board, the Chief Commissioner and`
  line `Commissioner of State tax of all States and Chief Commissioner and Commissioner of Union territory tax`
  line `of all Union territories and to the Authority or Appellate Authority, as the case may be, after such`
  line pronouncement.]
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (5217)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 112
  title `Rectification of advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5217&sectionno=102&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `The Authority or the Appellate Authority ^1[or the National`
  line `Appellate Authority] may amend any order passed by it under section 98 or section 101 ^1[or section 101C,`
  line `respectively,]so as to rectify any error apparent on the face of the record, if such error is noticed by the`
  line `Authority or the Appellate Authority ^1[ or the National Appellate Authority] on its own accord, or is`
  line `brought to its notice by the concerned officer, the jurisdictional officer, the applicant ^2[, appellant, the`
  line `Authority or the Appellate Authority] within a period of six months from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no rectification which has the effect of enhancing the tax liability or reducing the`
  line `amount of admissible input tax credit shall be made unless the applicant or the appellant has been given`
  line `an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 106 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 106, ibid., for "or the appellant" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (5218)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 113
  title `Applicability of advance ruling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 107, (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5218&sectionno=103&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `(1) The advance ruling pronounced by the Authority or the`
  line `Appellate Authority under this Chapter shall be binding only---`
  line
  line `(a) on the applicant who had sought it in respect of any matter referred to in sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 97 for advance ruling;`
  line
  line `(b) on the concerned officer or the jurisdictional officer in respect of the applicant.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) The Advance Ruling pronounced by the National Appellate Authority under this Chapter shall`
  line `be binding on---`
  line
  line `(a) the applicants, being distinct persons, who had sought the ruling under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 101B and all registered persons having the same Permanent Account Number issued under the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);`
  line
  line `(b) the concerned officers and the jurisdictional officers in respect of the applicants referred to in`
  line `clause (a) and the registered persons having the same Permanent Account Number issued under the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
  line
  line `(2) The advance ruling referred to in sub-section (1) ^1[and sub-section (1A)] shall be binding unless`
  line `the law, facts or circumstances supporting the original advance ruling have changed.`
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (5219)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 114
  title `Advance ruling to be void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5219&sectionno=104&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Authority ^1[or the National Appellate Authority] finds that advance ruling pronounced by it under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 98 or under sub-section (1) of section 101 ^1[or under section 101C] has been`
  line `obtained by the applicant or the appellant by fraud or suppression of material facts or misrepresentation of`
  line `facts, it may, by order, declare such ruling to be void ab-initio and thereupon all the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules made thereunder shall apply to the applicant or the appellant as if such advance ruling had never`
  line `been made:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be passed under this sub-section unless an opportunity of being heard has`
  line `been given to the applicant or the appellant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- The period beginning with the date of such advance ruling and ending with the date`
  line `of order under this sub-section shall be excluded while computing the period specified in sub-sections (2)`
  line `and (10) of section 73 or sub-sections (2) and (10) of section 74 ^2[or sub-sections (2) and (7) of section`
  line 74A].
  line
  line `(2) A copy of the order made under sub-section (1) shall be sent to the applicant, the concerned`
  line `officer and the jurisdictional officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 108 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 140 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024)`
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (5220)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 115
  title `Powers of Authority, Appellate Authority and National Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5220&sectionno=105&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `^1[Powers of Authority, Appellate Authority and National Appellate Authority.]--- (1) The`
  line `Authority or the Appellate Authority ^2[or the National Appellate Authority] shall, for the purpose of`
  line `exercising its powers regarding---`
  line
  line `(a) discovery and inspection;`
  line
  line `(b) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commissions and compelling production of books of account and other records,`
  line
  line `have all the powers of a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(2) The Authority or the Appellate Authority ^2[or the National Appellate Authority] shall be deemed`
  line `to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195, but not for the purposes of Chapter XXVI of the Code`
  line `of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), and every proceeding before the Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Authority shall be deemed to be a judicial proceedings within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and`
  line `for the purpose of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 109, for "marginal heading" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 109, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (5221)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 116
  title `Procedure of Authority, Appellate Authority and National Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5221&sectionno=106&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `^1[Procedure of Authority, Appellate Authority and National Appellate Authority.]--- The`
  line `Authority or the Appellate Authority ^2[or the National Appellate Authority] shall, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, have power to regulate its own procedure.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 110 for "marginal heading" (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 110, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (5222)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 117
  title `Appeals to Appellate Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5222&sectionno=107&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order passed`
  line `under this Act or the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act by an adjudicating authority may appeal to such Appellate Authority as may be prescribed within`
  line `three months from the date on which the said decision or order is communicated to such person.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner may, on his own motion, or upon request from the Commissioner of State tax or`
  line `the Commissioner of Union territory tax, call for and examine the record of any proceedings in which an`
  line `adjudicating authority has passed any decision or order under this Act or the State Goods and Services Tax Act`
  line `or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act, for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or`
  line `propriety of the said decision or order and may, by order, direct any officer subordinate to him to apply to the`
  line `Appellate Authority within six months from the date of communication of the said decision or order for the`
  line `determination of such points arising out of the said decision or order as may be specified by the Commissioner`
  line `in his order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, in pursuance of an order under sub-section (2), the authorised officer makes an application`
  line `to the Appellate Authority, such application shall be dealt with by the Appellate Authority as if it were an`
  line `appeal made against the decision or order of the adjudicating authority and such authorised officer were`
  line `an appellant and the provisions of this Act relating to appeals shall apply to such application.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Authority may, if he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from presenting the appeal within the aforesaid period of three months or six months, as the case may be,`
  line `allow it to be presented within a further period of one month.`
  line
  line `(5) Every appeal under this section shall be in such form and shall be verified in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) No appeal shall be filed under sub-section (1), unless the appellant has paid---`
  line
  line `(a) in full, such part of the amount of tax, interest, fine, fee and penalty arising from the`
  line `impugned order, as is admitted by him; and`
  line
  line `(b) a sum equal to ten per cent. of the remaining amount of tax in dispute arising from the said order, ^1[subject to a maximum of ^2[twenty] crore rupees,] in relation to which the appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that no appeal shall be filed against an order under sub-section (3) of section 129, unless a`
  line `sum equal to twenty-five per cent. of the penalty has been paid by the appellant.]`
  line
  line `(7) Where the appellant has paid the amount under sub-section (6), the recovery proceedings for the`
  line `balance amount shall be deemed to be stayed.`
  line
  line `(8) The Appellate Authority shall give an opportunity to the appellant of being heard.`
  line
  line `(9) The Appellate Authority may, if sufficient cause is shown at any stage of hearing of an appeal, grant time to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal for reasons to be recorded in writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(10) The Appellate Authority may, at the time of hearing of an appeal, allow an appellant to add any ground of appeal not specified in the grounds of appeal, if it is satisfied that the omission of that ground from the grounds of appeal was not wilful or unreasonable.`
  line
  line `(11) The Appellate Authority shall, after making such further inquiry as may be necessary, pass such order, as it thinks just and proper, confirming, modifying or annulling the decision or order appealed against but shall not refer the case back to the adjudicating authority that passed the said decision or order:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing any fee or penalty or fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating goods of greater value or reducing the amount of refund or input tax credit shall not be passed unless the appellant has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the proposed order:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Appellate Authority is of the opinion that any tax has not been paid or short-paid or erroneously refunded, or where input tax credit has been wrongly availed or utilised, no order requiring the appellant to pay such tax or input tax credit shall be passed unless the appellant is given notice to show cause against the proposed order and the order is passed within the time limit specified under section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A].`
  line
  line `(12) The order of the Appellate Authority disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall state the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons for such decision.`
  line
  line `(13) The Appellate Authority shall, where it is possible to do so, hear and decide every appeal within a period of one year from the date on which it is filed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the issuance of order is stayed by an order of a court or Tribunal, the period of such stay shall be excluded in computing the period of one year.`
  line
  line `(14) On disposal of the appeal, the Appellate Authority shall communicate the order passed by it to`
  line `the appellant, respondent and to the adjudicating authority.`
  line
  line `(15) A copy of the order passed by the Appellate Authority shall also be sent to the jurisdictional`
  line `Commissioner or the authority designated by him in this behalf and the jurisdictional Commissioner of State tax or Commissioner of Union Territory Tax or an authority designated by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(16) Every order passed under this section shall, subject to the provisions of section 108 or section 113 or section 117 or section 118 be final and binding on the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 25 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 141, for "twenty-five" (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 116 (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (5223)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 118
  title `Powers of Revisional Authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5223&sectionno=108&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of section 121 and any rules made`
  line `thereunder, the Revisional Authority may, on his own motion, or upon information received by him or on`
  line `request from the Commissioner of State tax, or the Commissioner of Union territory tax, call for and examine`
  line `the record of any proceedings, and if he considers that any decision or order passed under this Act or under the`
  line `State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act by any officer`
  line `subordinate to him is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interest of revenue and is illegal or improper`
  line `or has not taken into account certain material facts, whether available at the time of issuance of the said order`
  line `or not or in consequence of an observation by the Comptroller and Auditor General of India, he may, if`
  line `necessary, stay the operation of such decision or order for such period as he deems fit and after giving the`
  line `person concerned an opportunity of being heard and after making such further inquiry as may be necessary,`
  line `pass such order, as he thinks just and proper, including enhancing or modifying or annulling the said decision`
  line `or order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Revisional Authority shall not exercise any power under sub-section (1), if---`
  line
  line `(a) the order has been subject to an appeal under section 107 or section 112 or section 117 or`
  line `section 118; or`
  line
  line `(b) the period specified under sub-section (2) of section 107 has not yet expired or more than`
  line `three years have expired after the passing of the decision or order sought to be revised; or`
  line
  line `(c) the order has already been taken for revision under this section at an earlier stage; or`
  line
  line `(d) the order has been passed in exercise of the powers under sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Revisional Authority may pass an order under sub-section (1) on any point which`
  line `has not been raised and decided in an appeal referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (2), before the expiry`
  line `of a period of one year from the date of the order in such appeal or before the expiry of a period of three`
  line `years referred to in clause (b) of that sub-section, whichever is later.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order passed in revision under sub-section (1) shall, subject to the provisions of section 113 or`
  line `section 117 or section 118, be final and binding on the parties.`
  line
  line `(4) If the said decision or order involves an issue on which the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court has`
  line `given its decision in some other proceedings and an appeal to the High Court or the Supreme Court against`
  line `such decision of the Appellate Tribunal or the High Court is pending, the period spent between the date of the`
  line `decision of the Appellate Tribunal and the date of the decision of the High Court or the date of the decision of`
  line `the High Court and the date of decision of the Supreme Court shall be excluded in computing the period of`
  line `limitation referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (2) where proceedings for revision have been initiated by way`
  line `of issue of a notice under this section.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the issuance of an order under sub-section (1) is stayed by the order of a court or Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, the period of such stay shall be excluded in computing the period of limitation referred to in`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(6) For the purposes of this section, the term,---`
  line
  line `(i) "record" shall include all records relating to any proceedings under this Act available at the`
  line `time of examination by the Revisional Authority;`
  line
  line `(ii) "decision" shall include intimation given by any officer lower in rank than the Revisional`
  line Authority.
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (5224)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 119
  title `Constitution of Appellate Tribunal and Benches thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5224&sectionno=109&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `^1[109. Constitution of Appellate Tribunal and Benches thereof.--- (1) The Government shall, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, by notification, establish with effect from such date as may be specified`
  line `therein, an Appellate Tribunal known as the Goods and Services Tax Appellate Tribunal for hearing`
  line `appeals against the orders passed by the Appellate Authority or the Revisional Authority ^2[, or for`
  line `conducting an examination or adjudicating the cases referred to in sub-section (2) of sections 171, if so`
  line `notified under the said section].`
  line
  line `(2) The jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on the Appellate Tribunal shall be exercised by`
  line `the Principal Bench and the State Benches constituted under sub-section (3) and sub-section (4).`
  line
  line `(3) The Government shall, by notification, constitute a Principal Bench of the Appellate Tribunal at`
  line `New Delhi which shall consist of the President, a Judicial Member, a Technical Member (Centre) and a`
  line `Technical Member (State).`
  line
  line `(4) On the request of the State, the Government may, by notification, constitute such number of State`
  line `Benches at such places and with such jurisdiction as may be recommended by the Council, which shall`
  line `consist of two Judical Members, a Technial Member (Centre) and a Technical Member (State).`
  line
  line `(5) The Principal Bench and the State Bench shall hear appeals against the orders passed by the`
  line `Appellate Authority or the Revisional Authority:`
  line
  line `Provided that the cases in which any one of the issues involved relates to the place of supply, shall be`
  line `heard only by the Principal Bench.`
  line
  line `^2[Provided further that the matters referred to in sub-section (2) of section 171 shall be examined or`
  line `adjudicated only by the Principal Bench:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, notify other cases or`
  line `class of cases which shall be heard only by the Principal Bench.]`
  line
  line `(6) ^1[Subject to the provisions of sub-section (5), the President shall, from time to time, by a general`
  line `or special order, distribute the business of the Appellate Tribunal among the Benches and may transfer`
  line `cases from one Bench to another.`
  line
  line `(7) The senior-most Judicial Member within the State Benches, as may be notified, shall act as the`
  line `Vice-President for such State Benches and shall exercise such powers of the President as may be`
  line `prescribed, but for all other purposes be considered as a Member.`
  line
  line `(8) Appeals, where the tax or input tax credit involved or the amount of fine, fee or penalty`
  line `determined in any order appealed against, does not exceed fifty lakh rupees and which does not involve`
  line `any question of law may, with the approval of the President, and subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed on the recommendations of the Council, be heard by a single Member, and in all other cases,`
  line `shall be heard together by one Judicial Member and one Technical Member.`
  line
  line `(9) If, after hearing the case, the Members differ in their opinion on any point or points, such Member`
  line `shall state the point or points on which they differ, and the President shall refer such case for hearing,---`
  line
  line `(a) where the appeal was originally heard by Members of a State Bench, to another Member of a`
  line `State Bench within the State or, where no such other State Bench is available within the State, to a`
  line `Member of a State Bench in another State;`
  line
  line `(b) where the appeal was originally heard by Members of the Principal Bench, to another Member`
  line `from the Principal Bench or, where no such other Member is available, to a Member of any State`
  line Bench,
  line
  line `and such point or points shall be decided according to the majority opinion including the opinion of the`
  line `Members who first heard the case.`
  line
  line `(10) The Government may, in consultation with the President, for the administrative efficiency,`
  line `transfer Members from one Bench to another Bench:`
  line
  line `Provided that a Technical Member (State) of a State Bench may be transferred to a State Bench only`
  line `of the same State in which he was originally appointed, in consultation with the State Government.`
  line
  line `(11) No act or proceedings of the Appellate Tribunal shall be questioned or shall be invalid merely on`
  line `the ground of the existence of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 149, for section 109 (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 142 (w.e.f. 27-9-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 142, for "The President" (w.e.f. 27-9-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (5225)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 120
  title `President and Members of Appellate Tribunal, their qualification, appointment, conditions of service, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5225&sectionno=110&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `^1[110. President and Members of Appellate Tribunal, their qualification, appointment, conditions of`
  line `service, etc.]--- (1) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as---`
  line
  line `(a) the President, unless he has been a Judge of the Supreme Court or is or has been the Chief`
  line `Justice of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) a Judicial Member, unless he---`
  line
  line `(i) has been a Judge of the High Court; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has, for a combined period of ten years, been a District Judge or an Additional District`
  line Judge;
  line
  line `^2[(iii) has been an advocate for ten years with substantial experience in litigation in matters`
  line `relating to indirect taxes in the Appellate Tribunal, Customs, Excise and Service Tax Appellate`
  line `Tribunal, State Value Added Tax Tribunal, by whatever name called, High Court or Supreme`
  line Court;]
  line
  line `^3[Provided that a person who has not completed the age of fifty years shall not be eligible for`
  line `appointment as the President or Member.]`
  line
  line `(c) a Technical Member (Centre), unless he is or has been a member of the Indian Revenue`
  line `(Customs and Indirect Taxes) Service, Group A, or of the All India Service with at least three years of`
  line `experience in the administration of an existing law or goods and services tax in the Central`
  line `Government, and has completed at least twenty-five years of service in Group A;`
  line
  line `(d) a Technical Member (State), unless he is or has been an officer of the State Government or an`
  line `officer of All India Service, not below the rank of Additional Commissioner of Value Added Tax or`
  line `the State goods and services tax or such rank, not lower than that of the First Appellate Authority, as`
  line `may be notified by the concerned State Government, on the recommendations of the Council and has`
  line `completed twenty-five years of service in Group A, or equivalent, with at least three years of`
  line `experience in the administration of an existing law or the goods and services tax or in the field of`
  line `finance and taxation in the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by notification,`
  line `relax the requirement of completion of twenty-five years of service in Group A, or equivalent, in`
  line `respect of officers of such State where no person has completed twenty-five years of service in Group`
  line `A, or equivalent, but has completed twenty-five years of service in the Government, subject to such`
  line `conditions, and till such period, as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) The President, Judicial Member, Technical Member (Centre) and Technical Member (State) shall`
  line `be appointed or re-appointed by the Government on the recommendations of a Search-cum-Selection`
  line `Committee constituted under sub-section (4):`
  line
  line `Provided that in the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the President by reason of`
  line `his death, resignation or otherwise, the Judicial Member or, in his absence, the senior-most Technical`
  line `Member of the Principal Bench shall act as the President until the date on which a new President,`
  line `appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the President is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence,`
  line `illness or any other cause, the Judicial Member or, in his absence, the senior-most Technical Member of`
  line `the Principal Bench, shall discharge the functions of the President until the date on which the President`
  line `resumes his duties.`
  line
  line `(3) While making selection for Technical Member (State) of a State Bench, first preference shall be`
  line `given to officers who have worked in the State Government of the State to which the jurisdiction of the`
  line `Bench extends.`
  line
  line `(4) (a) The Search-cum-Selection Committee for Technical Member (State) of a State Bench shall`
  line `consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Justice of the High Court in whose jurisdiction the State Bench is located, to be the`
  line `Chairperson of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) the senior-most Judicial Member in the State, and where no Judicial Member is available, a`
  line `retired Judge of the High Court in whose jurisdiction the State Bench is located, as may be nominated`
  line `by the Chief Justice of such High Court;`
  line
  line `(iii) Chief Secretary of the State in which the State Bench is located;`
  line
  line `(iv) one Additional Chief Secretary or Principal Secretary or Secretary of the State in which the`
  line `State Bench is located, as may be nominated by such State Government, not in-charge of the`
  line `Department responsible for administration of State tax; and`
  line
  line `(v) Additional Chief Secretary or Principal Secretary or Secretary of the Department responsible`
  line `for administration of State tax, of the State in which the State Bench is located Member Secretary;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the Search-cum-Selection Committee for all other cases shall consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Justice of India or a Judge of Supreme Court nominated by him, to be the`
  line `Chairperson of the Committee;`
  line
  line `(ii) Secretary of the Central Government nominated by the Cabinet Secretary --- Member;`
  line
  line `(iii) Chief Secretary of a State to be nominated by the Council--- Member;`
  line
  line `(iv) one Member, who---`
  line
  line `(A) in case of appointment of a President of a Tribunal, shall be the outgoing President of the`
  line `Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(B) in case of appointment of a Member of a Tribunal, shall be the sitting President of the`
  line `Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(C) in case of the President of the Tribunal seeking re-appointment or where the outgoing`
  line `President is unavailable or the removal of the President is being considered, shall be a retired`
  line `Judge of the Supreme Court or a retired Chief Justice of a High Court nominated by the Chief`
  line `Justice of India; and`
  line
  line `(v) Secretary of the Department of Revenue in the Ministry of Finance of the Central`
  line `Government---Member Secretary.`
  line
  line `(5) The Chairperson shall have the casting vote and the Member Secretary shall not have a vote.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order, or decree of any court or any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the Committee shall recommend a panel of two names for appointment or`
  line `re-appointment to the post of the President or a Member, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) No appointment or re-appointment of the Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall be invalid`
  line `merely by reason of any vacancy or defect in the constitution of the Search-cum-Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(8) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order, or decree of any court or any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the salary of the President and the Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall be`
  line `such as may be prescribed and their allowances and other terms and conditions of service shall be the`
  line `same as applicable to Central Government officers carrying the same pay:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `President of Members of the Appellate Tribunal shall be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line `appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, if the President or Member takes a house on rent, he may be reimbursed a house`
  line `rent higher than the house rent allowance as are admissible to a Central Government officer holding the`
  line `post carrying the same pay, subject to such limitations and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order, or decree of any court or any law for`
  line `the time being in force, the President of the Appellate Tribunal shall hold office for a term of four years`
  line `from the date on which he enters upon his office, or until he attains the age of ^4[seventy years, whichever`
  line `is earlier and shall be eligible for re-appointment for a period not exceeding two years subject to the age-limit specified above].`
  line
  line `(10) Notwithstanding anything contained in any judgment, order, or decree of any court or any law`
  line `for the time being in force, the Judicial Member, Technical Member (Centre) or Technical Member`
  line `(State) of the Appellate Tribunal shall hold office for a term of four years from the date on which he`
  line `enters upon his office, or until he attains the age of ^4[sixty-seven years, whichever is earlier and shall be`
  line `eligible for re-appointment for a period not exceeding two years subject to the age-limit specified above].`
  line
  line `(11) The President or any Member may, by notice in writing under his hand addressed to the`
  line `Government, resign from his office:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or Member shall continue to hold office until the expiry of three months`
  line `from the date of receipt of such notice by the Government or until a person duly appointed as his`
  line `successor enters upon his office or until the expiry of his term of office, whichever is the earliest.`
  line
  line `(12) The Government may, on the recommendations of the Search-cum-Selection Committee, remove`
  line `from the office President or a Member, who---`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which involves moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable of acting as such President or Member; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions as`
  line `such President or Member; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line `interest:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President or the Member shall not be removed on any of the grounds specified`
  line `in clauses (d) and (e), unless he has been informed of the charges against him and has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(13) The Government, on the recommendations of the Search-cum-Selection Committee, may`
  line `suspend from office, the President or a Judicial or Technical Member in respect of whom proceedings for`
  line `removal have been initiated under sub-section (12).`
  line
  line `(14) Subject to the provisions of article 220 of the Constitution, the President or other Members, on`
  line `ceasing to hold their office, shall not be eligible to appear, act or plead before the Principal Bench or the`
  line `State Bench in which he was the President or, as the case may be, a Member.]`
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 150, for section 110 (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 48 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-12-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 48 of 2023, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-12-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 48 of 2023, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 28-12-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (5226)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 121
  title `Procedure before Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5226&sectionno=111&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal shall not, while disposing`
  line `of any proceedings before it or an appeal before it, be bound by the procedure laid down in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder, the Appellate Tribunal shall have power to regulate its`
  line `own procedure.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, have`
  line `the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) while`
  line `trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872), requisitioning any public record or document or a copy of such record or document from`
  line `any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing a representation for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any representation for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Any order made by the Appellate Tribunal may be enforced by it in the same manner as if it were`
  line `a decree made by a court in a suit pending therein, and it shall be lawful for the Appellate Tribunal to`
  line `send for execution of its orders to the court within the local limits of whose jurisdiction,---`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of an order against a company, the registered office of the company is situated; or`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of an order against any other person, the person concerned voluntarily resides or`
  line `carries on business or personally works for gain.`
  line
  line `(4) All proceedings before the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860),`
  line `and the Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI`
  line `of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (5227)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 122
  title `Appeals to Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5227&sectionno=112&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order passed against him`
  line `under section 107 or section 108 of this Act or the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order within`
  line `three months from the date on which the order sought to be appealed against is communicated to the`
  line `person preferring the appeal ^1[; or the date, as may be notified by the Government, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council, for filing appeal before the Appellate Tribunal under this Act,`
  line `whichever is later.]`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal may, in its discretion, refuse to admit any such appeal where the tax or`
  line `input tax credit involved or the difference in tax or input tax credit involved or the amount of fine, fee or`
  line `penalty determined by such order, does not exceed fifty thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(3) The Commissioner may, on his own motion, or upon request from the Commissioner of State tax or`
  line `Commissioner of Union territory tax, call for and examine the record of any order passed by the Appellate`
  line `Authority or the Revisional Authority under this Act or the State Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or propriety of the`
  line `said order and may, by order, direct any officer subordinate to him to apply to the Appellate Tribunal within`
  line `six months from the date on which the said order has been passed ^1[; or the date, as may be notified by the`
  line `Government, on the recommendations of the Council, for the purpose of filing application before the`
  line `Appellate Tribunal under this Act, whichever is later,] for determination of such points arising out`
  line `of the said order as may be specified by the Commissioner in his order.`
  line
  line `(4) Where in pursuance of an order under sub-section (3) the authorised officer makes an application to`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal, such application shall be dealt with by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal`
  line `made against the order under sub-section (11) of section 107 or under sub-section (1) of section 108 and the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall apply to such application, as they apply in relation to appeals filed under`
  line `sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(5) On receipt of notice that an appeal has been preferred under this section, the party against whom`
  line `the appeal has been preferred may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order or`
  line `any part thereof, file, within forty-five days of the receipt of notice, a memorandum of cross-objections,`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order appealed against and such memorandum`
  line `shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal, as if it were an appeal presented within the time specified`
  line `in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(6) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal within three months after the expiry of the period`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1)`
  line `^2[or permit the filing of an application within three months after the expiry`
  line `of the period referred to in sub-section (1)], or permit the filing of a memorandum of cross-objections within forty-five`
  line `days after the expiry of the period referred to in sub-section (5) if it is satisfied that there was sufficient`
  line `cause for not presenting it within that period.`
  line
  line `(7) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in such form, verified in such manner and shall be`
  line `accompanied by such fee, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(8) No appeal shall be filed under sub-section (1), unless the appellant has paid--`
  line
  line `(a) in full, such part of the amount of tax, interest, fine, fee and penalty arising from the`
  line `impugned order, as is admitted by him; and`
  line
  line `(b) a sum equal to ^3[ten per cent.] of the remaining amount of tax in dispute, in addition to the amount paid under sub-section (6) of section 107, arising from the said order, ^4[subject to a maximum`
  line `of ^5[twenty crore rupees],] in relation to which the appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(9) Where the appellant has paid the amount as per sub-section (8), the recovery proceedings for the`
  line `balance amount shall be deemed to be stayed till the disposal of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(10) Every application made before the Appellate Tribunal,---`
  line
  line `(a) in an appeal for rectification of error or for any other purpose; or`
  line
  line `(b) for restoration of an appeal or an application,`
  line
  line `shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 143 (w.e.f. 1-8-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 143 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 143, ibid., for "twenty per cent." (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 143, for "fifty crore rupees" (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (5228)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 123
  title `Orders of Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5228&sectionno=113&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the parties to the`
  line `appeal an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, confirming, modifying or`
  line `annulling the decision or order appealed against or may refer the case back to the Appellate Authority, or`
  line `the Revisional Authority or to the original adjudicating authority, with such directions as it may think fit,`
  line `for a fresh adjudication or decision after taking additional evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The Appellate Tribunal may, if sufficient cause is shown, at any stage of hearing of an appeal,`
  line `grant time to the parties or any of them and adjourn the hearing of the appeal for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such adjournment shall be granted more than three times to a party during hearing`
  line `of the appeal.`
  line
  line `(3) The Appellate Tribunal may amend any order passed by it under sub-section (1) so as to rectify`
  line `any error apparent on the face of the record, if such error is noticed by it on its own accord, or is brought`
  line `to its notice by the Commissioner or the Commissioner of State tax or the Commissioner of the Union`
  line `territory tax or the other party to the appeal within a period of three months from the date of the order:`
  line
  line `Provided that no amendment which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `input tax credit or otherwise increasing the liability of the other party, shall be made under this`
  line `sub-section, unless the party has been given an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal shall, as far as possible, hear and decide every appeal within a period of`
  line `one year from the date on which it is filed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order passed under this section to the Appellate`
  line `Authority or the Revisional Authority, or the original adjudicating authority, as the case may be, the appellant`
  line `and the jurisdictional Commissioner or the Commissioner of State tax or the Union territory tax.`
  line
  line `(6) Save as provided in section 117 or section 118, orders passed by the Appellate Tribunal on an`
  line `appeal shall be final and binding on the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (5229)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 124
  title `Financial and administrative powers of President.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 151, for section 114 (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5229&sectionno=114&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `^1[114. Financial and administrative powers of President.--- The President shall exercise such`
  line `financial and administrative powers over the Appellate Tribunal as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (5230)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 125
  title `Interest on refund of amount paid for admission of appeal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5230&sectionno=115&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Where an amount paid by the`
  line `appellant under sub-section (6) of section 107 or sub-section (8) of section 112 is required to be refunded`
  line `consequent to any order of the Appellate Authority or of the Appellate Tribunal, interest at the rate`
  line `specified under section 56 shall be payable in respect of such refund from the date of payment of the`
  line `amount till the date of refund of such amount.`
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (5231)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 126
  title `Appearance by authorised representative.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5231&sectionno=116&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who is entitled or required to`
  line `appear before an officer appointed under this Act, or the Appellate Authority or the Appellate Tribunal in`
  line `connection with any proceedings under this Act, may, otherwise than when required under this Act to`
  line `appear personally for examination on oath or affirmation, subject to the other provisions of this section,`
  line `appear by an authorised representative.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this Act, the expression "authorised representative" shall mean a person`
  line `authorised by the person referred to in sub-section (1) to appear on his behalf, being--`
  line
  line `(a) his relative or regular employee; or`
  line
  line `(b) an advocate who is entitled to practice in any court in India, and who has not been debarred`
  line `from practicing before any court in India; or`
  line
  line `(c) any chartered accountant, a cost accountant or a company secretary, who holds a certificate of`
  line `practice and who has not been debarred from practice; or`
  line
  line `(d) a retired officer of the Commercial Tax Department of any State Government or Union territory or`
  line `of the Board who, during his service under the Government, had worked in a post not below the rank than`
  line `that of a Group-B Gazetted officer for a period of not less than two years:`
  line
  line `Provided that such officer shall not be entitled to appear before any proceedings under this Act for a`
  line `period of one year from the date of his retirement or resignation; or`
  line
  line `(e) any person who has been authorised to act as a goods and services tax practitioner on behalf of`
  line `the concerned registered person.`
  line
  line `(3) No person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been dismissed or removed from Government service; or`
  line
  line `(b) who is convicted of an offence connected with any proceedings under this Act, the State`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act, the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union Territory`
  line `Goods and Services Tax Act, or under the existing law or under any of the Acts passed by a State`
  line `Legislature dealing with the imposition of taxes on sale of goods or supply of goods or services or`
  line `both; or`
  line
  line `(c) who is found guilty of misconduct by the prescribed authority; or`
  line
  line `(d) who has been adjudged as an insolvent,`
  line
  line `shall be qualified to represent any person under sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(i) for all times in case of persons referred to in clauses (a), (b) and (c); and`
  line
  line `(ii) for the period during which the insolvency continues in the case of a person referred to in`
  line `clause (d).`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who has been disqualified under the provisions of the State Goods and Services Tax`
  line `Act or the Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act shall be deemed to be disqualified under this Act`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (5232)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 127
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 152, for "State Bench or Area Bench" (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5232&sectionno=117&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any order passed by the ^1[State Benches] or`
  line `Area Benches of the Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court and the High Court may admit`
  line `such appeal, if it is satisfied that the case involves a substantial question of law.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of one hundred and eighty days from`
  line `the date on which the order appealed against is received by the aggrieved person and it shall be in such`
  line `form, verified in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period if it is`
  line `satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within such period.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the High Court is satisfied that a substantial question of law is involved in any case, it shall`
  line `formulate that question and the appeal shall be heard only on the question so formulated, and the`
  line `respondents shall, at the hearing of the appeal, be allowed to argue that the case does not involve such`
  line `question:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be deemed to take away or abridge the power of the court`
  line `to hear, for reasons to be recorded, the appeal on any other substantial question of law not formulated by it,`
  line `if it is satisfied that the case involves such question.`
  line
  line `(4) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver such judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and may award such cost as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(5) The High Court may determine any issue which---`
  line
  line `(a) has not been determined by the ^1[State Benches] or Area Benches; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been wrongly determined by the ^1[State Benches] or Area Benches, by reason of a decision on`
  line `such question of law as herein referred to in sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(6) Where an appeal has been filed before the High Court, it shall be heard by a Bench of not less`
  line `than two Judges of the High Court, and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such Judges or`
  line `of the majority, if any, of such Judges.`
  line
  line `(7) Where there is no such majority, the Judges shall state the point of law upon which they differ and the`
  line `case shall, then, be heard upon that point only, by one or more of the other Judges of the High Court and such`
  line `point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Judges who have heard the case`
  line `including those who first heard it.`
  line
  line `(8) Where the High Court delivers a judgment in an appeal filed before it under this section, effect`
  line `shall be given to such judgment by either side on the basis of a certified copy of the judgment.`
  line
  line `(9) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the High Court shall, as far as may be, apply in the case of appeals`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (5233)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 128
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 153, for "National Bench or Regional Bench" (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5233&sectionno=118&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court--`
  line
  line `(a) from any order passed by the ^1[Principal Bench] of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal; or`
  line
  line `(b) from any judgment or order passed by the High Court in an appeal made under section 117`
  line `in any case which, on its own motion or on an application made by or on behalf of the party`
  line `aggrieved, immediately after passing of the judgment or order, the High Court certifies to be a fit`
  line `one for appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), relating to appeals to the`
  line `Supreme Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under this section as they apply in the`
  line `case of appeals from decrees of a High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed in the appeal, effect shall be given to`
  line `the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in section 117 in the case of a judgment of the`
  line `High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (5234)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 129
  title `Sums due to be paid notwithstanding appeal, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5234&sectionno=119&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding that an appeal has been`
  line `preferred to the High Court or the Supreme Court, sums due to the Government as a result of an order`
  line `passed by the ^1[Principal Bench] of the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 113 or an order passed by the ^2[Principal Bench] of the Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 113 or an order passed by the High Court under section 117, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be payable in accordance with the order so passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 154, ibid., for "National Bench or Regional Benches" (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for "State Bench or Area Benches" (w.e.f. 1-8-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (5235)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 130
  title `Appeal not to be filed in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5235&sectionno=120&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, on the recommendations of the`
  line `Council, from time to time, issue orders or instructions or directions fixing such monetary limits, as it`
  line `may deem fit, for the purposes of regulating the filing of appeal or application by the officer of the central`
  line `tax under the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, in pursuance of the orders or instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1), the`
  line `officer of the central tax has not filed an appeal or application against any decision or order passed under`
  line `the provisions of this Act, it shall not preclude such officer of the central tax from filing appeal or`
  line `application in any other case involving the same or similar issues or questions of law.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the fact that no appeal or application has been filed by the officer of the central`
  line `tax pursuant to the orders or instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1), no person, being a`
  line `party in appeal or application shall contend that the officer of the central tax has acquiesced in the`
  line `decision on the disputed issue by not filing an appeal or application.`
  line
  line `(4) The Appellate Tribunal or court hearing such appeal or application shall have regard to the`
  line `circumstances under which appeal or application was not filed by the officer of the central tax in`
  line `pursuance of the orders or instructions or directions issued under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (5236)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 131
  title `Non-appealable decisions and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5236&sectionno=121&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in any`
  line `provisions of this Act, no appeal shall lie against any decision taken or order passed by an officer of central tax`
  line `if such decision taken or order passed relates to any one or more of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) an order of the Commissioner or other authority empowered to direct transfer of proceedings`
  line `from one officer to another officer; or`
  line
  line `(b) an order pertaining to the seizure or retention of books of account, register and other`
  line `documents; or`
  line
  line `(c) an order sanctioning prosecution under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) an order passed under section 80.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (5237)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 132
  title `Penalty for certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5237&sectionno=122&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a taxable person who---`
  line
  line `(i) supplies any goods or services or both without issue of any invoice or issues an incorrect or`
  line `false invoice with regard to any such supply;`
  line
  line `(ii) issues any invoice or bill without supply of goods or services or both in violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(iii) collects any amount as tax but fails to pay the same to the Government beyond a period of three`
  line `months from the date on which such payment becomes due;`
  line
  line `(iv) collects any tax in contravention of the provisions of this Act but fails to pay the same to the`
  line `Government beyond a period of three months from the date on which such payment becomes due;`
  line
  line `(v) fails to deduct the tax in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 51, or`
  line `deducts an amount which is less than the amount required to be deducted under the said sub-section,`
  line `or where he fails to pay to the Government under sub-section (2) thereof, the amount deducted as tax;`
  line
  line `(vi) fails to collect tax in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) of section 52, or`
  line `collects an amount which is less than the amount required to be collected under the said sub-section`
  line `or where he fails to pay to the Government the amount collected as tax under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 52;`
  line
  line `(vii) takes or utilises input tax credit without actual receipt of goods or services or both either`
  line `fully or partially, in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(viii) fraudulently obtains refund of tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ix) takes or distributes input tax credit in contravention of section 20, or the rules made`
  line thereunder;
  line
  line `(x) falsifies or substitutes financial records or produces fake accounts or documents or furnishes`
  line `any false information or return with an intention to evade payment of tax due under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xi) is liable to be registered under this Act but fails to obtain registration;`
  line
  line `(xii) furnishes any false information with regard to registration particulars, either at the time of`
  line `applying for registration, or subsequently;`
  line
  line `(xiii) obstructs or prevents any officer in discharge of his duties under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xiv) transports any taxable goods without the cover of documents as may be specified in this`
  line behalf;
  line
  line `(xv) suppresses his turnover leading to evasion of tax under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xvi) fails to keep, maintain or retain books of account and other documents in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(xvii) fails to furnish information or documents called for by an officer in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder or furnishes false information or documents`
  line `during any proceedings under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xviii) supplies, transports or stores any goods which he has reasons to believe are liable to`
  line `confiscation under this Act;`
  line
  line `(xix) issues any invoice or document by using the registration number of another registered`
  line person;
  line
  line `(xx) tampers with, or destroys any material evidence or document;`
  line
  line `(xxi) disposes of or tampers with any goods that have been detained, seized, or attached under this`
  line Act,
  line
  line `shall be liable to pay a penalty of ten thousand rupees or an amount equivalent to the tax evaded or the tax not`
  line `deducted under section 51 or short deducted or deducted but not paid to the Government or tax not collected`
  line `under section 52 or short collected or collected but not paid to the Government or input tax credit availed of or`
  line `passed on or distributed irregularly, or the refund claimed fraudulently, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `^1[(1A) Any person who retains the benefit of a transaction covered under clauses (i), (ii), (vii) or`
  line `clause (ix) of sub-section (1) and at whose instance such transaction is conducted, shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty of an amount equivalent to the tax evaded or input tax credit availed of or passed on.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any registered person who supplies any goods or services or both on which any tax has not been`
  line `paid or short-paid or erroneously refunded, or where the input tax credit has been wrongly availed or`
  line utilised,---
  line
  line `(a) for any reason, other than the reason of fraud or any wilful misstatement or suppression of`
  line `facts to evade tax, shall be liable to a penalty of ten thousand rupees or ten per cent. of the tax due`
  line `from such person, whichever is higher;`
  line
  line `(b) for reason of fraud or any wilful misstatement or suppression of facts to evade tax, shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty equal to ten thousand rupees or the tax due from such person, whichever is higher.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person who---`
  line
  line `(a) aids or abets any of the offences specified in clauses (i) to (xxi) of sub-section (1);`
  line
  line `(b) acquires possession of, or in any way concerns himself in transporting, removing, depositing,`
  line `keeping, concealing, supplying, or purchasing or in any other manner deals with any goods which he`
  line `knows or has reasons to believe are liable to confiscation under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(c) receives or is in any way concerned with the supply of, or in any other manner deals with any`
  line `supply of services which he knows or has reasons to believe are in contravention of any provisions of`
  line `this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(d) fails to appear before the officer of central tax, when issued with a summons for appearance to`
  line `give evidence or produce a document in an inquiry;`
  line
  line `(e) fails to issue invoice in accordance with the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder or fails to account for an invoice in his books of account,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to a penalty which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `^2[(1B) ^3[Any electronic commerce operator, who is liable to collect tax at source under`
  line `section 52,]---`
  line
  line `(i) allows a supply of goods or services or both through it by an unregistered person other`
  line `than a person exempted from registration by a notification issued under this Act to make such`
  line supply;
  line
  line `(ii) allows an inter-State supply of goods or services or both through it by a person who is not`
  line `eligible to make such inter-State supply; or`
  line
  line `(iii) fails to furnish the correct details in the statement to be furnished under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 52 of any outward supply of goods effected through it by a person exempted from`
  line `obtaining registration under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to pay a penalty of ten thousand rupees, or an amount equivalent to the amount of tax`
  line `involved had such supply been made by a registered person other than a person paying tax under`
  line `section 10, whichever is higher.]`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 126 (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 155 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 144, for "Any electronic commerce operator who" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_122_a:
  sectionId (96648)
  sectionNo 122A
  orderNo 133
  title `Penalty for failure to register certain machines used in manufacture of goods as per special procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2024, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-10-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=96648&sectionno=122A&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_122_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[122A. Penalty for failure to register certain machines used in manufacture of goods as per`
  line `special procedure.--- (1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where any person, who is`
  line `engaged in the manufacture of goods in respect of which any special procedure relating to registration of`
  line `machines has been notified under section 148, acts in contravention of the said special procedure, he`
  line `shall, in addition to any penalty that is paid or is payable by him under Chapter XV or any other`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, be liable to pay a penalty equal to an amount of one lakh rupees for every`
  line `machine not so registered.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the penalty under sub-section (1), every machine not so registered shall be liable for`
  line `seizure and confiscation:`
  line
  line `Provided that such machine shall not be confiscated where---`
  line
  line `(a) the penalty so imposed is paid; and`
  line
  line `(b) the registration of such machine is made in accordance with the special procedure within three`
  line `days of the receipt of communication of the order of penalty.]`
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (5238)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 134
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5238&sectionno=123&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `If a person who is required to furnish an`
  line `information return under section 150 fails to do so within the period specified in the notice issued under`
  line `sub-section (3) thereof, the proper officer may direct that such person shall be liable to pay a penalty of one`
  line `hundred rupees for each day of the period during which the failure to furnish such return continues:`
  line
  line `Provided that the penalty imposed under this section shall not exceed five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (5239)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 135
  title `Fine for failure to furnish statistics.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5239&sectionno=124&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `If any person required to furnish any information or return`
  line `under section 151,---`
  line
  line `(a) without reasonable cause fails to furnish such information or return as may be required under`
  line `that section, or`
  line
  line `(b) wilfully furnishes or causes to furnish any information or return which he knows to be false,`
  line
  line `he shall be punishable with a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees and in case of a continuing`
  line `offence to a further fine which may extend to one hundred rupees for each day after the first day during`
  line `which the offence continues subject to a maximum limit of twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (5240)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 136
  title `General penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5240&sectionno=125&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `Any person, who contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or any`
  line `rules made thereunder for which no penalty is separately provided for in this Act, shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (5241)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 137
  title `General disciplines related to penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5241&sectionno=126&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `(1) No officer under this Act shall impose any penalty`
  line `for minor breaches of tax regulations or procedural requirements and in particular, any omission or`
  line `mistake in documentation which is easily rectifiable and made without fraudulent intent or gross`
  line negligence.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this sub-section,---`
  line
  line `(a) a breach shall be considered a 'minor breach' if the amount of tax involved is less than five`
  line `thousand rupees;`
  line
  line `(b) an omission or mistake in documentation shall be considered to be easily rectifiable if the`
  line `same is an error apparent on the face of record.`
  line
  line `(2) The penalty imposed under this Act shall depend on the facts and circumstances of each case and`
  line `shall be commensurate with the degree and severity of the breach.`
  line
  line `(3) No penalty shall be imposed on any person without giving him an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(4) The officer under this Act shall while imposing penalty in an order for a breach of any law,`
  line `regulation or procedural requirement, specify the nature of the breach and the applicable law, regulation`
  line `or procedure under which the amount of penalty for the breach has been specified.`
  line
  line `(5) When a person voluntarily discloses to an officer under this Act the circumstances of a breach of the`
  line `tax law, regulation or procedural requirement prior to the discovery of the breach by the officer under this`
  line `Act, the proper officer may consider this fact as a mitigating factor when quantifying a penalty for that`
  line person.
  line
  line `(6) The provisions of this section shall not apply in such cases where the penalty specified under this`
  line `Act is either a fixed sum or expressed as a fixed percentage.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (5242)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 138
  title `Power to impose penalty in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 145 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5242&sectionno=127&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `Where the proper officer is of the view that a person is`
  line `liable to a penalty and the same is not covered under any proceedings under section 62 or section 63 or section`
  line `64 or section 73 or section 74 ^1[or section 74A] or section 129 or section 130, he may issue an order levying such penalty`
  line `after giving a reasonable opportunity of being heard to such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (5243)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 139
  title `Power to waive penalty or fee or both.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5243&sectionno=128&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, by notification, waive in part or`
  line `full, any penalty referred to in section 122 or section 123 or section 125 or any late fee referred to in section`
  line `47 for such class of taxpayers and under such mitigating circumstances as may be specified therein on the`
  line `recommendations of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128_a:
  sectionId (96649)
  sectionNo 128A
  orderNo 140
  title `Waiver of interest or penalty or both relating to demands raised under section 73, for certain tax periods.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 146 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=96649&sectionno=128A&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_128_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[128A. Waiver of interest or penalty or both relating to demands raised under section 73, for`
  line `certain tax periods.--- (1) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, where any`
  line `amount of tax is payable by a person chargeable with tax in accordance with,---`
  line
  line `(a) a notice issued under sub-section (1) of section 73 or a statement issued under sub-section (3)`
  line `of section 73, and where no order under sub-section (9) of section 73 has been issued; or`
  line
  line `(b) an order passed under sub-section (9) of section 73, and where no order under`
  line `sub-section (11) of section 107 or sub-section (1) of section 108 has been passed; or`
  line
  line `(c) an order passed under sub-section (11) of section 107 or sub-section (1) of section 108, and`
  line `where no order under sub-section (1) of section 113 has been passed,`
  line
  line `pertaining to the period from 1st July, 2017 to 31st March, 2020, or a part thereof, and the said person`
  line `pays the full amount of tax payable as per the notice or statement or the order referred to in clause (a),`
  line `clause (b) or clause (c), as the case may be, on or before the date, as may be notified by the Government`
  line `on the recommendations of the Council, no interest under section 50 and penalty under this Act, shall be`
  line `payable and all the proceedings in respect of the said notice or order or statement, as the case may be,`
  line `shall be deemed to be concluded, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a notice has been issued under sub-section (1) of section 74, and an order is`
  line `passed or required to be passed by the proper officer in pursuance of the direction of the Appellate`
  line `Authority or Appellate Tribunal or a court in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 75, the said notice or order shall be considered to be a notice or order, as the case may be, referred`
  line `to in clause (a) or clause(b) of this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the conclusion of the proceedings under this sub-section, in cases where an`
  line `application is filed under sub-section (3) of section 107 or under sub-section (3) of section 112 or an`
  line `appeal is filed by an officer of central tax under sub-section (1) of section 117 or under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 118 or where any proceedings are initiated under sub-section (1) of section 108, against an order`
  line `referred to in clause (b) or clause (c) or against the directions of the Appellate Authority or the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or the court referred to in the first proviso, shall be subject to the condition that the said person`
  line `pays the additional amount of tax payable, if any, in accordance with the order of the Appellate Authority`
  line `or the Appellate Tribunal or the court or the Revisional Authority, as the case may be, within three`
  line `months from the date of the said order:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where such interest and penalty has already been paid, no refund of the same shall`
  line `be available.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall be applicable in respect of any amount payable by the`
  line `person on account of erroneous refund.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall be applicable in respect of cases where an appeal or`
  line `writ petition filed by the said person is pending before Appellate Authority or Appellate Tribunal or a`
  line `court, as the case may be, and has not been withdrawn by the said person on or before the date notified`
  line `under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where any amount specified under sub-section (1)`
  line `has been paid and the proceedings are deemed to be concluded under the said sub-section, no appeal`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 107 or sub-section (1) of section 112 shall lie against an order referred to`
  line `in clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1), as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (5244)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 141
  title `Detention, seizure and release of goods and conveyances in transit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5244&sectionno=129&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, where any person transports any goods or stores any goods while they are in`
  line `transit in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, all such goods and`
  line `conveyance used as a means of transport for carrying the said goods and documents relating to such goods`
  line `and conveyance shall be liable to detention or seizure and after detention or seizure, shall be released,---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) on payment of penalty equal to two hundred per cent. of the tax payable on such goods and,`
  line `in case of exempted goods, on payment of an amount equal to two per cent. of the value of goods or`
  line `twenty-five thousand rupees, whichever is less, where the owner of the goods comes forward for`
  line `payment of such penalty;`
  line
  line `(b) on payment of penalty equal to fifty per cent. of the value of the goods or two hundred per`
  line `cent. of the tax payable on such goods, whichever is higher, and in case of exempted goods, on`
  line `payment of an amount equal to five per cent. of the value of goods or twenty-five thousand rupees,`
  line `whichever is less, where the owner of the goods does not come forward for payment of such penalty;]`
  line
  line `(c) upon furnishing a security equivalent to the amount payable under clause (a) or clause (b) in such form and manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such goods or conveyance shall be detained or seized without serving an order of`
  line `detention or seizure on the person transporting the goods.`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(3) The proper officer detaining or seizing goods or conveyance shall issue a notice within seven`
  line `days of such detention or seizure, specifying the penalty payable, and thereafter, pass an order within a`
  line `period of seven days from the date of service of such notice, for payment of penalty under clause (a) or`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line `(4) ^4[No penalty] shall be determined under sub-section (3) without giving the person concerned an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) On payment of amount referred in sub-section (1), all proceedings in respect of the notice`
  line `specified in sub-section (3) shall be deemed to be concluded.`
  line
  line `^5[(6) Where the person transporting any goods or the owner of such goods fails to pay the amount of`
  line `penalty under sub-section (1) within fifteen days from the date of receipt of the copy of the order passed`
  line `under sub-section (3), the goods or conveyance so detained or seized shall be liable to be sold or disposed`
  line `of otherwise, in such manner and within such time as may be prescribed, to recover the penalty payable`
  line `under sub-section (3):`
  line
  line `Provided that the conveyance shall be released on payment by the transporter of penalty under`
  line `sub-section (3) or one lakh rupees, whichever is less:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the detained or seized goods are perishable or hazardous in nature or are`
  line `likely to depreciate in value with passage of time, the said period of fifteen days may be reduced by the`
  line `proper officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 117, for clauses (a) and (b) (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 117, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 117, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 117, ibid., for "No tax, interest or penalty" (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 117, ibid., for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (5245)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 142
  title `Confiscation of goods or conveyances and levy of penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5245&sectionno=130&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Where] any person---`
  line
  line `(i) supplies or receives any goods in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act or the rules`
  line `made thereunder with intent to evade payment of tax; or`
  line
  line `(ii) does not account for any goods on which he is liable to pay tax under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) supplies any goods liable to tax under this Act without having applied for registration; or`
  line
  line `(iv) contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder with intent to`
  line `evade payment of tax; or`
  line
  line `(v) uses any conveyance as a means of transport for carriage of goods in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder unless the owner of the conveyance proves that it`
  line `was so used without the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself, his agent, if any, and the`
  line `person in charge of the conveyance,`
  line
  line `then, all such goods or conveyances shall be liable to confiscation and the person shall be liable to penalty`
  line `under section 122.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever confiscation of any goods or conveyance is authorised by this Act, the officer`
  line `adjudging it shall give to the owner of the goods an option to pay in lieu of confiscation, such fine as the`
  line `said officer thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that such fine leviable shall not exceed the market value of the goods confiscated, less the`
  line `tax chargeable thereon:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the aggregate of such fine and penalty leviable shall not be less than the ^2[penalty equal to hundred per cent. of the tax payable on such goods]:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where any such conveyance is used for the carriage of the goods or passengers for`
  line `hire, the owner of the conveyance shall be given an option to pay in lieu of the confiscation of the`
  line `conveyance a fine equal to the tax payable on the goods being transported thereon.`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(4) No order for confiscation of goods or conveyance or for imposition of penalty shall be issued`
  line `without giving the person an opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any goods or conveyance are confiscated under this Act, the title of such goods or`
  line `conveyance shall thereupon vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The proper officer adjudging confiscation shall take and hold possession of the things confiscated`
  line `and every officer of Police, on the requisition of such proper officer, shall assist him in taking and holding`
  line `such possession.`
  line
  line `(7) The proper officer may, after satisfying himself that the confiscated goods or conveyance are not`
  line `required in any other proceedings under this Act and after giving reasonable time not exceeding three`
  line `months to pay fine in lieu of confiscation, dispose of such goods or conveyance and deposit the sale`
  line `proceeds thereof with the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 118, for "Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if" (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 118,ibid. for "amount of penalty leviable under sub-section (1) of section 129" (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (3) omitted, by s. 118, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (5246)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 143
  title `Confiscation or penalty not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5246&sectionno=131&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the`
  line `provisions contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no confiscation made or penalty`
  line `imposed under the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder shall prevent the infliction of any other`
  line `punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under the provisions of this Act or under any other`
  line `law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (5247)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 144
  title `Punishment for certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5247&sectionno=132&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Whoever commits, or causes to commit and retain the`
  line `benefits arising out of, any of the following offences],`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) supplies any goods or services or both without issue of any invoice, in violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, with the intention to evade tax;`
  line
  line `(b) issues any invoice or bill without supply of goods or services or both in violation of the`
  line `provisions of this Act, or the rules made thereunder leading to wrongful availment or utilisation of`
  line `input tax credit or refund of tax;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) avails input tax credit using the invoice or bill referred to in clause (b) or fraudulently avails`
  line `input tax credit without any invoice or bill;]`
  line
  line `(d) collects any amount as tax but fails to pay the same to the Government beyond a period of three`
  line `months from the date on which such payment becomes due;`
  line
  line `(e) evades tax ^3*** or fraudulently obtains refund and where such offence is not covered under`
  line `clauses (a) to (d);`
  line
  line `(f) falsifies or substitutes financial records or produces fake accounts or documents or furnishes`
  line `any false information with an intention to evade payment of tax due under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(h) acquires possession of, or in any way concerns himself in transporting, removing, depositing,`
  line `keeping, concealing, supplying, or purchasing or in any other manner deals with, any goods which he`
  line `knows or has reasons to believe are liable to confiscation under this Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(i) receives or is in any way concerned with the supply of, or in any other manner deals with any`
  line `supply of services which he knows or has reasons to believe are in contravention of any provisions of this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(l) attempts to commit, or abets the commission of any of the offences mentioned in ^5[clauses (a)`
  line `to (f) and clauses (h) and (i)] of this section,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable---`
  line
  line `(i) in cases where the amount of tax evaded or the amount of input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised`
  line `or the amount of refund wrongly taken exceeds five hundred lakh rupees, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to five years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) in cases where the amount of tax evaded or the amount of input tax credit wrongly availed or`
  line `utilised or the amount of refund wrongly taken exceeds two hundred lakh rupees but does not exceed five`
  line `hundred lakh rupees, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(iii) in the case of ^6[an offence specified in clause (b),] where the amount of tax evaded or the`
  line `amount of input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised or the amount of refund wrongly taken exceeds`
  line `one hundred lakh rupees but does not exceed two hundred lakh rupees, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year and with fine;`
  line
  line `(iv) in cases where he commits or abets the commission of an offence specified in clause (f)`
  line `^7***, he`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(2) Where any person convicted of an offence under this section is again convicted of an offence`
  line `under this section, then, he shall be punishable for the second and for every subsequent offence with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and with fine.`
  line
  line `(3) The imprisonment referred to in clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) of sub-section (1) and sub-section (2)`
  line `shall, in the absence of special and adequate reasons to the contrary to be recorded in the judgment of the`
  line `Court, be for a term not less than six months.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all`
  line `offences under this Act, except the offences referred to in sub-section (5) shall be non-cognizable and`
  line bailable.
  line
  line `(5) The offences specified in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) or clause (d) of sub-section (1) and`
  line `punishable under clause (i) of that sub-section shall be cognizable and non-bailable.`
  line
  line `(6) A person shall not be prosecuted for any offence under this section except with the previous`
  line `sanction of the Commissioner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, the term "tax" shall include the amount of tax evaded or`
  line `the amount of input tax credit wrongly availed or utilised or refund wrongly taken under the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the State Goods and Services Tax Act, the Integrated Goods and Services Tax Act or the Union`
  line `Territory Goods and Services Tax Act and cess levied under the Goods and Services Tax (Compensation to`
  line `States) Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 127, for "Whoever commits any of the following offences" (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `3. The words ", fraudulently avails input tax credit" omitted by s. 127,ibid., (w.e.f. 1-1-2021).`
  line
  line `4. Clauses (g), (j) and (k) omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 156, (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 156, ibid., for the words brackets and letters "clauses (a) to (k)" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 156, ibid., for "any other offence" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `7. The words, brackets and letters "or clause (g) or clause (j)" omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 156, (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (5248)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 145
  title `Liability of officers and certain other persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5248&sectionno=133&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person engaged in connection`
  line `with the collection of statistics under section 151 or compilation or computerisation thereof or if any`
  line `officer of central tax having access to information specified under sub-section (1) of section 150, or if any`
  line `person engaged in connection with the provision of service on the common portal or the agent of common`
  line `portal, wilfully discloses any information or the contents of any return furnished under this Act or rules`
  line `made thereunder otherwise than in execution of his duties under the said sections or for the purposes of`
  line `prosecution for an offence under this Act or under any other Act for the time being in force, he shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months or with fine which may extend`
  line `to twenty-five thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person--`
  line
  line `(a) who is a Government servant shall not be prosecuted for any offence under this section except`
  line `with the previous sanction of the Government;`
  line
  line `(b) who is not a Government servant shall not be prosecuted for any offence under this section`
  line `except with the previous sanction of the Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (5249)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 146
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5249&sectionno=134&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder except with the previous sanction of the Commissioner, and no court`
  line `inferior to that of a Magistrate of the First Class, shall try any such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (5250)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 147
  title `Presumption of culpable mental state.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5250&sectionno=135&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `In any prosecution for an offence under this Act`
  line `which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the existence of`
  line `such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no such mental`
  line `state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(i) the expression "culpable mental state" includes intention, motive, knowledge of a fact, and`
  line `belief in, or reason to believe, a fact;`
  line
  line `(ii) a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist beyond reasonable doubt`
  line `and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of probability.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (5251)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 148
  title `Relevancy of statements under certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5251&sectionno=136&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `A statement made and signed by a`
  line `person on appearance in response to any summons issued under section 70 during the course of any`
  line `inquiry or proceedings under this Act shall be relevant, for the purpose of proving, in any prosecution for`
  line `an offence under this Act, the truth of the facts which it contains,--`
  line
  line `(a) when the person who made the statement is dead or cannot be found, or is incapable of giving`
  line `evidence, or is kept out of the way by the adverse party, or whose presence cannot be obtained`
  line `without an amount of delay or expense which, under the circumstances of the case, the court`
  line `considers unreasonable; or`
  line
  line `(b) when the person who made the statement is examined as a witness in the case before the court and`
  line `the court is of the opinion that, having regard to the circumstances of the case, the statement should be`
  line `admitted in evidence in the interest of justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (5252)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 149
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5252&sectionno=137&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence committed by a person under this Act is a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a taxable person being a partnership firm`
  line `or a Limited Liability Partnership or a Hindu Undivided Family or a trust, the partner or karta or`
  line `managing trustee shall be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly and the provisions of sub-section (2) shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to such`
  line persons.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing contained in this section shall render any such person liable to any punishment provided`
  line `in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `Explanation--- For the purposes of this section,---`
  line
  line `(i) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (5253)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 150
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5253&sectionno=138&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence under this Act may, either before or after the`
  line `institution of prosecution, be compounded by the Commissioner on payment, by the person accused of the`
  line `offence, to the Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, of such compounding`
  line `amount in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) a person who has been allowed to compound once in respect of any of the offences specified`
  line `in clauses (a) to (f), (h), (i) and (l) of sub-section (1) of section 132;]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `^3[(c) a person who has been accused of committing an offence under clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 132;]`
  line
  line `(d) a person who has been convicted for an offence under this Act by a court;`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(f) any other class of persons or offences as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any compounding allowed under the provisions of this section shall not affect`
  line `the proceedings, if any, instituted under any other law:`
  line
  line `Provided also that compounding shall be allowed only after making payment of tax, interest and`
  line `penalty involved in such offences.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount for compounding of offences under this section shall be such as may be prescribed,`
  line `subject to the minimum amount not being less than ^5[twenty-five per cent. of the tax involved and the`
  line `maximum amount not being more than one hundred per cent. of the tax involved].`
  line
  line `(3) On payment of such compounding amount as may be determined by the Commissioner, no further`
  line `proceedings shall be initiated under this Act against the accused person in respect of the same offence and`
  line `any criminal proceedings, if already initiated in respect of the said offence, shall stand abated.`
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 157, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `2. Cl (b) omitted by Act 8 of 2023, s. 157, (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 157, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `4. Cl (e) omitted by s. 157,ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 157, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (5254)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 151
  title `Migration of existing taxpayers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5254&sectionno=139&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the appointed day, every person registered`
  line `under any of the existing laws and having a valid Permanent Account Number shall be issued a certificate`
  line `of registration on provisional basis, subject to such conditions and in such form and manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, which unless replaced by a final certificate of registration under sub-section (2), shall be liable`
  line `to be cancelled if the conditions so prescribed are not complied with.`
  line
  line `(2) The final certificate of registration shall be granted in such form and manner and subject to such`
  line `conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The certificate of registration issued to a person under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to have not`
  line `been issued if the said registration is cancelled in pursuance of an application filed by such person that he`
  line `was not liable to registration under section 22 or section 24.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (5255)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 152
  title `Transitional arrangements for input tax credit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5255&sectionno=140&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered person, other than a person opting to pay tax under section 10, shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, the amount of CENVAT credit ^1[of eligible duties] carried forward in the return relating to the period ending with the day immediately preceding the appointed day, furnished by him under the existing law ^2[within such time and] in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered person shall not be allowed to take credit in the following`
  line `circumstances, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) where the said amount of credit is not admissible as input tax credit under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where he has not furnished all the returns required under the existing law for the period of six months immediately preceding the appointed date; or`
  line
  line `(iii) here the said amount of credit relates to goods manufactured and cleared under such exemption notifications as are notified by the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) A registered person, other than a person opting to pay tax under section 10, shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, credit of the unavailed CENVAT credit in respect of capital goods, not carried forward in a return, furnished under the existing law by him, for the period ending with the day immediately preceding the appointed day ^2[within such time and] in such manner as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered person shall not be allowed to take credit unless the said credit was admissible as CENVAT credit under the existing law and is also admissible as input tax credit under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the expression "unavailed CENVAT credit" means the amount that remains after subtracting the amount of CENVAT credit already availed in respect of capital goods by the taxable person under the existing law from the aggregate amount of CENVAT credit to which the said person was entitled in respect of the said capital goods under the existing law.`
  line
  line `(3) A registered person, who was not liable to be registered under the existing law, or who was engaged in the manufacture of exempted goods or provision of exempted services, or who was providing works contract service and was availing of the benefit of notification No. 26/2012Service Tax, dated the 20th June, 2012 or a first stage dealer or a second stage dealer or a registered importer or a depot of a manufacturer, shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, credit of eligible duties in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished ^3[goods held in stock on the appointed day, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, subject to] the following conditions,`
  line `namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) such inputs or goods are used or intended to be used for making taxable supplies under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(ii) the said registered person is eligible for input tax credit on such inputs under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) the said registered person is in possession of invoice or other prescribed documents`
  line `evidencing payment of duty under the existing law in respect of such inputs;`
  line
  line `(iv) such invoices or other prescribed documents were issued not earlier than twelve months`
  line `immediately preceding the appointed day; and`
  line
  line `(v) the supplier of services is not eligible for any abatement under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a registered person, other than a manufacturer or a supplier of services, is not in possession of an invoice or any other documents evidencing payment of duty in respect of inputs, then, such registered person shall, subject to such conditions, limitations and safeguards as may be prescribed, including that the said taxable person shall pass on the benefit of such credit by way of reduced prices to the recipient, be allowed to take credit at such rate and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) A registered person, who was engaged in the manufacture of taxable as well as exempted goods under the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) or provision of taxable as well as exempted services under Chapter V of the Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994), but which are liable to tax under this Act, shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger,--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of CENVAT credit carried forward in a return furnished under the existing law by him in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1); and`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of CENVAT credit of eligible duties in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock on the appointed day, relating to such exempted goods or services, in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(5) A registered person shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, credit of eligible duties and taxes in respect of inputs or input services received on or after the appointed day but the duty or tax in respect of which has been paid by the supplier under the ^4[existing law, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed], subject to the condition that the invoice or any other duty or tax paying document of the same was recorded in the books of account of such person within a period of thirty days from the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of thirty days may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the Commissioner for a further period not exceeding thirty days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that said registered person shall furnish a statement, in such manner as may be prescribed, in respect of credit that has been taken under this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(6) A registered person, who was either paying tax at a fixed rate or paying a fixed amount in lieu of the tax payable under the existing law shall be entitled to take, in his electronic credit ledger, credit of eligible duties in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished ^3[goods held in stock on the appointed day, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, subject to] the following conditions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) such inputs or goods are used or intended to be used for making taxable supplies under this Act;`
  line
  line `(ii) the said registered person is not paying tax under section 10;`
  line
  line `(iii) the said registered person is eligible for input tax credit on such inputs under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iv) the said registered person is in possession of invoice or other prescribed documents`
  line `evidencing payment of duty under the existing law in respect of inputs; and`
  line
  line `(v) such invoices or other prescribed documents were issued not earlier than twelve months`
  line `immediately preceding the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(7) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act, the input tax credit on account of any services received prior to the appointed day by an Input Service Distributor shall be eligible for distribution as ^5[credit under this Act, within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, ^6[whether the invoices relating to such services are received prior to, on or after, the appointed day]].`
  line
  line `(8) Where a registered person having centralised registration under the existing law has obtained a registration under this Act, such person shall be allowed to take, in his electronic credit ledger, credit of the amount of CENVAT credit carried forward in a return, furnished under the existing law by him, in respect of the period ending with the day immediately preceding the appointed day ^7[within such time and in such manner] as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the registered person furnishes his return for the period ending with the day`
  line `immediately preceding the appointed day within three months of the appointed day, such credit shall be`
  line `allowed subject to the condition that the said return is either an original return or a revised return where the`
  line `credit has been reduced from that claimed earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the registered person shall not be allowed to take credit unless the said amount is`
  line `admissible as input tax credit under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such credit may be transferred to any of the registered persons having the same Permanent Account Number for which the centralised registration was obtained under the existing law.`
  line
  line `(9) Where any CENVAT credit availed for the input services provided under the existing law has been reversed due to non-payment of the consideration within a period of three months, such ^8[credit can be reclaimed within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed, subject to] the condition that the registered person has made the payment of the consideration for that supply of services within a period of`
  line `three months from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(10) The amount of credit under sub-sections (3), (4) and (6) shall be calculated in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `Explanation1.--For the purposes of ^9[sub-sections (1), (3), (4)] and (6), the expression "eligible duties" means--`
  line
  line `(i) the additional duty of excise leviable under section 3 of the Additional Duties of Excise`
  line `(Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(ii) the additional duty leviable under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975);`
  line
  line `(iii) the additional duty leviable under sub-section (5) of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act,`
  line `1975 (51 of 1975);`
  line
  line `^10* * * * *`
  line
  line `(v) the duty of excise specified in the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(vi) the duty of excise specified in the Second Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985`
  line `(5 of 1986); and`
  line
  line `(vii) the National Calamity Contingent Duty leviable under section 136 of the Finance Act, 2001 (14 of 2001),`
  line
  line `in respect of inputs held in stock and inputs contained in semi-finished or finished goods held in stock on the appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--- For the purposes of ^11[sub-sections (1) and (5)], the expression "eligible duties and taxes" means---`
  line
  line `(i) the additional duty of excise leviable under section 3 of the Additional Duties of Excise (Goods of Special Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957);`
  line
  line `(ii) the additional duty leviable under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975);`
  line
  line `(iii) the additional duty leviable under sub-section (5) of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act,`
  line `1975 (51 of 1975);`
  line
  line `^12* * * * *`
  line
  line `(iv) the additional duty of excise leviable under section 3 of the Additional Duties of Excise`
  line `(Textiles and Textile Articles) Act, 1978 (40 of 1978);`
  line
  line `(v) the duty of excise specified in the First Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985`
  line `(5 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(vi) the duty of excise specified in the Second Schedule to the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(vii) the National Calamity Contingent Duty leviable under section 136 of the Finance Act, 2001 (14 of 2001); and`
  line
  line `(viii) the service tax leviable under section 66B of the Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994),`
  line `in respect of inputs and input services received on or after the appointed day.`
  line
  line `^13[Explanation 3.--For removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that the expression "eligible dutiesand taxes" excludes any cess which has not been specified in Explanation 1 or Explanation 2 and any cess which is collected as additional duty of customs under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Customs Tariff Act, 1975 (51 of 1975).]`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 28 (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 128 (w.e.f. 18-05-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 128, ibid., for "goods held in stock on the appointed day subject to" (w.e.f. 18-5-2020)`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 128, for "existing law" (w.e.f. 18-5-2020).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 128, ibid., for "credit under this Act even if" (w.e.f. 18-5-2020).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 147, for "even if the invoices relating to such services are received on or after the appointed day" (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 128, for "in such manner" (w.e.f. 18-5-2020).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 128, for "credit can be reclaimed subject to" (w.e.f. 18-5-2020).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 28, for "sub-section (3), (4)" (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `10. Cl. (iv) omitted by s. 28, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for "sub-section (5)" (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `12. Cl. (iv) omitted by s. 28, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by s. 28, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-7-2017).`
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (5256)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 153
  title `Transitional provisions relating to job work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5256&sectionno=141&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any inputs received at a place of`
  line `business had been removed as such or removed after being partially processed to a job worker for further`
  line `processing, testing, repair, reconditioning or any other purpose in accordance with the provisions of existing law prior to the appointed day and such inputs are returned to the said place on or after the`
  line `appointed day, no tax shall be payable if such inputs, after completion of the job work or otherwise, are`
  line `returned to the said place within six months from the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line `Commissioner for a further period not exceeding two months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if such inputs are not returned within the period specified in this sub-section, the`
  line `input tax credit shall be liable to be recovered in accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 142.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any semi-finished goods had been removed from the place of business to any other`
  line `premises for carrying out certain manufacturing processes in accordance with the provisions of existing`
  line `law prior to the appointed day and such goods (hereafter in this section referred to as "the said goods")`
  line `are returned to the said place on or after the appointed day, no tax shall be payable, if the said goods, after`
  line `undergoing manufacturing processes or otherwise, are returned to the said place within six months from`
  line `the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line `Commissioner for a further period not exceeding two months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the said goods are not returned within the period specified in this`
  line `sub-section, the input tax credit shall be liable to be recovered in accordance with the provisions of clause`
  line `(a) of sub-section (8) of section 142:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the manufacturer may, in accordance with the provisions of the existing law,`
  line `transfer the said goods to the premises of any registered person for the purpose of supplying therefrom on`
  line `payment of tax in India or without payment of tax for exports within the period specified in this`
  line sub-section.
  line
  line `(3) Where any excisable goods manufactured at a place of business had been removed without`
  line `payment of duty for carrying out tests or any other process not amounting to manufacture, to any other`
  line `premises, whether registered or not, in accordance with the provisions of existing law prior to the appointed`
  line `day and such goods, are returned to the said place on or after the appointed day, no tax shall be payable if`
  line `the said goods, after undergoing tests or any other process, are returned to the said place within six months`
  line `from the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line `Commissioner for a further period not exceeding two months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that if the said goods are not returned within the period specified in this`
  line `sub-section, the input tax credit shall be liable to be recovered in accordance with the provisions of`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (8) of section 142:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the manufacturer may, in accordance with the provisions of the existing law,`
  line `transfer the said goods from the said other premises on payment of tax in India or without payment of tax`
  line `for exports within the period specified in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(4) The tax under sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall not be payable, only if the manufacturer and the`
  line `job worker declare the details of the inputs or goods held in stock by the job worker on behalf of the`
  line `manufacturer on the appointed day in such form and manner and within such time as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (5257)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 154
  title `Miscellaneous transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5257&sectionno=142&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any goods on which duty, if any, had been`
  line `paid under the existing law at the time of removal thereof, not being earlier than six months prior to the`
  line `appointed day, are returned to any place of business on or after the appointed day, the registered person shall`
  line `be eligible for refund of the duty paid under the existing law where such goods are returned by a person, other`
  line `than a registered person, to the said place of business within a period of six months from the appointed day`
  line `and such goods are identifiable to the satisfaction of the proper officer:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the said goods are returned by a registered person, the return of such goods shall be`
  line `deemed to be a supply.`
  line
  line `(2) (a) where, in pursuance of a contract entered into prior to the appointed day, the price of any goods`
  line `or services or both is revised upwards on or after the appointed day, the registered person who had`
  line `removed or provided such goods or services or both shall issue to the recipient a supplementary invoice or`
  line `debit note, containing such particulars as may be prescribed, within thirty days of such price revision and`
  line `for the purposes of this Act such supplementary invoice or debit note shall be deemed to have been issued`
  line `in respect of an outward supply made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where, in pursuance of a contract entered into prior to the appointed day, the price of any goods or`
  line `services or both is revised downwards on or after the appointed day, the registered person who had removed`
  line `or provided such goods or services or both may issue to the recipient a credit note, containing such`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed, within thirty days of such price revision and for the purposes of this Act`
  line `such credit note shall be deemed to have been issued in respect of an outward supply made under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the registered person shall be allowed to reduce his tax liability on account of issue of`
  line `the credit note only if the recipient of the credit note has reduced his input tax credit corresponding to`
  line `such reduction of tax liability.`
  line
  line `(3) Every claim for refund filed by any person before, on or after the appointed day, for refund of any`
  line `amount of CENVAT credit, duty, tax, interest or any other amount paid under the existing law, shall be`
  line `disposed of in accordance with the provisions of existing law and any amount eventually accruing to him`
  line `shall be paid in cash, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained under the provisions of existing law`
  line `other than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944):`
  line
  line `Provided that where any claim for refund of CENVAT credit is fully or partially rejected, the amount`
  line `so rejected shall lapse:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no refund shall be allowed of any amount of CENVAT credit where the balance`
  line `of the said amount as on the appointed day has been carried forward under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Every claim for refund filed after the appointed day for refund of any duty or tax paid under existing`
  line `law in respect of the goods or services exported before or after the appointed day, shall be disposed of in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the existing law:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any claim for refund of CENVAT credit is fully or partially rejected, the amount`
  line `so rejected shall lapse:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no refund shall be allowed of any amount of CENVAT credit where the balance`
  line `of the said amount as on the appointed day has been carried forward under this Act.`
  line
  line `(5) Every claim filed by a person after the appointed day for refund of tax paid under the existing law in`
  line `respect of services not provided shall be disposed of in accordance with the provisions of existing law and`
  line `any amount eventually accruing to him shall be paid in cash, notwithstanding anything to the contrary`
  line `contained under the provisions of existing law other than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B`
  line `of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944).`
  line
  line `(6) (a) every proceeding of appeal, review or reference relating to a claim for CENVAT credit initiated`
  line `whether before, on or after the appointed day under the existing law shall be disposed of in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of existing law, and any amount of credit found to be admissible to the claimant shall be`
  line `refunded to him in cash, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained under the provisions of existing`
  line `law other than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944)`
  line `and the amount rejected, if any, shall not be admissible as input tax credit under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no refund shall be allowed of any amount of CENVAT credit where the balance of the`
  line `said amount as on the appointed day has been carried forward under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) every proceeding of appeal, review or reference relating to recovery of CENVAT credit initiated`
  line `whether before, on or after the appointed day under the existing law shall be disposed of in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of existing law and if any amount of credit becomes recoverable as a result of such appeal,`
  line `review or reference, the same shall, unless recovered under the existing law, be recovered as an arrear of tax`
  line `under this Act and the amount so recovered shall not be admissible as input tax credit under this Act.`
  line
  line `(7) (a) every proceeding of appeal, review or reference relating to any output duty or tax liability`
  line `initiated whether before, on or after the appointed day under the existing law, shall be disposed of in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of the existing law, and if any amount becomes recoverable as a result of`
  line `such appeal, review or reference, the same shall, unless recovered under the existing law, be recovered`
  line `as an arrear of duty or tax under this Act and the amount so recovered shall not be admissible as input`
  line `tax credit under this Act.`
  line
  line `(b) every proceeding of appeal, review or reference relating to any output duty or tax liability initiated`
  line `whether before, on or after the appointed day under the existing law, shall be disposed of in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of the existing law, and any amount found to be admissible to the claimant shall be refunded to`
  line `him in cash, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained under the provisions of existing law other`
  line `than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and the`
  line `amount rejected, if any, shall not be admissible as input tax credit under this Act.`
  line
  line `(8) (a) where in pursuance of an assessment or adjudication proceedings instituted, whether before,`
  line `on or after the appointed day, under the existing law, any amount of tax, interest, fine or penalty becomes`
  line `recoverable from the person, the same shall, unless recovered under the existing law, be recovered as an`
  line `arrear of tax under this Act and the amount so recovered shall not be admissible as input tax credit under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where in pursuance of an assessment or adjudication proceedings instituted, whether before, on or after`
  line `the appointed day, under the existing law, any amount of tax, interest, fine or penalty becomes refundable to the`
  line `taxable person, the same shall be refunded to him in cash under the said law, notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in the said law other than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B of the Central`
  line `Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and the amount rejected, if any, shall not be admissible as input tax credit under`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(9) (a) where any return, furnished under the existing law, is revised after the appointed day and if,`
  line `pursuant to such revision, any amount is found to be recoverable or any amount of CENVAT credit is found to`
  line `be inadmissible, the same shall, unless recovered under the existing law, be recovered as an arrear of tax under`
  line `this Act and the amount so recovered shall not be admissible as input tax credit under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) where any return, furnished under the existing law, is revised after the appointed day but within the`
  line `time limit specified for such revision under the existing law and if, pursuant to such revision, any amount is`
  line `found to be refundable or CENVAT credit is found to be admissible to any taxable person, the same shall be`
  line `refunded to him in cash under the existing law, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the said`
  line `law other than the provisions of sub-section (2) of section 11B of the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) and`
  line `the amount rejected, if any, shall not be admissible as input tax credit under this Act.`
  line
  line `(10) Save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, the goods or services or both supplied on or after the`
  line `appointed day in pursuance of a contract entered into prior to the appointed day shall be liable to tax`
  line `under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(11) (a) notwithstanding anything contained in section 12, no tax shall be payable on goods under this`
  line `Act to the extent the tax was leviable on the said goods under the Value Added Tax Act of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) notwithstanding anything contained in section 13, no tax shall be payable on services under this`
  line `Act to the extent the tax was leviable on the said services under Chapter V of the Finance Act, 1994`
  line `(32 of 1994);`
  line
  line `(c) where tax was paid on any supply both under the Value Added Tax Act and under Chapter V of the`
  line `Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994), tax shall be leviable under this Act and the taxable person shall be entitled to take credit of value added tax or service tax paid under the existing law to the extent of supplies made after`
  line `the appointed day and such credit shall be calculated in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(12) Where any goods sent on approval basis, not earlier than six months before the appointed day,`
  line `are rejected or not approved by the buyer and returned to the seller on or after the appointed day, no tax`
  line `shall be payable thereon if such goods are returned within six months from the appointed day:`
  line
  line `Provided that the said period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the`
  line `Commissioner for a further period not exceeding two months:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the tax shall be payable by the person returning the goods if such goods are`
  line `liable to tax under this Act, and are returned after a period specified in this sub-section:`
  line
  line `Provided also that tax shall be payable by the person who has sent the goods on approval basis if such`
  line `goods are liable to tax under this Act, and are not returned within a period specified in this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(13) Where a supplier has made any sale of goods in respect of which tax was required to be deducted`
  line `at source under any law of a State or Union territory relating to Value Added Tax and has also issued an`
  line `invoice for the same before the appointed day, no deduction of tax at source under section 51 shall be`
  line `made by the deductor under the said section where payment to the said supplier is made on or after the`
  line `appointed day.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this Chapter, the expressions "capital goods", "Central Value`
  line `Added Tax (CENVAT) credit", "first stage dealer", "second stage dealer", or "manufacture" shall have`
  line `the same meaning as respectively assigned to them in the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) or the`
  line `rules made thereunder`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (5258)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 155
  title `Job work procedure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 2018, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-2-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5258&sectionno=143&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `(1) A registered person (hereafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `"principal") may under intimation and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, send any inputs or capital goods, without payment of tax, to a job worker for job work and from there subsequently send to another job worker and likewise, and shall,---`
  line
  line `(a) bring back inputs, after completion of job work or otherwise, or capital goods, other than moulds and dies, jigs and fixtures, or tools, within one year and three years, respectively, of their being sent out, to any of his place of business, without payment of tax;`
  line
  line `(b) supply such inputs, after completion of job work or otherwise, or capital goods, other than moulds and dies, jigs and fixtures, or tools, within one year and three years, respectively, of their being sent out from the place of business of a job worker on payment of tax within India, or with or without payment of tax for export, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that the principal shall not supply the goods from the place of business of a job worker in accordance with the provisions of this clause unless the said principal declares the place of business of the job worker as his additional place of business except in a case---`
  line
  line `(i) where the job worker is registered under section 25; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the principal is engaged in the supply of such goods as may be notified by the`
  line Commissioner.
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that the period of one year and three years may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended by the Commissioner for a further period not exceeding one year and two years respectively.]`
  line
  line `(2) The responsibility for keeping proper accounts for the inputs or capital goods shall lie with the principal.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the inputs sent for job work are not received back by the principal after completion of job work or otherwise in accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) or are not supplied from the place of business of the job worker in accordance with the provisions of clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `within a period of one year of their being sent out, it shall be deemed that such inputs had been supplied by the principal to the job worker on the day when the said inputs were sent out.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the capital goods, other than moulds and dies, jigs and fixtures, or tools, sent for job work are not received back by the principal in accordance with the provisions of clause (a) of sub-section (1) or are not supplied from the place of business of the job worker in accordance with the provisions of clause (b) of sub-section (1) within a period of three years of their being sent out, it shall be deemed that such capital goods had been supplied by the principal to the job worker on the day when the said capital goods were sent out.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), any waste and scrap generated during the job work may be supplied by the job worker directly from his place of business on payment of tax, if such job worker is registered, or by the principal, if the job worker is not registered.`
  line
  line `Explanation--- For the purposes of job work, input includes intermediate goods arising from any treatment`
  line `or process carried out on the inputs by the principal or the job worker.`
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (5259)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 156
  title `Presumption as to documents in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5259&sectionno=144&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `Where any document---`
  line
  line `(i) is produced by any person under this Act or any other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(ii) has been seized from the custody or control of any person under this Act or any other law for`
  line `the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) has been received from any place outside India in the course of any proceedings under this`
  line `Act or any other law for the time being in force,`
  line
  line `and such document is tendered by the prosecution in evidence against him or any other person who is`
  line `tried jointly with him, the court shall---`
  line
  line `(a) unless the contrary is proved by such person, presume---`
  line
  line `(i) the truth of the contents of such document;`
  line
  line `(ii) that the signature and every other part of such document which purports to be in the`
  line `handwriting of any particular person or which the court may reasonably assume to have been`
  line `signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, is in that persons`
  line `handwriting, and in the case of a document executed or attested, that it was executed or`
  line `attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested;`
  line
  line `(b) admit the document in evidence notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such`
  line `document is otherwise admissible in evidence.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (5260)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 157
  title `Admissibility of micro films, facsimile copies of documents and computer printouts as documents and as evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5260&sectionno=145&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force,---`
  line
  line `(a) a micro film of a document or the reproduction of the image or images embodied in such`
  line `micro film (whether enlarged or not); or`
  line
  line `(b) a facsimile copy of a document; or`
  line
  line `(c) a statement contained in a document and included in a printed material produced by a`
  line `computer, subject to such conditions as may be prescribed; or`
  line
  line `(d) any information stored electronically in any device or media, including any hard copies made`
  line `of such information,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be a document for the purposes of this Act and the rules made thereunder and shall be`
  line `admissible in any proceedings thereunder, without further proof or production of the original, as evidence`
  line `of any contents of the original or of any fact stated therein of which direct evidence would be admissible.`
  line
  line `(2) In any proceedings under this Act or the rules made thereunder, where it is desired to give a`
  line `statement in evidence by virtue of this section, a certificate,---`
  line
  line `(a) identifying the document containing the statement and describing the manner in which it was`
  line produced;
  line
  line `(b) giving such particulars of any device involved in the production of that document as may be`
  line `appropriate for the purpose of showing that the document was produced by a computer,`
  line
  line `shall be evidence of any matter stated in the certificate and for the purposes of this sub-section it shall be`
  line `sufficient for a matter to be stated to the best of the knowledge and belief of the person stating it.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (5261)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 158
  title `Common Portal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5261&sectionno=146&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, notify the`
  line `Common Goods and Services Tax Electronic Portal for facilitating registration, payment of tax, furnishing of`
  line `returns, computation and settlement of integrated tax, electronic way bill and for carrying out such other`
  line `functions and for such purposes as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (5262)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 159
  title `Deemed exports.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5262&sectionno=147&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, notify`
  line `certain supplies of goods as deemed exports, where goods supplied do not leave India, and payment for`
  line `such supplies is received either in Indian rupees or in convertible foreign exchange, if such goods are`
  line `manufactured in India.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (5263)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 160
  title `Special procedure for certain processes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5263&sectionno=148&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `The Government may, on the recommendations of`
  line `the Council, and subject to such conditions and safeguards as may be prescribed, notify certain classes of`
  line `registered persons, and the special procedures to be followed by such persons including those with regard`
  line `to registration, furnishing of return, payment of tax and administration of such persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (5264)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 161
  title `Goods and services tax compliance rating.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5264&sectionno=149&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every registered person may be assigned a`
  line `goods and services tax compliance rating score by the Government based on his record of compliance`
  line `with the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2)The goods and services tax compliance rating score may be determined on the basis of such`
  line `parameters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The goods and services tax compliance rating score may be updated at periodic intervals and`
  line `intimated to the registered person and also placed in the public domain in such manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (5265)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 162
  title `Obligation to furnish information return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5265&sectionno=150&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, being--`
  line
  line `(a) a taxable person; or`
  line
  line `(b) a local authority or other public body or association; or`
  line
  line `(c) any authority of the State Government responsible for the collection of value added tax or`
  line `sales tax or State excise duty or an authority of the Central Government responsible for the collection`
  line `of excise duty or customs duty; or`
  line
  line `(d) an income-tax authority appointed under the provisions of the Income-tax Act, 1961`
  line `(43 of 1961); or`
  line
  line `(e) a banking company within the meaning of clause (a) of section 45A of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(f) a State Electricity Board or an electricity distribution or transmission licensee under the`
  line `Electricity Act, 2003 (36 of 2003), or any other entity entrusted with such functions by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government; or`
  line
  line `(g) the Registrar or Sub-Registrar appointed under section 6 of the Registration Act, 1908`
  line `(16 of 1908); or`
  line
  line `(h) a Registrar within the meaning of the Companies Act, 2013 (18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(i) the registering authority empowered to register motor vehicles under the Motor Vehicles Act,`
  line `1988 (59 of 1988); or`
  line
  line `(j) the Collector referred to in clause (c) of section 3 of the Right to Fair Compensation and`
  line `Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013 (30 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(k) the recognised stock exchange referred to in clause (f) of section 2 of the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956); or`
  line
  line `(l) a depository referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Depositories Act,`
  line `1996 (22 of 1996); or`
  line
  line `(m) an officer of the Reserve Bank of India as constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of`
  line `India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934); or`
  line
  line `(n) the Goods and Services Tax Network, a company registered under the Companies Act, 2013`
  line `(18 of 2013); or`
  line
  line `(o) a person to whom a Unique Identity Number has been granted under sub-section (9) of`
  line `section 25; or`
  line
  line `(p) any other person as may be specified, on the recommendations of the Council, by the`
  line Government,
  line
  line `who is responsible for maintaining record of registration or statement of accounts or any periodic return or`
  line `document containing details of payment of tax and other details of transaction of goods or services or both or`
  line `transactions related to a bank account or consumption of electricity or transaction of purchase, sale or`
  line `exchange of goods or property or right or interest in a property under any law for the time being in force, shall`
  line `furnish an information return of the same in respect of such periods, within such time, in such form and`
  line `manner and to such authority or agency as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Commissioner, or an officer authorised by him in this behalf, considers that the`
  line `information furnished in the information return is defective, he may intimate the defect to the person who`
  line `has furnished such information return and give him an opportunity of rectifying the defect within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of such intimation or within such further period which, on an application made in`
  line `this behalf, the said authority may allow and if the defect is not rectified within the said period of thirty days`
  line `or, the further period so allowed, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this`
  line `Act, such information return shall be treated as not furnished and the provisions of this Act shall apply.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a person who is required to furnish information return has not furnished the same within`
  line `the time specified in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the said authority may serve upon him a notice`
  line `requiring furnishing of such information return within a period not exceeding ninety days from the date of`
  line `service of the notice and such person shall furnish the information return.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (5266)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 163
  title `Power to call for information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 119, for section 151 (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5266&sectionno=151&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `^1[151. Power to call for information.--- The Commissioner or an officer authorised by him may, by`
  line `an order, direct any person to furnish information relating to any matter dealt with in connection with this`
  line `Act, within such time, in such form, and in such manner, as may be specified therein.]`
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (5267)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 164
  title `Bar on disclosure of information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5267&sectionno=152&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) No information ^1*** with respect to any matter given for`
  line `the purposes of section 150 or section 151 shall, without the previous consent in writing of the concerned`
  line `person or his authorised representative, be published in such manner so as to enable such particulars to be`
  line `identified as referring to a particular person and no such information shall be used for the purpose of any`
  line `proceedings under this Act ^2[without giving an opportunity of being heard to the person concerned].`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in this section shall apply to the publication of any information relating to a class of taxable`
  line `persons or class of transactions, if in the opinion of the Commissioner, it is desirable in the public interest to`
  line `publish such information.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "of any individual return or part thereof" omitted by s. 120, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 120, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `3. Sub-section (2) omitted by s. 120, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (5268)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 165
  title `Taking assistance from an expert.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5268&sectionno=153&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `Any officer not below the rank of Assistant Commissioner`
  line `may, having regard to the nature and complexity of the case and the interest of revenue, take assistance of`
  line `any expert at any stage of scrutiny, inquiry, investigation or any other proceedings before him.`
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (5269)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 166
  title `Power to take samples.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5269&sectionno=154&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner or an officer authorised by him may take samples`
  line `of goods from the possession of any taxable person, where he considers it necessary, and provide a receipt`
  line `for any samples so taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (5270)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 167
  title `Burden of proof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5270&sectionno=155&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `Where any person claims that he is eligible for input tax credit under this`
  line `Act, the burden of proving such claim shall lie on such person.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (5271)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 168
  title `Persons deemed to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5271&sectionno=156&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `All persons discharging functions under this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (5272)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 169
  title `Protection of action take under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5272&sectionno=157&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings`
  line `shall lie against the President, State President, Members, officers or other employees of the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal or any other person authorised by the said Appellate Tribunal for anything which is in good faith`
  line `done or intended to be done under this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall lie against any officer appointed or`
  line `authorised under this Act for anything which is done or intended to be done in good faith under this Act`
  line `or the rules made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (5273)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 170
  title `Disclosure of information by a public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5273&sectionno=158&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `(1) All particulars contained in any statement`
  line `made, return furnished or accounts or documents produced in accordance with this Act, or in any record of`
  line `evidence given in the course of any proceedings under this Act (other than proceedings before a criminal`
  line `court), or in any record of any proceedings under this Act shall, save as provided in sub-section (3), not be`
  line disclosed.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), no court shall,`
  line `save as otherwise provided in sub-section (3), require any officer appointed or authorised under this Act`
  line `to produce before it or to give evidence before it in respect of particulars referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to the disclosure of,--`
  line
  line `(a) any particulars in respect of any statement, return, accounts, documents, evidence, affidavit or`
  line `deposition, for the purpose of any prosecution under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or the`
  line `Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988), or any other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) any particulars to the Central Government or the State Government or to any person acting in`
  line `the implementation of this Act, for the purposes of carrying out the objects of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) any particulars when such disclosure is occasioned by the lawful exercise under this Act of any`
  line `process for the service of any notice or recovery of any demand; or`
  line
  line `(d) any particulars to a civil court in any suit or proceedings, to which the Government or any`
  line `authority under this Act is a party, which relates to any matter arising out of any proceedings under`
  line `this Act or under any other law for the time being in force authorising any such authority to exercise`
  line `any powers thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(e) any particulars to any officer appointed for the purpose of audit of tax receipts or refunds of`
  line `the tax imposed by this Act; or`
  line
  line `(f) any particulars where such particulars are relevant for the purposes of any inquiry into the`
  line `conduct of any officer appointed or authorised under this Act, to any person or persons appointed as`
  line `an inquiry officer under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(g) any such particulars to an officer of the Central Government or of any State Government, as may`
  line `be necessary for the purpose of enabling that Government to levy or realise any tax or duty; or`
  line
  line `(h) any particulars when such disclosure is occasioned by the lawful exercise by a public servant`
  line `or any other statutory authority, of his or its powers under any law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(i) any particulars relevant to any inquiry into a charge of misconduct in connection with any`
  line `proceedings under this Act against a practising advocate, a tax practitioner, a practising cost accountant, a`
  line `practising chartered accountant, a practising company secretary to the authority empowered to take disciplinary action against the members practising the profession of a legal practitioner, a cost`
  line `accountant, a chartered accountant or a company secretary, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(j) any particulars to any agency appointed for the purposes of data entry on any automated`
  line `system or for the purpose of operating, upgrading or maintaining any automated system where such`
  line `agency is contractually bound not to use or disclose such particulars except for the aforesaid`
  line `purposes; or`
  line
  line `(k) any particulars to an officer of the Government as may be necessary for the purposes of any`
  line `other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(l) any information relating to any class of taxable persons or class of transactions for publication,`
  line `if, in the opinion of the Commissioner, it is desirable in the public interest, to publish such`
  line information.
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158_a:
  sectionId (89162)
  sectionNo 158A
  orderNo 171
  title `Consent based sharing of information furnished by taxable person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 8 of 2023, s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=89162&sectionno=158A&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_158_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[158A. Consent based sharing of information furnished by taxable person.--- (1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 133, 152 and 158, the following details furnished by a`
  line `registered person may, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), and on the recommendations of the`
  line `Council, be shared by the common portal with such other systems as may be notified by the Government,`
  line `in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) particulars furnished in the application for registration under section 25 or in the return filed`
  line `under section 39 or under section 44;`
  line
  line `(b) the particulars uploaded on the common portal for preparation of invoice, the details of`
  line `outward supplies furnished under section 37 and the particulars uploaded on the common portal for`
  line `generation of documents under section 68;`
  line
  line `(c) such other details as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sharing details under sub-section (1), the consent shall be obtained, of---`
  line
  line `(a) the supplier, in respect of details furnished under clauses (a), (b) and (c) of sub-section (1);`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) the recipient, in respect of details furnished under clause(b) of sub-section (1), and under`
  line `clause (c) of sub-section (1) only where such details include identity information of the recipient,`
  line
  line `in such form and manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force, no action shall lie`
  line `against the Government or the common portal with respect to any liability arising consequent to`
  line `information shared under this section and there shall be no impact on the liability to pay tax on the`
  line `relevant supply or as per the relevant return.`
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (5274)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 172
  title `Publication of information in respect of persons in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5274&sectionno=159&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Commissioner,`
  line `or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf, is of the opinion that it is necessary or expedient in`
  line `the public interest to publish the name of any person and any other particulars relating to any proceedings`
  line `or prosecution under this Act in respect of such person, it may cause to be published such name and`
  line `particulars in such manner as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(2) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the Appellate Authority under section 107 has expired without`
  line `an appeal having been presented or the appeal, if presented, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of firm, company or other association of persons, the names of the partners`
  line `of the firm, directors, managing agents, secretaries and treasurers or managers of the company, or the`
  line `members of the association, as the case may be, may also be published if, in the opinion of the`
  line `Commissioner, or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf, circumstances of the case justify it.`
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (5275)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 173
  title `Assessment proceedings, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5275&sectionno=160&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `(1) No assessment, reassessment,`
  line `adjudication, review, revision, appeal, rectification, notice, summons or other proceedings done,`
  line `accepted, made, issued, initiated, or purported to have been done, accepted, made, issued, initiated in`
  line `pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act shall be invalid or deemed to be invalid merely by reason of`
  line `any mistake, defect or omission therein, if such assessment, re-assessment, adjudication, review, revision,`
  line `appeal, rectification, notice, summons or other proceedings are in substance and effect in conformity with or`
  line `according to the intents, purposes and requirements of this Act or any existing law.`
  line
  line `(2) The service of any notice, order or communication shall not be called in question, if the notice, order`
  line `or communication, as the case may be, has already been acted upon by the person to whom it is issued or`
  line `where such service has not been called in question at or in the earlier proceedings commenced, continued or`
  line `finalised pursuant to such notice, order or communication.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (5276)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 174
  title `Rectification of errors apparent on the face of record.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5276&sectionno=161&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 160, and notwithstanding anything contained in any other provisions of this Act, any authority, who`
  line `has passed or issued any decision or order or notice or certificate or any other document, may rectify any`
  line `error which is apparent on the face of record in such decision or order or notice or certificate or any other`
  line `document, either on its own motion or where such error is brought to its notice by any officer appointed under`
  line `this Act or an officer appointed under the State Goods and Services Tax Act or an officer appointed under the`
  line `Union Territory Goods and Services Tax Act or by the affected person within a period of three months from`
  line `the date of issue of such decision or order or notice or certificate or any other document, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such rectification shall be done after a period of six months from the date of issue of`
  line `such decision or order or notice or certificate or any other document:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the said period of six months shall not apply in such cases where the`
  line `rectification is purely in the nature of correction of a clerical or arithmetical error, arising from any`
  line `accidental slip or omission:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where such rectification adversely affects any person, the principles of natural justice`
  line `shall be followed by the authority carrying out such rectification.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (5277)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 175
  title `Bar on jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5277&sectionno=162&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `Save as provided in sections 117 and 118, no civil court`
  line `shall have jurisdiction to deal with or decide any question arising from or relating to anything done or`
  line `purported to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (5278)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 176
  title `Levy of fee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5278&sectionno=163&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `Wherever a copy of any order or document is to be provided to any person on an`
  line `application made by him for that purpose, there shall be paid such fee as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (5279)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 177
  title `Power of Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5279&sectionno=164&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Government may, on the recommendations of`
  line `the Council, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1), the Government may make`
  line `rules for all or any of the matters which by this Act are required to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of`
  line `which provisions are to be or may be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect to the rules or any of them from a date not earlier than the date on which the provisions of this Act`
  line `come into force.`
  line
  line `(4) Any rules made under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) may provide that a contravention thereof`
  line `shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding ten thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (5280)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 178
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5280&sectionno=165&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by notification, make regulations consistent with`
  line `this Act and the rules made thereunder to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (5281)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 179
  title `Laying of rules, regulations and notifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5281&sectionno=166&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Government, every`
  line `regulation made by the Board and every notification issued by the Government under this Act, shall be laid,`
  line `as soon as may be after it is made or issued, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if,`
  line `before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or in the notification, as the case may`
  line `be, or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation or the notification should not be made, the rule or`
  line `regulation or notification, as the case may be, shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be`
  line `of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation or notification, as the`
  line `case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (5282)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 180
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5282&sectionno=167&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `The Commissioner may, by notification, direct that subject to such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, any power exercisable by any authority or officer`
  line `under this Act may be exercisable also by another authority or officer as may be specified in such`
  line notification.
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (5283)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 181
  title `Power to issue instructions or directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5283&sectionno=168&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, if it considers it necessary or`
  line `expedient so to do for the purpose of uniformity in the implementation of this Act, issue such orders,`
  line `instructions or directions to the central tax officers as it may deem fit, and thereupon all such officers and`
  line `all other persons employed in the implementation of this Act shall observe and follow such orders,`
  line `instructions or directions.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commissioner specified in clause (91) of section 2, sub-section (3) of section 5, clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (9) of section 25, sub-sections (3) and (4) of section 35, sub-section (1) of section 37,`
  line `^1*** sub-section (6) of section 39, ^2[ ^3[section 44], sub-sections (4) and (5) of section 52,] ^4[sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 143, except the second proviso thereof],`
  line `^5*** clause (l) of sub-section (3) of section 158`
  line `and section 167 shall mean a Commissioner or Joint Secretary posted in the Board and such`
  line `Commissioner or Joint Secretary shall exercise the powers specified in the said sections with the`
  line `approval of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "sub-section (2) of section 38," omitted by Act 6 of 2022, s. 114 (w.e.f. 1-10-2022).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 121, for the words "sub-section (1) of section 44" (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 129, for words "sub-section (5) of section 66, sub-section (1) of section 143" (w.e.f. 30-6-2020).`
  line
  line `5. The words "sub-section (1) of section 151," omitted by Act 13 of 2021, s. 121, (w.e.f. 1-1-2022).`
obj_root_law_sections_168_a:
  sectionId (51543)
  sectionNo 168A
  orderNo 182
  title `Power of Government to extend time limit in special circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 38 of 2020, s. 7 (w.e.f. 31-3-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=51543&sectionno=168A&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_168_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[168A. Power of Government to extend time limit in special circumstances.--(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the Government may, on the recommendations of the`
  line `Council, by notification, extend the time limit specified in, or prescribed or notified under, this Act in`
  line `respect of actions which cannot be completed of complied with due to force majeure.`
  line
  line `(2) The power to issue notification under sub-section (1) shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect to such notification from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, the expression "force majeure" means a case of war,`
  line `epidemic, flood, drought, fire, cyclone, earthquake or any other calamity caused by nature or otherwise`
  line `affecting the implementation of any of the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (5284)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 183
  title `Service of notice in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5284&sectionno=169&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any decision, order, summons, notice or other`
  line `communication under this Act or the rules made thereunder shall be served by any one of the following`
  line `methods, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) by giving or tendering it directly or by a messenger including a courier to the addressee or the`
  line `taxable person or to his manager or authorised representative or an advocate or a tax practitioner`
  line `holding authority to appear in the proceedings on behalf of the taxable person or to a person regularly`
  line `employed by him in connection with the business, or to any adult member of family residing with the`
  line `taxable person; or`
  line
  line `(b) by registered post or speed post or courier with acknowledgment due, to the person for whom`
  line `it is intended or his authorised representative, if any, at his last known place of business or residence;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) by sending a communication to his e-mail address provided at the time of registration or as`
  line `amended from time to time; or`
  line
  line `(d) by making it available on the common portal; or`
  line
  line `(e) by publication in a newspaper circulating in the locality in which the taxable person or the`
  line `person to whom it is issued is last known to have resided, carried on business or personally worked`
  line `for gain; or`
  line
  line `(f) if none of the modes aforesaid is practicable, by affixing it in some conspicuous place at his last`
  line `known place of business or residence and if such mode is not practicable for any reason, then by affixing a`
  line `copy thereof on the notice board of the office of the concerned officer or authority who or which passed`
  line `such decision or order or issued such summons or notice.`
  line
  line `(2) Every decision, order, summons, notice or any communication shall be deemed to have been`
  line `served on the date on which it is tendered or published or a copy thereof is affixed in the manner provided`
  line `in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) When such decision, order, summons, notice or any communication is sent by registered post or`
  line `speed post, it shall be deemed to have been received by the addressee at the expiry of the period normally`
  line `taken by such post in transit unless the contrary is proved.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (5285)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 184
  title `Rounding off of tax, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5285&sectionno=170&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `The amount of tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum payable,`
  line `and the amount of refund or any other sum due, under the provisions of this Act shall be rounded off to`
  line `the nearest rupee and, for this purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee consisting of paise,`
  line `then, if such part is fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee and if such part is less than fifty`
  line `paise it shall be ignored.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (5286)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 185
  title `Anti-profiteering measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5286&sectionno=171&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any reduction in rate of tax on any supply of goods or`
  line `services or the benefit of input tax credit shall be passed on to the recipient by way of commensurate`
  line `reduction in prices.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, on recommendations of the Council, by notification, constitute an`
  line `Authority, or empower an existing Authority constituted under any law for the time being in force, to`
  line `examine whether input tax credits availed by any registered person or the reduction in the tax rate have`
  line `actually resulted in a commensurate reduction in the price of the goods or services or both supplied by him.`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the Government may by notification, on the recommendations of the Council, specify`
  line `the date from which the said Authority shall not accept any request for examination as to whether input`
  line `tax credits availed by any registered person or the reduction in the tax rate have actually resulted in a`
  line `commensurate reduction in the price of the goods or services or both supplied by him.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this sub-section, "request for examination" shall mean the written`
  line `application filed by an applicant requesting for examination as to whether input tax credits availed by any`
  line `registered person or the reduction in the tax rate have actually resulted in a commensurate reduction in the`
  line `price of the goods or services or both supplied by him.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Authority referred to in sub-section (2) shall exercise such powers and discharge such`
  line `functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^2[(3A) Where the Authority referred to in sub-section (2), after holding examination as required under`
  line `the said sub-section comes to the conclusion that any registered person has profiteered under`
  line `sub-section (1), such person shall be liable to pay penalty equivalent to ten per cent. of the amount so`
  line `profiteered:`
  line
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be leviable if the profiteered amount is deposited within thirty days of`
  line `the date of passing of the order by the Authority.`
  line
  line `Explanation.^3[1]--- For the purposes of this section, the expression "profiteered" shall mean the amount`
  line `determined on account of not passing the benefit of reduction in rate of tax on supply of goods or services`
  line `or both or the benefit of input tax credit to the recipient by way of commensurate reduction in the price of`
  line `the goods or services or both.]`
  line
  line `^3[Explanation 2.---For the purposes of this section, the expression "Authority" shall include the`
  line `"Appellate Tribunal".]`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 2024, s. 148 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Renumbered and ins by Act 15 of 2024, s. 148 (w.e.f. 1-11-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (5287)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 186
  title `Removal of difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 12 of 2020, s. 130, for “three years” (w.e.f. 30-6-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5287&sectionno=172&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to any provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Government may, on the recommendations of the Council, by a general or a special order`
  line `published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act or`
  line `the rules or regulations made thereunder, as may be necessary or expedient for the purpose of removing`
  line `the said difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of ^1[five years] from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (5288)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 187
  title `Amendment of Act 32 of 1994.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5288&sectionno=173&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, Chapter V of the`
  line `Finance Act, 1994 shall be omitted.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (5289)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 188
  title `Repeal and saving.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102&sectionId=5289&sectionno=174&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_2_00042_201712_1517807328102
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this Act, on and from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Central Excise Act, 1944 (1 of 1944) (except as respects goods included in`
  line `entry 84 of the Union List of the Seventh Schedule to the Constitution), the Medicinal and Toilet`
  line `Preparations (Excise Duties) Act, 1955 (16 of 1955), the Additional Duties of Excise (Goods of Special`
  line `Importance) Act, 1957 (58 of 1957), the Additional Duties of Excise (Textiles and Textile Articles)`
  line `Act, 1978 (40 of 1978), and the Central Excise Tariff Act, 1985 (5 of 1986) (hereafter referred to as the`
  line `repealed Acts) are hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of the said Acts and the amendment of the Finance Act, 1994 (32 of 1994) (hereafter`
  line `referred to as "such amendment" or "amended Act", as the case may be) to the extent mentioned in the`
  line `sub-section (1) or section 173 shall not--`
  line
  line `(a) revive anything not in force or existing at the time of such amendment or repeal; or`
  line
  line `(b) affect the previous operation of the amended Act or repealed Acts and orders or anything duly`
  line `done or suffered thereunder; or`
  line
  line `(c) affect any right, privilege, obligation, or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the`
  line `amended Act or repealed Acts or orders under such repealed or amended Acts:`
  line
  line `Provided that any tax exemption granted as an incentive against investment through a notification`
  line `shall not continue as privilege if the said notification is rescinded on or after the appointed day; or`
  line
  line `(d) affect any duty, tax, surcharge, fine, penalty, interest as are due or may become due or any`
  line `forfeiture or punishment incurred or inflicted in respect of any offence or violation committed against`
  line `the provisions of the amended Act or repealed Acts; or`
  line
  line `(e) affect any investigation, inquiry, verification (including scrutiny and audit), assessment proceedings,`
  line `adjudication and any other legal proceedings or recovery of arrears or remedy in respect of any such duty,`
  line `tax, surcharge, penalty, fine, interest, right, privilege, obligation, liability, forfeiture or punishment, as`
  line `aforesaid, and any such investigation, inquiry, verification (including scrutiny and audit), assessment`
  line `proceedings, adjudication and other legal proceedings or recovery of arrears or remedy may be instituted,`
  line `continued or enforced, and any such tax, surcharge, penalty, fine, interest, forfeiture or punishment may be`
  line `levied or imposed as if these Acts had not been so amended or repealed; or`
  line
  line `(f) affect any proceedings including that relating to an appeal, review or reference, instituted before on,`
  line `or after the appointed day under the said amended Act or repealed Acts and such proceedings shall be`
  line `continued under the said amended Act or repealed Acts as if this Act had not come into force and the said`
  line `Acts had not been amended or repealed.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of the particular matters referred to in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall not be held to`
  line `prejudice or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with`
  line `regard to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
